      <Placemark>
        <name>Berkshire Youth Wind Orchestra</name>
        <address>Berkshire - UK</address>
        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South East<br>3. County: Berkshire<br>4. Location: Berkshire - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): Wind Band<br>7. Genre: Orchestral<br>8. Age: All Ages<br>9. Level: Grade 8+<br>10. Instruments: Piccolo/Flute, Clarinet, Oboe, Cor Anglais, Bassoon, Trumpet, Trombone, Tuba, Horns, Euphonium<br>11. Other Tags: Grade 8<br>12. Cost: https://www.berksmusictrust.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/Fees-2025-26-FINAL-EXT.pdf<br>13. About Opportunity: Our newly formed wind orchestra is Berkshire Youth Wind Orchestra. Led by Musical Director John Watts, coordinated by Jessica Wilkins, BYWO is the culmination of a student’s orchestral learning, providing members with outstanding orchestral training together with musical, cultural and social experiences that are truly exceptional. BYWO meets three times per year, creating a structure similar to that of a professional orchestra, and performs at prestigious venues including the Royal Albert Hall and Birmingham Symphony Hall. There will be a yearly international tour. Previous tours have included Poland, Italy and Spain Access to BYWO is by annual audition only.<br>14. When: Three Times Per Year<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://www.berksmusictrust.org.uk/music/music-groups/ensembles/<br>16. Organisation Name: Berkshire Music Trust<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: https://www.berksmusictrust.org.uk<br>19. Only for London/Local?: No Restriction<br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
