        <name>Reading - Out of the Attic Orchestra</name>
        <address>Reading Music Centre, Reading - UK</address>
        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South East<br>3. County: Berkshire<br>4. Location: Reading Music Centre, Reading - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): Orchestra<br>7. Genre: Orchestral<br>8. Age: 18 +<br>9. Level: Grade 5+<br>10. Instruments: Piccolo/Flute, Clarinet, Oboe, Cor Anglais, Bassoon, Trumpet, Trombone, Tuba, Horns, Harp, Violin, Viola, Cello, Double Bass, Euphonium<br>11. Other Tags: Grade 5, Grade 6, Grade 7, Grade 8<br>12. Cost: https://www.berksmusictrust.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/Fees-2025-26-FINAL-EXT.pdf<br>13. About Opportunity: ut of the Attic is a friendly, inclusive orchestra for adults. Our name was given by our founding members, many of whom were returning to playing music after a long break and were getting their instruments back 'Out of the Attic'. This ensemble is suited to any string, brass, woodwind or percussion players of roughly grade 5 standard or above. We are always pleased to welcome new members so please do get in touch if you would like to join.<br>14. When: Thursdays 19:00 - 20:00<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://www.berksmusictrust.org.uk/music/music-groups/ensembles/<br>16. Organisation Name: Berkshire Music Trust<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: https://www.berksmusictrust.org.uk<br>19. Only for London/Local?: No Restriction<br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
