        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South East<br>3. County: Berkshire<br>4. Location: Berkshire - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): String Ensemble<br>7. Genre: Orchestral<br>8. Age: All Ages<br>9. Level: Grade 8+<br>10. Instruments: Violin, Viola, Cello, Double Bass<br>11. Other Tags: Grade 8<br>12. Cost: https://www.berksmusictrust.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/Fees-2025-26-FINAL-EXT.pdf<br>13. About Opportunity: This ensemble offers young string musicians the opportunity to experience and achieve high standard performance in a professional-like atmosphere. Also provides our most talented pupils a more prominent platform to engage in the deep study of their instruments, while also developing orchestral/ensemble skills. Whenever required, the ensemble will function as well as a fixed group for Maestros events, such as the “Junior Music Festival”, competitions and so much more!<br>14. When: Mondays 20:05 - 21:55<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://www.berksmusictrust.org.uk/music/music-groups/ensembles/<br>16. Organisation Name: Berkshire Music Trust<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: https://www.berksmusictrust.org.uk<br>19. Only for London/Local?: No Restriction<br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
