        <name>Wokingham Intermediate String Orchestra</name>
        <address>Wokingham Music Centre - UK</address>
        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South East<br>3. County: Berkshire<br>4. Location: Wokingham Music Centre - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): String Ensemble<br>7. Genre: Orchestral<br>8. Age: Young Players<br>9. Level: Grade 3-5<br>10. Instruments: Violin, Viola, Cello, Double Bass, Percussion<br>11. Other Tags: Grade 3, Grade 4, Grade 5<br>12. Cost: https://www.berksmusictrust.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/Fees-2025-26-FINAL-EXT.pdf<br>13. About Opportunity: his is a great opportunity for those more established young string players that are currently working at Grade 3 to 5 standard. During this rehearsal pupils will have a first experience of pieces that they will probably recognise from the standard orchestral repertoire. Sight-reading skills will be practised regularly and new bowing techniques will be introduced, such as those off the string articulations.<br>14. When: Wednesdays 17:45  - 19:15<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://www.berksmusictrust.org.uk/music/music-groups/ensembles/<br>16. Organisation Name: Berkshire Music Trust<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: https://www.berksmusictrust.org.uk<br>19. Only for London/Local?: No Restriction<br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
