      <Placemark>
        <name><![CDATA[Let's Play - Strings (Bracknell)]]></name>
        <address>bracknell Music Centre - UK</address>
        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South East<br>3. County: Berkshire<br>4. Location: bracknell Music Centre - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): String Ensemble<br>7. Genre: Orchestral<br>8. Age: All Ages<br>9. Level: 5 Notes - Grade 1<br>10. Instruments: Violin, Viola, Cello, Double Bass, Percussion<br>11. Other Tags: Preparatory, Grade 1<br>12. Cost: https://www.berksmusictrust.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/Fees-2025-26-FINAL-EXT.pdf<br>13. About Opportunity: This ensemble is a weekly opportunity for all beginner string players to join in and have a first experience of playing in an ensemble. Repertoire is based mostly around the four open strings and the occasional use of finger one. Pupils will also learn what playing with other musicians is like, preparing for informal performances around the year and learning the basics of their instrumental playing. Do come and join us!<br>14. When: Fridays 16:30 - 17:15<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://www.berksmusictrust.org.uk/music/music-groups/ensembles/<br>16. Organisation Name: Berkshire Music Trust<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: https://www.berksmusictrust.org.uk<br>19. Only for London/Local?: No Restriction<br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
