      <Placemark>
        <name>Berkshire Youth Bassoon Ensemble</name>
        <address>Berkshire - UK</address>
        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South East<br>3. County: Berkshire<br>4. Location: Berkshire - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): Woodwind Ensemble<br>7. Genre: Orchestral<br>8. Age: 12 - 18<br>9. Level: Grade 8+<br>10. Instruments: Bassoon<br>11. Other Tags: Grade 8, Invitation Only, Audition<br>12. Cost: https://www.berksmusictrust.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/Fees-2025-26-FINAL-EXT.pdf<br>13. About Opportunity: The Berkshire Youth Bassoon Ensemble (Acer Minor) was formed in September 2010. It got its name as Acer is the genus of maple trees, from which bassoons are made. It is a by invitation ensemble, with a minimum standard of grade 8 for entry. At the moment it is 14 strong, with an age range of 12 to 18. Acer has been lucky enough to perform in many prestigious venues and has won awards at the Music for Youth Festival in Birmingham in the past, as well as prizes at a number of local festivals.<br><br>Former members of Acer have gone on to study Music at many top conservatoires and universities both in the UK and abroad. Regardless of what former members of the Acer family go on to do in their careers, they all still play their bassoons and join the current Acer group every summer for an alumni concert in aid of Acer’s charity; The Toby Fund. The Toby Fund has raised thousands of pounds over the years, in memory of one of the founding members, with the money going to maintain instruments, purchase accessories and fund masterclasses and consultation lessons for bassoonists and contrabassoonists in Berkshire. The Toby Fund and Acer will be hosting our first national event in March 2023, inviting players and teachers from all over the UK to join us for masterclasses, talks and ensembles.<br>14. When: Mondays 18:00 - 19:00<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://www.berksmusictrust.org.uk/music/music-groups/ensembles/<br>16. Organisation Name: Berkshire Music Trust<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: https://www.berksmusictrust.org.uk<br>19. Only for London/Local?: No Restriction<br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1801-9C27B0-labelson</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="2. Region">
            <value>South East</value>
          </Data>
