        <name>West Berkshire Senior String Orchestra</name>
        <address>West Berkshire Music Centre - UK</address>
        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South East<br>3. County: Berkshire<br>4. Location: West Berkshire Music Centre - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): String Ensemble<br>7. Genre: Orchestral<br>8. Age: 12 - 18<br>9. Level: Grade 6+<br>10. Instruments: Violin, Viola, Cello, Double Bass<br>11. Other Tags: Grade 6, Grade 7, Grade 8<br>12. Cost: https://www.berksmusictrust.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/Fees-2025-26-FINAL-EXT.pdf<br>13. About Opportunity: During this activity pupils of Grade 6 to 8 meet weekly to work on well-established string repertoire, such as pieces for string orchestra, as well as solo concerts. This ensemble regularly takes part in “Music for Youth Festival” performing in famous venues around the country. Most of the pupils that attend this ensemble are also members of the Berkshire Youth Symphony Orchestra. This String ensemble includes a social break where all senior ensembles at Music Centre can meet.<br>14. When: Saturdays 10:15 - 12:15<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://www.berksmusictrust.org.uk/music/music-groups/ensembles/<br>16. Organisation Name: Berkshire Music Trust<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: https://www.berksmusictrust.org.uk<br>19. Only for London/Local?: No Restriction<br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
