        <name>Reading Saxophone Ensemble</name>
        <address>Reading Music Centre, Reading - UK</address>
        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South East<br>3. County: Berkshire<br>4. Location: Reading Music Centre, Reading - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): Woodwind Ensemble<br>7. Genre: Orchestral<br>8. Age: All Ages<br>9. Level: Grade 8+<br>10. Instruments: Saxophone<br>11. Other Tags: Grade 8<br>12. Cost: https://www.berksmusictrust.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/Fees-2025-26-FINAL-EXT.pdf<br>13. About Opportunity: Berkshire Youth Saxophone Ensemble exists to join together the county's most talented young saxophonists in order to inspire and challenge them, and to develop their ability to perform chamber music to a high level. The group aims to explore a wide range of repertoire with influence from both western classical music and the world of jazz and there are often opportunities to explore improvisation. Pupils are also given the chance to play on the auxiliary instruments such as the soprano or baritone saxophone. Alongside tuition from our saxophone specialist teachers we have previously also worked with top level professional players including Rob Buckland and Gerard McChrystal.<br>14. When: Fridays 18:00 - 18:45<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://www.berksmusictrust.org.uk/music/music-groups/ensembles/<br>16. Organisation Name: Berkshire Music Trust<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: https://www.berksmusictrust.org.uk<br>19. Only for London/Local?: No Restriction<br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
