        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South East<br>3. County: Berkshire<br>4. Location: CultureMix Arts & Music Centre - UK<br>5. Type: Workshop<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): <br>7. Genre: Jazz<br>8. Age: 12 - 18<br>9. Level: All Abilities<br>10. Instruments: Trumpet, Trombone, Piano/Keys, Guitar, Bass Guitar, Singing, Saxophone, Drum Kit<br>11. Other Tags: Free<br>12. Cost: Free<br>13. About Opportunity: Launched in 2023 in a partnership with Youthsayers the free Jazz Reggae Afrobeat course encouraged young musicians to develop their live music playing alongside professionals. <br><br>In 2024 The Jazzrobeat Collective was created by the dedicated group with support from CultureMix tutors Jamie and Ruel for live performances at Carnival of the World and Readipop Festival.<br><br>To join the 2026 Summer course you will have some experience of playing a musical instrument so you can improve by playing in a band. The focus is on Afro Jazz, Funk and Reggae genres to develop and build up your music skills.<br><br>You are required to bring your own instruments like horns or guitars. CultureMix Arts has limited instruments available including keyboards and drum kit.<br><br>Classes are during term time only and you can book anytime.<br><br>For more information contact CultureMix Arts. Office: 0118 9587351 Mobile: 07973 251919<br><br>What to expect:<br>During the course you will learn, develop and rehearse new songs with the group for a performance at the end. Watch the above video and read about the Summer short course here.<br><br>The course takes place during term time. Please take careful note of the session dates.<br>14. When: Mondays 17:30 - 19:00 <br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://culturemixarts.co.uk/education/workshops-2/jazzrobeat-collective-afro-jazz-funk-music-making-course-for-12-18s-2/<br>16. Organisation Name: CultureMix<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: <br>19. Only for London/Local?: No Restriction<br>20. Extra Notes: Limited to 16 places - signup/pre-booking required]]></description>
