        <name>Music Therapy in Cornwall</name>
        <address>Cornwall - UK</address>
        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South West<br>3. County: Cornwall<br>4. Location: Cornwall - UK<br>5. Type: Workshop<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): <br>7. Genre: Other<br>8. Age: Unknown<br>9. Level: Music therapy has proven effectiveness for those with:<br><br>Learning disabilities<br><br>Challenging behaviour<br><br>Developmental delay<br><br>Mental health problems<br><br>Physical difficulties<br><br>Bereavement issues<br><br>Eating disorders<br><br>Autistic spectrum conditions<br><br>Problems relating to abuse<br><br>Attachment issues<br><br>Family and adoption issues<br><br>Dementia and Alzheimer’s<br><br>Aphasia<br><br>Life threatening conditions<br><br>Life-limiting conditions<br>10. Instruments: All<br>11. Other Tags: SEND<br>12. Cost: https://static1.squarespace.com/static/58077e542994ca4c49e321d4/t/688238e9cab6321c68477519/1753364713557/MT%2BCharges%2Bfrom%2BSeptember%2B2024%2Bfor%2BWebsite.pdf<br>13. About Opportunity: Music Therapy is not the same as music tuition: its purpose is not to teach someone how to play an instrument but to allow them to translate their emotions and psychological processes into expressive music in order to release feelings, repair them and heal. Music can offer an alternative method of communication or expression where words are not an option or are inadequate. Some feelings are just too heavy for words to carry – but music always finds a way to express them. The aim is to bring out the client’s creativity in order to develop positive changes in behaviour, emotional and physical well-being and communication.<br><br>Music is a powerful emotional medium which can affect people profoundly And seems to give us permission to connect with our deepest emotions. These emotions can sometimes be melancholy and sad, sometimes angry, sometimes exuberant, joyous and life affirming.<br><br>Moreover, this intense emotional response to music seems to be unimpaired by illness or disability.<br>14. When: Enquire for more info<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://cmst.co.uk/musictherapy<br>16. Organisation Name: Cornwall Music Service Trust<br>17. About Organisation: By enabling students of all generations, backgrounds and communities to enjoy a LIFE including music making and participation, we seek to grow and support the HEALTH of a musical COMMUNITY for now and for the FUTURE.<br><br>Music for LIFE<br><br>We believe that music is not merely a hobby but a way of living which can positively impact everyone's emotional and physical wellbeing. At CMST, we aim to create an inclusive atmosphere of music making that all can enjoy, characterised by the care and compassion to enrich all of our students’ lives into the future.<br><br>Music for the FUTURE<br><br>We aim to inspire our students, encouraging imagination and creativity, and welcoming new developments in technology and innovation to allow ever wider access to Musical Education. We encourage environmental awareness and sustainability in order to secure the future of new and existing musical communities.<br><br>Music for the COMMUNITY<br><br>We recognise community is at the heart of music making. We respect people, value diversity, and are committed to encouraging inclusivity throughout the music community within Cornwall and beyond. We value and foster partnerships within the local community and businesses in order to create and sustain new musical opportunities for all, and to nurture happy and healthy musical communities.<br><br>Music for HEALTH<br><br>We believe that music can be a key to the better understanding of our own emotional responses, and to improving mental health - regardless of age, ability or ways of communicating. We are committed to promoting this understanding throughout Cornwall and beyond. Our ambition is to provide access to Music Therapy for all of those in need of its support, to overcome difficulties, and build resilience to brighten their futures.<br>18. Organisation Website: https://cmst.co.uk<br>19. Only for London/Local?: <br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1637-FFD600-labelson</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="2. Region">
