        <name>Cornwall Youth Jazz Orchestra (Truro)</name>
        <address>Truro, Cornwall - UK</address>
        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South West<br>3. County: Cornwall<br>4. Location: Truro, Cornwall - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): Jazz Band<br>7. Genre: Jazz<br>8. Age: 12 - 16<br>9. Level: Intermediate - Advanced<br>10. Instruments: Piccolo/Flute, Trumpet, Trombone, Double Bass, Piano/Keys, Guitar, Bass Guitar, Saxophone, Drum Kit<br>11. Other Tags: <br>12. Cost: £165 per year<br>13. About Opportunity: Cornwall Youth Jazz Orchestra: Where Young Musicians Swing Into Action<br><br>Looking for an exciting opportunity to take your music to the next level? The Cornwall Youth Jazz Orchestra (CYJO) is the perfect place for secondary school musicians to shine! Whether you’re a parent eager to see your child develop their talent or a young musician ready to step into the spotlight, CYJO offers an incredible experience filled with music, camaraderie, and unforgettable performances.<br><br>WHAT IS CYJO?<br><br>CYJO is a dynamic group of talented young jazz musicians led by the inspiring Andy Bilham, with plenty of laughs courtesy of our resident comedian, James Robinson. Together, we explore the rich world of jazz, from swing and bebop to contemporary styles. We perform at all kinds of events—village halls, charity gigs, festivals, and beyond.<br><br>WHY JOIN CYJO?<br><br>Being part of CYJO is about more than just playing great music. It’s about:<br><br>Skill-Building: Hone your technique, learn advanced jazz styles, and develop ensemble skills.<br><br>Performance Opportunities: Take the stage at diverse venues, showcasing your talent to audiences across Cornwall and beyond.<br><br>Community: Connect with like-minded young musicians and form lasting friendships in a supportive and fun environment.<br><br>Confidence: Gain experience playing in a professional-style jazz ensemble, building confidence with every performance.<br><br><br>WHO CAN JOIN?<br><br>CYJO is open to:<br><br>Secondary School Students: Young musicians from across Cornwall.<br><br>Intermediate to Advanced Musicians: If you have some experience under your belt and a love for jazz, we want to hear from you!<br><br>Wide Variety of Instrumentation: Whether you play saxophone, trumpet, trombone, piano, drums, bass, or even the flute, there’s a place for you in our ensemble.<br><br>WHAT’S THE COMMITMENT?<br><br>CYJO rehearses regularly, giving members plenty of time to develop their skills and prepare for gigs. We’re all about making great music while keeping it fun and manageable alongside your school commitments.<br><br>READY TO JOIN THE BAND?<br><br>Don’t miss this chance to be part of one of Cornwall’s most exciting youth music groups. Whether you’re looking to expand your musical horizons or take your first steps into the vibrant world of jazz, CYJO is the place to b<br>14. When: Enquire for more info<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://cmst.co.uk/cyjo<br>16. Organisation Name: Cornwall Music Service Trust<br>17. About Organisation: By enabling students of all generations, backgrounds and communities to enjoy a LIFE including music making and participation, we seek to grow and support the HEALTH of a musical COMMUNITY for now and for the FUTURE.<br><br>Music for LIFE<br><br>We believe that music is not merely a hobby but a way of living which can positively impact everyone's emotional and physical wellbeing. At CMST, we aim to create an inclusive atmosphere of music making that all can enjoy, characterised by the care and compassion to enrich all of our students’ lives into the future.<br><br>Music for the FUTURE<br><br>We aim to inspire our students, encouraging imagination and creativity, and welcoming new developments in technology and innovation to allow ever wider access to Musical Education. We encourage environmental awareness and sustainability in order to secure the future of new and existing musical communities.<br><br>Music for the COMMUNITY<br><br>We recognise community is at the heart of music making. We respect people, value diversity, and are committed to encouraging inclusivity throughout the music community within Cornwall and beyond. We value and foster partnerships within the local community and businesses in order to create and sustain new musical opportunities for all, and to nurture happy and healthy musical communities.<br><br>Music for HEALTH<br><br>We believe that music can be a key to the better understanding of our own emotional responses, and to improving mental health - regardless of age, ability or ways of communicating. We are committed to promoting this understanding throughout Cornwall and beyond. Our ambition is to provide access to Music Therapy for all of those in need of its support, to overcome difficulties, and build resilience to brighten their futures.<br>18. Organisation Website: https://cmst.co.uk<br>19. Only for London/Local?: <br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
