        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South West<br>3. County: Cornwall<br>4. Location: Truro High School, Cornwall - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): Concert Band<br>7. Genre: Orchestral<br>8. Age: <br>9. Level: Intermediate - Advanced<br>10. Instruments: <br>11. Other Tags: <br>12. Cost: £30 per term<br>13. About Opportunity: Join our dynamic ensemble, Sax is our Business, dedicated to intermediate and advanced saxophone players in Truro! Be part of a vibrant group where you'll fine-tune your skills, collaborate with like-minded musicians, and explore an exciting repertoire. From thrilling performances to diverse gigs throughout the year, this is your chance to elevate your saxophone prowess while having a blast making music together. Don't miss the chance to be part of this fantastic saxophone ensemble!<br>Musical Director - Steve Clifford<br><br>Steve studied clarinet under Colin Courtney in London and on leaving college joined the Royal Air Force as a musician. He was posted to the RAF Central Band and performed with them for 26 years. During his military career, he performed with the RAF Central Band, The RAF Squadronaires and the RAF Dance Orchestra, touring and performing throughout the world including USA, Japan, Africa and Europe.<br><br>On retiring to Cornwall, he joined CMST and acts as the cross service lead for first access. Teaching in schools and colleges from Truro through to Saltash.<br><br> Want to join the sensational Sax is our Business? Shoot us an email to find out more!<br>14. When: Mondays 19:00 - 20:15<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://cmst.co.uk/carrick-winds<br>16. Organisation Name: Cornwall Music Service Trust<br>17. About Organisation: By enabling students of all generations, backgrounds and communities to enjoy a LIFE including music making and participation, we seek to grow and support the HEALTH of a musical COMMUNITY for now and for the FUTURE.<br><br>Music for LIFE<br><br>We believe that music is not merely a hobby but a way of living which can positively impact everyone's emotional and physical wellbeing. At CMST, we aim to create an inclusive atmosphere of music making that all can enjoy, characterised by the care and compassion to enrich all of our students’ lives into the future.<br><br>Music for the FUTURE<br><br>We aim to inspire our students, encouraging imagination and creativity, and welcoming new developments in technology and innovation to allow ever wider access to Musical Education. We encourage environmental awareness and sustainability in order to secure the future of new and existing musical communities.<br><br>Music for the COMMUNITY<br><br>We recognise community is at the heart of music making. We respect people, value diversity, and are committed to encouraging inclusivity throughout the music community within Cornwall and beyond. We value and foster partnerships within the local community and businesses in order to create and sustain new musical opportunities for all, and to nurture happy and healthy musical communities.<br><br>Music for HEALTH<br><br>We believe that music can be a key to the better understanding of our own emotional responses, and to improving mental health - regardless of age, ability or ways of communicating. We are committed to promoting this understanding throughout Cornwall and beyond. Our ambition is to provide access to Music Therapy for all of those in need of its support, to overcome difficulties, and build resilience to brighten their futures.<br>18. Organisation Website: https://cmst.co.uk<br>19. Only for London/Local?: <br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
