        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South West<br>3. County: Cornwall<br>4. Location: Newlyn Primary School, Penzance - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): Mixed Ensemble<br>7. Genre: Orchestral<br>8. Age: Year 3 - 8<br>9. Level: Intermediate - Advanced<br>10. Instruments: <br>11. Other Tags: <br>12. Cost: £30 per term<br>13. About Opportunity: Play West, a vibrant children's music ensemble based in West Cornwall convenes weekly rehearsals at Newlyn Primary School in Penzance every Monday from 4 to 5 pm. The ensemble prides itself on being an inclusive space, welcoming children of all skill levels and proficient on any instrument. Our group currently comprises of enthusiastic participants ranging from year 3 to year 8, showcasing their talents on guitar, cello, violin, flute, and keyboard. The group is always welcome to new musicians.<br><br>At Play West, music is our passion, and our repertoire spans various genres. Additionally, we foster creativity by composing our pieces. Our performances have graced notable events such as the Golowan festival and the St Piran's Day parade in Penzance. We also enjoy collaborating with other ensembles for special events and performances, enhancing our musical experience. We always encourage new members to join our vibrant ensemble and be part of our musical journey!<br><br>Join us in embracing the joy of music-making and exploration!<br><br>For further information and inquiries about Play West, please get in touch with Christine Judge at cjudge@cmst.co.uk<br>14. When: Mondays 16:00 - 17:00<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://cmst.co.uk/play-west<br>16. Organisation Name: Cornwall Music Service Trust<br>17. About Organisation: By enabling students of all generations, backgrounds and communities to enjoy a LIFE including music making and participation, we seek to grow and support the HEALTH of a musical COMMUNITY for now and for the FUTURE.<br><br>Music for LIFE<br><br>We believe that music is not merely