        <address>Helston, Cornwall - UK</address>
        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South West<br>3. County: Cornwall<br>4. Location: Helston, Cornwall - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): Mixed Ensemble<br>7. Genre: Orchestral<br>8. Age: All Ages<br>9. Level: All Abilities<br>10. Instruments: All<br>11. Other Tags: <br>12. Cost: £30 per term<br>13. About Opportunity: Are you passionate about music? Do you play an instrument? Whether you're a seasoned musician or just starting your musical journey, we have an exciting opportunity for you. Welcome to our multi-instrument ensemble, where we welcome all instruments. On this page, we'll delve into the vibrant world of our ensemble, its welcoming atmosphere, diverse repertoire, and the joyous experiences it offers. Join us as we explore the magic of music!<br><br>Embracing All Instruments: A Welcoming Community<br><br>At our ensemble, we believe that music knows no boundaries. We welcome musicians of all levels and any instrument, from wind and brass to violin, the versatile keyboards, and the rhythmic beats of percussion.<br><br>Joining our ensemble is simple. All you need is the ability to make a sound on your instrument. We have a dedicated team of staff members and volunteers who are eager to support you on your musical journey. Whether you're a beginner or a seasoned player, we are here to help you grow and develop your musical talents.<br><br>Custom Music for All Abilities<br><br>One of the unique aspects of our ensemble is that our music and arrangements are tailored to our band members. We understand that each musician has abilities and limitations, and we want everyone to feel comfortable and confident while playing. Our band leaders arrange the repertoire that allows you to showcase your skills and play what you can manage.<br><br>Whether we're exploring the classical masterpieces of Mozart, delving into the captivating world of jazz, rocking to popular tunes, or immersing ourselves in the enchanting melodies of show tunes, our repertoire covers a wide range of musical genres. You'll be able to explore different styles and expand your musical horizons.<br>JOIN THE GROUP<br><br><br>The Joy of Rehearsals: Fun and Friendship<br><br>When you join our ensemble, you become part of a vibrant community united by a love for music. Every week, we gather for rehearsals filled with excitement, camaraderie, and, most importantly, fun! Our warm-up games get us energised and ready to embark on a musical adventure.<br><br>During rehearsals, we encourage improvisation, allowing you to express yourself and unleash your creativity. It's a time of exploration and personal growth as you discover new musical possibilities. The joyous experience of playing in this group setting is truly unparalleled and a stepping stone to the many other fantastic ensembles Cornwall has to offer.<br><br>Join Us at St. Michaels School in Helston<br><br>Our rehearsals take place on a Saturday morning at St. Michaels School in Helston. Located in a serene environment, the school is ideal for our musical gatherings, and we have access to school keyboards, drum kit and percussion. We meet fortnightly, allowing you to balance your passion for music with your other commitments.<br><br>The rehearsals last an hour and a half, starting at 10:30, which allows parents plenty of time to explore the local amenities. We also have a drink and biscuit break to recharge and socialise with fellow musicians. It's a time to connect, share experiences, and forge lasting friendships with people who share your love for music.<br>Varenna Watkiss - Musical Director<br><br>Verena, a proud Cornish musician, honed her flute and piano skills from a young age. She studied music at Helston Community College, joining their jazz band and taking up the saxophone. Pursuing her passion, she earned a jazz and popular music degree at Middlesex University, followed by a PGCE in Music Education. For a decade, she served as head of music at a local secondary school. Verena's talent led her to the Cornwall and National Youth Jazz orchestras. Now, she leads the thriving Cornish Roots big band while regularly performing in local bands and shows.<br><br>Not only a dedicated bandleader, but Verena also remains an active player, relishing the opportunity to perform regularly in local bands and captivating shows. Currently residing in the vibrant Helston area, she passionately imparts her expertise as she teaches <br>14. When: Enquire for more info<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://cmst.co.uk/trosanhellys<br>16. Organisation Name: Cornwall Music Service Trust<br>17. About Organisation: By enabling students of all generations, backgrounds and communities to enjoy a LIFE including music making and participation, we seek to grow and support the HEALTH of a musical COMMUNITY for now and for the FUTURE.<br><br>Music for LIFE<br><br>We believe that music is not merely a hobby but a way of living which can positively impact everyone's emotional and physical wellbeing. At CMST, we aim to create an inclusive atmosphere of music making that all can enjoy, characterised by the care and compassion to enrich all of our students’ lives into the future.<br><br>Music for the FUTURE<br><br>We aim to inspire our students, encouraging imagination and creativity, and welcoming new developments in technology and innovation to allow ever wider access to Musical Education. We encourage environmental awareness and sustainability in order to secure the future of new and existing musical communities.<br><br>Music for the COMMUNITY<br><br>We recognise community is at the heart of music making. We respect people, value diversity, and are committed to encouraging inclusivity throughout the music community within Cornwall and beyond. We value and foster partnerships within the local community and businesses in order to create and sustain new musical opportunities for all, and to nurture happy and healthy musical communities.<br><br>Music for HEALTH<br><br>We believe that music can be a key to the better understanding of our own emotional responses, and to improving mental health - regardless of age, ability or ways of communicating. We are committed to promoting this understanding throughout Cornwall and beyond. Our ambition is to provide access to Music Therapy for all of those in need of its support, to overcome difficulties, and build resilience to brighten their futures.<br>18. Organisation Website: https://cmst.co.uk<br>19. Only for London/Local?: <br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
