        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South West<br>3. County: Cornwall<br>4. Location: St Michaels School, Helston, Cornwall - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): Other Ensemble<br>7. Genre: Orchestral<br>8. Age: 6 - Adults<br>9. Level: All Abilities<br>10. Instruments: Ukelele<br>11. Other Tags: <br>12. Cost: £30 per term<br>13. About Opportunity: Do you want to learn to play the ukulele ?<br><br>Kerrier ukulele’s was set up for those that have taken First Access ukulele in school and want to continue to enjoy playing & singing together in a group. We take complete beginners from the age of 6 through to adults and enjoy playing together and performing locally.<br><br>We meet in St. Michaels School in Helston on Saturday mornings fortnightly, allowing you to balance your passion for music with your other commitments.<br><br>The rehearsals last an hour and a half, starting at 10:30, which allows parents plenty of time to explore the local amenities. We also have a drink and biscuit break to recharge and socialise with fellow musicians. It's a time to connect, share experiences, and forge lasting friendships with people who share your love for music.<br>Sara Scott - musical director <br><br>Sara grew up in Truro studying violin, clarinet & piano and was a  dedicated member of her local school choir & orchestras,  Truro Youth Orchestra, Cornwall Youth Orchestra and Three Spires Festival Singers. Studying her music degree in Cardiff, she performed in many choirs, orchestras, brass bands, church bands & even sung solos in an opera! She has been teaching music for over 25 years and has recently returned to Cornwall to continue her teaching career across many musical disciplines.<br>CONTACT SARA<br><br>Sophie Orchard <br><br>Sophie grew up in Cornwall, participating in many school, local and county ensembles including CYWO. With the help of the Radford trust, the community and the music service, she was able to study Oboe at the RWCMD where she joined local ensembles and Orchestras, including various musical theatre groups. Sophie started learning Ukulele whilst on maternity leave and with Sara's enthusiasm and vast knowledge guiding her, she works with our younger members and complete beginners. You'll see Sophie and Sara popping across to Tros an Hellys to join in the fun there too as we coordinate concerts, make friends and swap snacks! <br>CONTACT SOPHIE<br><br>If you would like more information or to join our group then please click on one of the links below.<br>14. When: Saturdays (fortnightly) 10:30 - 12:00<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://cmst.co.uk/kerrier-ukulele<br>16. Organisation Name: Cornwall Music Service Trust<br>17. About Organisation: By enabling students of all generations, backgrounds and communities to enjoy a LIFE including music making and participation, we seek to grow and support the HEALTH of a musical COMMUNITY for now and for the FUTURE.<br><br>Music for LIFE<br><br>We believe that music is not merely a hobby but a way of living which can positively impact everyone's emotional and physical wellbeing. At CMST, we aim to create an inclusive atmosphere of music making that all can enjoy, characterised by the care and compassion to enrich all of our students’ lives into the future.<br><br>Music for the FUTURE<br><br>We aim to inspire our students, encouraging imagination and creativity, and welcoming new developments in technology and innovation to allow ever wider access to Musical Education. We encourage environmental awareness and sustainability in order to secure the future of new and existing musical communities.<br><br>Music for the COMMUNITY<br><br>We recognise community is at the heart of music making. We respect people, value diversity, and are committed to encouraging inclusivity throughout the music community within Cornwall and beyond. We value and foster partnerships within the local community and businesses in order to create and sustain new musical opportunities for all, and to nurture happy and healthy musical communities.<br><br>Music for HEALTH<br><br>We believe that music can be a key to the better understanding of our own emotional responses, and to improving mental health - regardless of age, ability or ways of communicating. We are committed to promoting this understanding throughout Cornwall and beyond. Our ambition is to provide access to Music Therapy for all of those in need of its support, to overcome difficulties, and build resilience to brighten their futures.<br>18. Organisation Website: https://cmst.co.uk<br>19. Only for London/Local?: <br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
