        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South West<br>3. County: Cornwall<br>4. Location: Old Cathedral School, Truro, Cornwall - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): Choir<br>7. Genre: Choral<br>8. Age: All Ages<br>9. Level: All Abilities<br>10. Instruments: Singing<br>11. Other Tags: <br>12. Cost: £40 per term<br>13. About Opportunity: The choir meets every Thursday evening during term time from 6.30 pm till 8.00 pm in the Old Cathedral School. They perform a variety of styles of music, ranging from classical pieces such as Handel's Zadok the Priest, Mozart's Ave Verum and Haydn's The Heavens Are Telling, to modern songs like Eric Whitacre's The Seal Lullaby, John Rutter's Look At The World and Russell Pascoe's Celtic Blessing. They also perform lighter pieces such as You Raise Me, Goodnight Sweetheart, And So It Goes, and folk songs such as Londonderry Air. <br><br>The CYCC has performed at various venues, including The Mince Theatre, Truro Cathedral, Carnglaze Caverns, The Eden Project, Tate St Ives and different churches where audiences have praised their high-quality performances and their ability to captivate listeners. <br><br>In addition to their concerts, the choir participates in various educational and community activities, such as workshops, masterclasses and outreach programmes. <br><br>The choir always seeks new members and welcomes singers of all ages and abilities. They are committed to providing a safe, supportive and enjoyable environment for everyone to grow and develop their musical skills while having fun. <br><br>So, if you want to join a choir and make new friends, the Cornwall Youth Chamber Choir could be a perfect choice.<br><br>REHEARSALS<br><br>Rehearsals for the CYCC Youth Chamber Choir take place at The Old Cathedral School (OCS) from 6.30 pm to 8 pm. Parents should drop off and pick up their children from the entrance across the grass at the side of the Cathedral. Occasionally, the rehearsal venue may need to be changed; you will be notified of any changes via text.<br><br>We ask everyone to support the CYCC Facebook page and Twitter, as it is essential to keep a high profile and keep up to date with rehearsals and concerts.<br><br>If you are not at a rehearsal where times and dates are discussed, information will be emailed (and texted) to you, and you will be notified of any changes in time, date or rehearsal venue. We need everyone there for the parts to balance, so please make every effort to attend once you have committed to a concert and put the dates in your diary in advance.<br><br>We encourage friends who may be interested in singing with us to come along to an open rehearsal, and we love having friends and family at our concerts. <br><br>Please note that the dress code for concerts, unless otherwise stated, is ALL BLACK: girls should wear a mid/long-sleeved top, below-knee skirts and tights (or trousers) and shoes; men/boys should wear long-sleeved button-up shirts, long trousers and black shoes. <br>14. When: Thursdays 18:30 - 20:00<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://cmst.co.uk/cycc<br>16. Organisation Name: Cornwall Music Service Trust<br>17. About Organisation: By enabling students of all generations, backgrounds and communities to enjoy a LIFE including music making and participation, we seek to grow and support the HEALTH of a musical COMMUNITY for now and for the FUTURE.<br><br>Music for LIFE<br><br>We believe that music is not merely a hobby but a way of living which can positively impact everyone's emotional and physical wellbeing. At CMST, we aim to create an inclusive atmosphere of music making that all can enjoy, characterised by the care and compassion to enrich all of our students’ lives into the future.<br><br>Music for the FUTURE<br><br>We aim to inspire our students, encouraging imagination and creativity, and welcoming new developments in technology and innovation to allow ever wider access to Musical Education. We encourage environmental awareness and sustainability in order to secure the future of new and existing musical communities.<br><br>Music for the COMMUNITY<br><br>We recognise community is at the heart of music making. We respect people, value diversity, and are committed to encouraging inclusivity throughout the music community within Cornwall and beyond. We value and foster partnerships within the local community and businesses in order to create and sustain new musical opportunities for all, and to nurture happy and healthy musical communities.<br><br>Music for HEALTH<br><br>We believe that music can be a key to the better understanding of our own emotional responses, and to improving mental health - regardless of age, ability or ways of communicating. We are committed to promoting this understanding throughout Cornwall and beyond. Our ambition is to provide access to Music Therapy for all of those in need of its support, to overcome difficulties, and build resilience to brighten their futures.<br>18. Organisation Website: https://cmst.co.uk<br>19. Only for London/Local?: <br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
