        <name>SuperStrings (Truro)</name>
        <address>Cornwall - UK</address>
        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South West<br>3. County: Cornwall<br>4. Location: Cornwall - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): String Ensemble<br>7. Genre: Orchestral<br>8. Age: Unknown<br>9. Level: Unknown <br>10. Instruments: Violin, Viola, Cello, Double Bass<br>11. Other Tags: <br>12. Cost: Enquire for more info<br>13. About Opportunity: Prepare to be enchanted by CMST’s breathtaking musical supergroup the StringStrings Ensemble! This illustrious group harmoniously combines musicians with a range of abilities; specialising in violin, viola, cello, and double bass. This ensemble dynamically evolves with every term by amalgamating smaller ensembles from all around the county, culminating in a grand orchestral masterpiece. Their captivating concerts, frequently enhanced by percussion, woodwind, and brass accompaniment, are the highlight of each term. Under the mentorship of our dedicated teachers and with a substantial group size, they fearlessly tackle complex compositions, showcasing an unparalleled blend of talent, dedication, and sheer passion on the stage! <br><br>At SuperString performances, the stage comes alive with a dynamic fusion of strings, brass, woodwind, and percussion talent! This collaboration gives students an incredible chance to perform within a larger-than-life orchestra, exploring a repertoire and vibrant sound that could otherwise be beyond their wildest musical dreams. Get ready to be part of this electrifying musical synergy!<br>Musical Director - Karen Frost<br><br>Having taught the violin and viola for over 30 years, Karen enjoys teaching a mix of ages and abilities and believes that every child, whatever their background should be given the opportunity to learn a musical instrument and experience the joy of playing in an ensemble for its life enhancing qualities.<br><br>Along with Superstrings she also directs the St. Austell Chamber Orchestra for pupils in the St. Austell/Roseland area, giving students an opportunity to play with others and enjoy a range of musical styles from pop to baroque!<br><br>Music making is an integral part of everyday life in Cornwall and in Karen’s spare time and she is actively involved in music making for many local orchestras and choral societies, notably Three Spires Singers, Truro Choral Society, Cornish Sinfonia and many more as well as performing with a professional string quartet which plays regularly for weddings and other events.<br><br>14. When: 10:00 - 11:30 (enquire for dates)<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://cmst.co.uk/superstrings<br>16. Organisation Name: Cornwall Music Service Trust<br>17. About Organisation: By enabling students of all generations, backgrounds and communities to enjoy a LIFE including music making and participation, we seek to grow and support the HEALTH of a musical COMMUNITY for now and for the FUTURE.<br><br>Music for LIFE<br><br>We believe that music is not merely a hobby but a way of living which can positively impact everyone's emotional and physical wellbeing. At CMST, we aim to create an inclusive atmosphere of music making that all can enjoy, characterised by the care and compassion to enrich all of our students’ lives into the future.<br><br>Music for the FUTURE<br><br>We aim to inspire our students, encouraging imagination and creativity, and welcoming new developments in technology and innovation to allow ever wider access to Musical Education. We encourage environmental awareness and sustainability in order to secure the future of new and existing musical communities.<br><br>Music for the COMMUNITY<br><br>We recognise community is at the heart of music making. We respect people, value diversity, and are committed to encouraging inclusivity throughout the music community within Cornwall and beyond. We value and foster partnerships within the local community and businesses in order to create and sustain new musical opportunities for all, and to nurture happy and healthy musical communities.<br><br>Music for HEALTH<br><br>We believe that music can be a key to the better understanding of our own emotional responses, and to improving mental health - regardless of age, ability or ways of communicating. We are committed to promoting this understanding throughout Cornwall and beyond. Our ambition is to provide access to Music Therapy for all of those in need of its support, to overcome difficulties, and build resilience to brighten their futures.<br>18. Organisation Website: https://cmst.co.uk<br>19. Only for London/Local?: <br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
