        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South West<br>3. County: Cornwall<br>4. Location: Falmouth School, Falmouth - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): String Ensemble<br>7. Genre: Orchestral<br>8. Age: All ages<br>9. Level: All Abilities<br>10. Instruments: Violin, Viola, Cello, Double Bass<br>11. Other Tags: <br>12. Cost: £34 per term<br>13. About Opportunity: Carrick Strings was formed in October 2022 when the equivalent much loved ensemble - Fal River Strings - could no longer operate and was sorely missed.  Many of the Fal River Strings members managed to successfully integrate into other existing strings groups in Cornwall, but a few members were left stranded!  Hence the drive to create the Carrick Strings ensemble.<br><br>Ensemble playing is an important and motivating part of learning an instrument - to develop playing and listening techniques, working as a team with other players, opening up more opportunities and for the social aspects too. <br><br>Carrick Strings tries to choose a varied repertoire from Classical, Film, Pop, Jazz to Cornish.  We invite young players of all ages and abilities and adapt the music according to ability.<br><br>Rehearsals take place at:<br><br>Falmouth School<br><br>Thursday’s, (term time only)<br><br>4:30pm - 5:30pm<br><br>Superstrings:<br><br>Carrick Strings is also part of the much bigger SuperStrings; the SuperStrings provide a vital role in music education in the community, providing opportunities for young musicians to learn and perform alongside more experienced musicians - it is a profoundly magical and exhilarating group to be a part of.<br><br>Lucetta Radcliffe - Musical Director of Carrick Strings in Falmouth<br><br>Lucetta Radcliffe is a teacher, musician and composer. She studied music at Goldsmiths College in London with a particular focus on composition. After her studies she moved to Cornwall and worked for National Foundation for Youth Music as a community musician for CYMAZ. She also collaborated with a variety of arts practitioners as part of Luminos and worked with young people to create participant-led and devised performances. After this she enjoyed teaching piano for many years and has worked as an Associate Lecturer in Music Theatre at Amata, Falmouth University. She performs (vocals, flute and accordion)  regularly with Radio Rio, a four piece Brazilian/Latin band and is the music director and conductor of River Notes, a community choir based in Falmouth. Most recently she has written a new musical called Bal Maiden and is currently producing it with Cobb Riddle and Spall Music Theatre company. This has given her the opportunity to return to her first musical love of composition. <br><br>Fathyma Parker - Strings Teacher and Musician<br><br>Fathyma Parker is musician, violin teacher and eager orchestral player whose main occupation is looking after dogs! She is the mother of two young ambitious musicians. Music is her passion, hobby and joy. She is a member of several orchestras and has participated in a variety of ensembles including; String orchestra, chamber music and contemporary music ensembles.<br>Joining the Orchestra<br><br>We invite young string players of all ages and abilities; potential members are invited to a free taster session before being expected to commit to regular rehearsals and termly informal performances.<br><br>For enquiries or to book your free taster session, please contact:<br>14. When: Thursdays (term time) 16:30 - 17:30<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://cmst.co.uk/carrickstrings<br>16. Organisation Name: Cornwall Music Service Trust<br>17. About Organisation: By enabling students of all generations, backgrounds and communities to enjoy a LIFE including music making and participation, we seek to grow and support the HEALTH of a musical COMMUNITY for now and for the FUTURE.<br><br>Music for LIFE<br><br>We believe that music is not merely a hobby but a way of living which can positively impact everyone's emotional and physical wellbeing. At CMST, we aim to create an inclusive atmosphere of music making that all can enjoy, characterised by the care and compassion to enrich all of our students’ lives into the future.<br><br>Music for the FUTURE<br><br>We aim to inspire our students, encouraging imagination and creativity, and welcoming new developments in technology and innovation to allow ever wider access to Musical Education. We encourage environmental awareness and sustainability in order to secure the future of new and existing musical communities.<br><br>Music for the COMMUNITY<br><br>We recognise community is at the heart of music making. We respect people, value diversity, and are committed to encouraging inclusivity throughout the music community within Cornwall and beyond. We value and foster partnerships within the local community and businesses in order to create and sustain new musical opportunities for all, and to nurture happy and healthy musical communities.<br><br>Music for HEALTH<br><br>We believe that music can be a key to the better understanding of our own emotional responses, and to improving mental health - regardless of age, ability or ways of communicating. We are committed to promoting this understanding throughout Cornwall and beyond. Our ambition is to provide access to Music Therapy for all of those in need of its support, to overcome difficulties, and build resilience to brighten their futures.<br>18. Organisation Website: https://cmst.co.uk<br>19. Only for London/Local?: <br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
