          <Data name="13. About Opportunity">
            <value><![CDATA[Seaton Starz – Creative Music & Performing Arts Club for Children (Ages 5–8)
Seaton Starz is a fun, weekly after-school club where children aged 5–8 can explore music, drama, dance, and performing arts through games, activities, and creative workshops. Kids also get the chance to take part in regular mini performances, building confidence and having a blast along the way!
Inclusivity and Accessibility
We welcome all young people who want to make music, regardless of financial circumstances. Sessions are affordable, with subsidised and free places available for those who need them.
Try a Free Taster
Curious to see what Seaton Starz is all about? Children are welcome to attend a free taster session before signing up.
When & Where
Every Tuesday during term time
3:45 PM – 4:45 PM
📍 The Gateway Theatre, Fore Street, Seaton, EX12 2LE
👉 View on Google Maps 
Cost
£6.00 per session, booked termly]]></value>
