          <Data name="13. About Opportunity">
            <value>The Cooperative Big Band (Coop BB) are a quality youth ensemble that has a highly regarded regional reputation that is currently on track to develop a national reputation.

This year they have performed at the Music For Youth (MFY) Regional Cornwall Festival and have qualified to perform at the Nationals in Birmingham for MFM. In addition, they have performed at many music festivals (Armed Forces Day main stage), corporate functions and local TV and radio opportunities.

This high-class ensemble consists of; a saxophone section, brass section, rhythm section and vocalist and has a varied repertoire covering many genres in addition to swing. It is run by 3 professional music tutors and is absolutely free to join!

If you play an instrument that fits the description above and you can read music, please come along on a Tuesday night 5-6.30pm (during Term Time only) at Lipson Cooperative Academy, Bernice Terrace, Plymouth PL4 7PG.​

Where        Lipson Cooperative Academy, Bernice Terrace, Plymouth PL4 7PG
Email        Plymouth Youth Music Service at youthmusic@plymouth.gov.uk
Web        
</value>
