        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South West<br>3. County: Devon<br>4. Location: Ashburton Arts Centre - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): String Ensemble<br>7. Genre: Orchestral<br>8. Age: 10 - 18<br>9. Level: Grade 4-8<br>10. Instruments: <br>11. Other Tags: Grade 4, Grade 5, Grade 6, Grade 7, Grade 8<br>12. Cost: £15 per session<br>13. About Opportunity: Run by professional string players and tutors, Lindsay Braga and Andrew Gillett, and supported by Devon Music Education Hub, we want to give young players (aged 10-18, of grade 5+) the chance to develop the skills of more advanced ensemble playing.  The group aims to explore sight-reading, confidence, listening, performance skills and technique and we hope players will have fun making music and friends in an encouraging atmosphere.  <br>14. When: One saturday per half term (see website for more details)<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://www.theviolinden.co.uk/dartmoor-strings<br>16. Organisation Name: Dartmoor Strings<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: <br>19. Only for London/Local?: <br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
