        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South West<br>3. County: Devon<br>4. Location: King Edward VI Community College Ashburton Road, Totnes - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): Woodwind Ensemble<br>7. Genre: Orchestral<br>8. Age: Young saxophonists<br>9. Level: Grade 4+<br>10. Instruments: Saxophone<br>11. Other Tags: Grade 4, Grade 5, Grade 6, Grade 7, Grade 8<br>12. Cost: Enquire for more info<br>13. About Opportunity: The Devon Youth Saxophone Ensemble is a new county-wide group for young saxophonists around Grade 4 and above. It offers the chance to develop ensemble skills, play fun and varied repertoire, and meet like-minded musicians. Starting on 16th November, the ensemble will explore chamber music for small and medium saxophone groups across six Gathering Days throughout the year, each running from 2:00–4:30pm.<br>14. When: Various dates throughout the year (see website for more details)<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://devonyouthsax.co.uk<br>16. Organisation Name: Devon Youth Saxophone Ensemble<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: <br>19. Only for London/Local?: <br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
