        <name>(Moor to Sea) - Sounding Together</name>
        <address><![CDATA[People's Parkfield, Paignton - UK]]></address>
        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South West<br>3. County: Devon<br>4. Location: People's Parkfield, Paignton - UK<br>5. Type: Workshop<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): <br>7. Genre: Various<br>8. Age: All Ages<br>9. Level: All Abilities<br>10. Instruments: <br>11. Other Tags: No Experience, Free<br>12. Cost: Free<br>13. About Opportunity: A monthly fun, free music for wellbeing group for people living with dementia and their family, friends and carers.<br>3rd Wednesday of the month, 2.30pm – 4.30pm at People’s Parkfield, Paignton<br>Join us in growing this new musical meet-up at People’s Parkfield!<br>We’re welcoming people living with dementia and those that support them to join us in creating this group space!<br>The wonderful Torbay Community Builders support alongside Moor to Sea. Social Prescribing link workers signpost to these sessions.<br>If you like listening to music, playing or singing, this session is for you. No musical experience required.<br>This is a dementia friendly, creative space we are hoping to build together.<br>Connecting, sharing and Sounding Together!<br>Sessions are hosted in an accessible space with parking, toilets and warm drinks all in easy reach!<br>Contact us for further details and to sign up.<br>14. When: 3rd Wednesday of the month, 2.30pm – 4.30pm<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://moortoseamusic.org.uk/sounding-together/<br>16. Organisation Name: Moor to Sea Music Collective<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: <br>19. Only for London/Local?: <br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
