          <Data name="13. About Opportunity">
            <value>A monthly fun, free music for wellbeing group for people living with dementia and their family, friends and carers.
3rd Wednesday of the month, 2.30pm – 4.30pm at People’s Parkfield, Paignton
Join us in growing this new musical meet-up at People’s Parkfield!
We’re welcoming people living with dementia and those that support them to join us in creating this group space!
The wonderful Torbay Community Builders support alongside Moor to Sea. Social Prescribing link workers signpost to these sessions.
If you like listening to music, playing or singing, this session is for you. No musical experience required.
This is a dementia friendly, creative space we are hoping to build together.
Connecting, sharing and Sounding Together!
Sessions are hosted in an accessible space with parking, toilets and warm drinks all in easy reach!
Contact us for further details and to sign up.</value>
