        <name>Exeter Young Strings: Poco-a-Poco</name>
        <address>Exeter - UK</address>
        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South West<br>3. County: Devon<br>4. Location: Exeter - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): String Ensemble<br>7. Genre: Orchestral<br>8. Age: Young musicians<br>9. Level: Beginners - Grade 2<br>10. Instruments: <br>11. Other Tags: Preparatory, Grade 1, Grade 2<br>12. Cost: from £60 per term<br>13. About Opportunity: Poco-a-Poco follows on from the Mini Music Makers and meets monthly. Children will continues to develop their musicianship  as well as group playing. This group is not intended to teach the instruments so all members should have started one to one instrumental lessons in order to join.  It is for beginner to grade 2 orchestral string players.<br><br>Perhaps the greatest joy of learning an instrument, at all stages, is the ability to play together with others. We encourage even at very beginner levels that students join in one of our small ensembles.<br>14. When: Saturdays 15:15 - 16:30 (Monthly)<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://exeteryoungstrings.org<br>16. Organisation Name: Exeter Young Strings<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: <br>19. Only for London/Local?: <br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
