        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South West<br>3. County: Devon<br>4. Location: Honiton Community College Music Department, EX14 1QT - UK<br>5. Type: Instrument Lessons<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): <br>7. Genre: Various<br>8. Age: Primary & Secondary age<br>9. Level: Beginners<br>10. Instruments: Horns, Trombone, Clarinet, Saxophone, Violin, Cello<br>11. Other Tags: <br>12. Cost: from £4 a week<br>13. About Opportunity: The Honiton Music Centre launched in September 2025 hosted and coordinated by Honiton Community College in their Music Department. At the Centre, youngsters of Primary and Secondary school age in the Honiton Community are able to learn the cornet, trombone, flute, clarinet, alto saxophone, violin or cello for just £4 a week. This includes a 30 minute group lesson on a chosen instrument, a 30 minute musicianship lesson and 30 minutes playing as an Ensemble.<br><br>Where        The Honiton Music Centre is hosted by Honiton Community College Music Department, School Lane, Honiton, EX14 1QT every Wednesday between 4pm and 6:30pm.<br>Who        Youngsters of Primary and Secondary school age in the Honiton Community<br>Email        David Turner at david.turner@honiton.college<br>Web        <br>forms.office.com/e/vV7VXhQj4L<br>14. When: Wednesdays 16:00 - 18:30<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://forms.office.com/e/vV7VXhQj4L<br>16. Organisation Name: Honiton Music Centre<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: Email David Turner at david.turner@honiton.college<br>19. Only for London/Local?: <br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
