      <Placemark>
        <name>Ivybridge Music Centre - Future Musicians (Primary)</name>
        <address>Ivybridge Community College - UK</address>
        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South West<br>3. County: Devon<br>4. Location: Ivybridge Community College - UK<br>5. Type: Instrument Lessons<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): <br>7. Genre: Other<br>8. Age: Years 4 - 6<br>9. Level: Beginners<br>10. Instruments: Violin, Cello, Double Bass, Trumpet, Trombone, Clarinet, Piccolo/Flute, Percussion, Saxophone, Piano/Keys<br>11. Other Tags: <br>12. Cost: Enquire for more info<br>13. About Opportunity: FUTURE MUSICIANS - ORCHESTRAL MUSIC PROGRAMME FOR PRIMARY - WEDNESDAYS<br>This is our Twenty-eight-week programme for students in years 4, 5 and 6 to learn an orchestral instrument from scratch in a group. They will also receive keyboard and general musicianship classes, and gain an Arts Award Discover qualification. Instruments are provided free of charge to use at Music Centre, and there is the option to rent an instrument to take home for a additional fee. <br>14. When: 28 week programme (enquire for starting period) - WEDS<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://www.ticketsource.co.uk/ivybridge-music-centre<br>16. Organisation Name: Ivybridge Music Centre<br>17. About Organisation: Ivybridge Music Centre is funded by Devon Music Education Hub and provides music education to the Ivybridge Learning Community. Sessions take place after school at Ivybridge Community College and are for children at primary school and secondary school. We believe that music making should be accessible to all. That is why our fees are low, and all our sessions are discounted for those eligible for Free School Meals.<br><br>Contact Email: musiccentre@ivybridge.devon.sch.uk<br>18. Organisation Website: https://www.ticketsource.co.uk/ivybridge-music-centre<br>19. Only for London/Local?: Local Only<br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
