          <Data name="13. About Opportunity">
            <value>FUTURE MUSICIANS - ORCHESTRAL MUSIC PROGRAMME FOR PRIMARY - WEDNESDAYS
This is our Twenty-eight-week programme for students in years 4, 5 and 6 to learn an orchestral instrument from scratch in a group. They will also receive keyboard and general musicianship classes, and gain an Arts Award Discover qualification. Instruments are provided free of charge to use at Music Centre, and there is the option to rent an instrument to take home for a additional fee. </value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="14. When">
            <value>28 week programme (enquire for starting period) - WEDS</value>
          </Data>
