      <Placemark>
        <name>Ivybridge Music Centre - Jam Slam (Primary)</name>
        <address>Ivybridge Community College - UK</address>
        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South West<br>3. County: Devon<br>4. Location: Ivybridge Community College - UK<br>5. Type: Workshop<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): <br>7. Genre: Rock<br>8. Age: Years 5 - 6<br>9. Level: All abilities<br>10. Instruments: Piano/Keys, Singing, Guitar, Bass Guitar, Drum Kit<br>11. Other Tags: <br>12. Cost: From £4 a session<br>13. About Opportunity: A programme for young people to come and learn how to play rock and pop collaboratively! From drum kit, to bass and guitar, vocals or keyboards – this session is run by professional musicians who will help your child to learn instrumental/vocal skills in a fun band project. JAM SLAM takes place on Monday afternoons and has sessions for students in years 5 and 6 at primary and years 7 to 13 at secondary. Sessions cost just over £4.00 per session, plus a small booking fee. You can pay for the whole year in advance, or in two instalments, and students eligible for free school pay only £20.00 for the whole year. Instruments will be provided for use at the sessions. <br>KEYBOARD/VOCALS, GUITAR, BASS GUITAR, DRUMS<br>14. When: Monday Afternoons<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://www.ticketsource.co.uk/ivybridge-music-centre<br>16. Organisation Name: Ivybridge Music Centre<br>17. About Organisation: Ivybridge Music Centre is funded by Devon Music Education Hub and provides music education to the Ivybridge Learning Community. Sessions take place after school at Ivybridge Community College and are for children at primary school and secondary school. We believe that music making should be accessible to all. That is why our fees are low, and all our sessions are discounted for those eligible for Free School Meals.<br><br>Contact Email: musiccentre@ivybridge.devon.sch.uk<br>18. Organisation Website: https://www.ticketsource.co.uk/ivybridge-music-centre<br>19. Only for London/Local?: Local Only<br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
