      <Placemark>
        <name>Ivybridge Community Big Band</name>
        <address>Ivybridge Community College - UK</address>
        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South West<br>3. County: Devon<br>4. Location: Ivybridge Community College - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): Jazz Band<br>7. Genre: Jazz<br>8. Age: Adults & Students<br>9. Level: Grade 4+<br>10. Instruments: Clarinet, Piccolo/Flute, Trumpet, Trombone, Tuba, Bass Guitar, Guitar, Drum Kit, Piano/Keys<br>11. Other Tags: Grade 4, Grade 5, Grade 6, Grade 7, Grade 8, Free<br>12. Cost: Free<br>13. About Opportunity: IVYBRIDGE COMMUNITY BIG BAND - ALTERNATE MONDAYS 7.00PM TO 8.30PM<br>The Community Big Band is for those who play and read music to grade 4 standard or above. Adults and students are welcome to attend. Big Band instruments are Saxophone, Trumpet, Trombone, Piano, Guitar, Bass and Drums, but we also welcome Clarinet, Flute and any brass instrument. Taking part in the Community Big Band is completely free of charge. Contact: musiccentre@ivybridge.co.uk<br>14. When: Alternate Mondays 19:00 - 20:30<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://www.ticketsource.co.uk/ivybridge-music-centre<br>16. Organisation Name: Ivybridge Music Centre<br>17. About Organisation: Ivybridge Music Centre is funded by Devon Music Education Hub and provides music education to the Ivybridge Learning Community. Sessions take place after school at Ivybridge Community College and are for children at primary school and secondary school. We believe that music making should be accessible to all. That is why our fees are low, and all our sessions are discounted for those eligible for Free School Meals.<br><br>Contact Email: musiccentre@ivybridge.devon.sch.uk<br>18. Organisation Website: https://www.ticketsource.co.uk/ivybridge-music-centre<br>19. Only for London/Local?: Local Only<br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
