          <Data name="12. Cost">
            <value>Free</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="13. About Opportunity">
            <value>IVYBRIDGE COMMUNITY BIG BAND - ALTERNATE MONDAYS 7.00PM TO 8.30PM
The Community Big Band is for those who play and read music to grade 4 standard or above. Adults and students are welcome to attend. Big Band instruments are Saxophone, Trumpet, Trombone, Piano, Guitar, Bass and Drums, but we also welcome Clarinet, Flute and any brass instrument. Taking part in the Community Big Band is completely free of charge. Contact: musiccentre@ivybridge.co.uk</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="14. When">
            <value>Alternate Mondays 19:00 - 20:30</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="15. Opportunity Website / Signup">
            <value>https://www.ticketsource.co.uk/ivybridge-music-centre</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="16. Organisation Name">
            <value>Ivybridge Music Centre</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="17. About Organisation">
            <value>Ivybridge Music Centre is funded by Devon Music Education Hub and provides music education to the Ivybridge Learning Community. Sessions take place after school at Ivybridge Community College and are for children at primary school and secondary school. We believe that music making should be accessible to all. That is why our fees are low, and all our sessions are discounted for those eligible for Free School Meals.

Contact Email: musiccentre@ivybridge.devon.sch.uk</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="18. Organisation Website">
            <value>https://www.ticketsource.co.uk/ivybridge-music-centre</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="19. Only for London/Local?">
            <value>Local Only</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="20. Extra Notes">
            <value/>
          </Data>
        </ExtendedData>
