      <Placemark>
        <name>Junior Concert Band</name>
        <address>Devonport High School for Boys, Devonport - UK</address>
        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South West<br>3. County: Devon<br>4. Location: Devonport High School for Boys, Devonport - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): Concert Band<br>7. Genre: Orchestral<br>8. Age: 8 - 13 (anticipated range, but not age restricted)<br>9. Level: Beginner - Intermediate<br>10. Instruments: <br>11. Other Tags: <br>12. Cost: Enquire for more info<br>13. About Opportunity: One of our longest running groups, The Plymouth Junior Concert Band has been established to offer young woodwind and brass musicians the opportunity to meet, and make music with other young players from across the city. It is aimed at children who have completed their whole class lessons in primary school and are either continuing to play at school or privately. However, any pupils who haven’t had the opportunity to continue through school but would like to join would also be very welcome.<br><br>The anticipated age range is 8-13 years 8-13 years but the group is certainly not age-restricted.<br><br>The band will rehearse every Wednesday in school term time from 4.00 – 5.00pm at Devonport High School for Boys.<br><br>Where        Devonport High School for Boys<br>Who        From age 8 to 13 but the group is not age-restricted<br>Email        Plymouth Youth Music Service at youthmusic@plymouth.gov.uk<br>14. When: Wednesdays 16:00 - 17:00 <br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://www.plymouthyouthmusic.com/ensembles<br>16. Organisation Name: Plymouth Youth Music Service<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: <br>19. Only for London/Local?: <br>20. Extra Notes: Email        Plymouth Youth Music Service at youthmusic@plymouth.gov.uk]]></description>
