        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South West<br>3. County: Devon<br>4. Location: Marjon University, Plymouth - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): Orchestra<br>7. Genre: Orchestral<br>8. Age: 11 - 21<br>9. Level: Grade 4+<br>10. Instruments: Violin, Viola, Cello, Double Bass, Oboe, Bassoon, Horns, Tuba, Clarinet, Percussion, Trombone, Trumpet, Piccolo/Flute<br>11. Other Tags: Free<br>12. Cost: Free<br>13. About Opportunity: Plymouth Youth Symphony Orchestra started in October 2022 for musicians aged between 11 and 21.  We are offering young musicians of intermediate and advanced ability (of grade 4 and above or equivalent), the opportunity to play exciting, challenging and varied orchestral works from symphonies to overtures and musicals to film music. <br>​<br>Strings: Violin, Viola, Cello & Double Bass<br>Woodwind: Oboe, Flute, Clarinet, Bassoon<br>Brass: Trumpet, French Horn, Trombone, Tuba<br>Percussion: Drum Kit, Timpani, Tuned<br>​<br>As with all our ensembles it is free to join and to participate<br>Weekly rehearsals each Wednesday 5:30pm - 7:00pm at Marjon University<br><br>For more information contact pysorchestra@gmail.com or use the “Contact Us” form on this website.<br>14. When: Wednesdays 17:30 - 19:00 <br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://www.plymouthyouthmusic.com/ensembles<br>16. Organisation Name: Plymouth Youth Music Service<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: <br>19. Only for London/Local?: <br>20. Extra Notes: Email        Plymouth Youth Music Service at youthmusic@plymouth.gov.uk]]></description>
