      <Placemark>
        <name>Legacy A Capella</name>
        <address>Montpelier Primary School, Plymouth - UK</address>
        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South West<br>3. County: Devon<br>4. Location: Montpelier Primary School, Plymouth - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): Choir<br>7. Genre: Choral<br>8. Age: Year 7 onwards<br>9. Level: Audition/Invitation from Legacy Choir members<br>10. Instruments: Singing<br>11. Other Tags: Free, Audition, Invitation Only<br>12. Cost: Free<br>13. About Opportunity: <br>The Legacy Choir<br>The Legacy Choir is a  fun and friendly, high performing  choir for young people from Year 7 upwards.   No audition required, just a love of singing!<br> <br>The choir gets involved with  fun performances at events in the local community and  exciting projects including exchanges to the USA and we sing a whole range of repertoire – something for everyone! We are the lead choir for the Plymouth International Chorus.<br> <br>The choir meets Monday 4.15 p.m. – 5.30 p.m. at Montpelier Primary School.<br>Legacy A Capella (LEGS)<br> Membership of LEGS is  drawn from members of  the Legacy Choir by invitation/audition. They sing completely unaccompanied  in a wide range of styles including contemporary a cappella including beatboxing.  They have developed a fresh, exciting, energised sound and the group offers a completely different vocal experience for singers, where singers also take on leadership roles.<br>​<br>Highlights have included a Royal Albert Hall Performance and placing 2nd in the ICCA UK quarter final in Feb 24 leading to qualifying for the UK semi final in London in April 2024.<br>​<br>Meets Fridays from 4pm to 5.30pm at Montpelier Primary School.<br>14. When: Fridays 16:00 - 17:30<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://www.plymouthyouthmusic.com/ensembles<br>16. Organisation Name: Plymouth Youth Music Service<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: <br>19. Only for London/Local?: <br>20. Extra Notes: Email        Plymouth Youth Music Service at youthmusic@plymouth.gov.uk]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1801-9C27B0-labelson</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="2. Region">
            <value>South West</value>
