          <Data name="5. Type">
            <value>Ensemble</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="6. Ensemble (if app.)">
            <value>Choir</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="7. Genre">
            <value>Choral</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="8. Age">
            <value>Year 7 onwards</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="9. Level">
            <value>Audition/Invitation from Legacy Choir members</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="10. Instruments">
            <value>Singing</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="11. Other Tags">
            <value>Free, Audition, Invitation Only</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="12. Cost">
            <value>Free</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="13. About Opportunity">
            <value>
The Legacy Choir
The Legacy Choir is a  fun and friendly, high performing  choir for young people from Year 7 upwards.   No audition required, just a love of singing!
 
The choir gets involved with  fun performances at events in the local community and  exciting projects including exchanges to the USA and we sing a whole range of repertoire – something for everyone! We are the lead choir for the Plymouth International Chorus.
 
The choir meets Monday 4.15 p.m. – 5.30 p.m. at Montpelier Primary School.
Legacy A Capella (LEGS)
 Membership of LEGS is  drawn from members of  the Legacy Choir by invitation/audition. They sing completely unaccompanied  in a wide range of styles including contemporary a cappella including beatboxing.  They have developed a fresh, exciting, energised sound and the group offers a completely different vocal experience for singers, where singers also take on leadership roles.
​
Highlights have included a Royal Albert Hall Performance and placing 2nd in the ICCA UK quarter final in Feb 24 leading to qualifying for the UK semi final in London in April 2024.
​
Meets Fridays from 4pm to 5.30pm at Montpelier Primary School.</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="14. When">
            <value>Fridays 16:00 - 17:30</value>
          </Data>
