          <Data name="13. About Opportunity">
            <value>
Plymouth City Brass
Plymouth City Brass run both a highly successful academy band and training band, encouraging members of all ages and abilities to learn to play a brass instrument in a friendly, fun and challenging environment. These are supported by PYMS.

​Plymouth City Academy Band - MD Paul Norley
The Academy band was formed in 2019 to bridge the gap from the training and senior bands. The Academy band perform across the South West taking part in concerts and contests.
​
Plymouth City Training Band - MD Gary Thompson
The Training Band was formed in 2003 and is open to anyone and everyone to come along and learn a brass instrument. Free tuition and free instrument rental allow for anyone to come along and learn in a safe, fun and creative environment.
​
Training Band: Thursday Evenings - 6.00pm - 7.15pm
Academy Band: Thursday Evenings - 6:15 - 7:30pm
at The Soundhouse, Tor Bridge High Community College, Estover.</value>
