          <Data name="13. About Opportunity">
            <value>RootNotes Family Music sessions are aimed at children aged 5-11 with parents/carers. These sessions explore different music activities:  warm-ups, singing, playing instruments, movement.
Instruments are provided but you are welcome to bring your own acoustic one too.
No musical experience is necessary to take part, just enthusiasm! Younger and older siblings are welcome too.
​
RootNotes Family Music runs on Tuesdays after school at Alwington Village Hall, Fairy Cross, near Bideford. The session runs from 4-5pm.
Cost: £30 per family per half term (5 sessions)</value>
