        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South West<br>3. County: Devon<br>4. Location: Alwington Village Hall, Fairy Cross - UK<br>5. Type: Workshop<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): <br>7. Genre: Folk<br>8. Age: 9+<br>9. Level: All abilities<br>10. Instruments: All<br>11. Other Tags: <br>12. Cost: £30 per half term<br>13. About Opportunity: RootNotes Young Folk is a music group for children and young people aged 9+ who want to develop their music skills and play in a band. You will need your own acoustic instrument to join the group but there are opportunities to try out different ones too. You will learn folk tunes from across Europe and North America and have a go at composing your own new ones. You will develop skills as a performer and in playing and singing as part of a group.<br>​<br>RootNotes Young Folk meets on Tuesdays after school at Alwington Village Hall, Fairy Cross, near Bideford. The session runs from 5.15-6.15pm.<br>Cost: £30 per person for a half term (5 sessions). Sibling discount available - please contact Becki for details.<br>14. When: Tuesdays 17:15 - 18:00<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://www.rootnotes.org.uk/young-folk<br>16. Organisation Name: RootNotes<br>17. About Organisation: <br>Welcome to the RootNotes website!<br>​<br>RootNotes is a Bideford-based community music organisation, run by local musician Becki Driscoll.<br>​<br>RootNotes offers music workshops for all ages and all abilities in a variety of different settings. Whether you are a confident player or just starting out on your musical journey RootNotes offers opportunities to join in and and take part.<br>​<br>Our weekly music groups encourage people to have fun whilst learning music and song, with an emphasis on 'hands-on' learning. We can provide instruments for sessions, or help you to develop skills on your own instrument within the group.<br>Becki Driscoll Community Musician<br>Young performers with RootNotes<br>RootNotes music workshops are suitable for schools, preschools, SEN settings, care homes and community events. Workshops can be tailored to suit a theme or a specific group of people.<br>​<br>If you are interested in coming along to one of the music groups or would like to book a RootNotes music workshop for your setting please get in touch!<br>​​<br>18. Organisation Website: https://www.rootnotes.org.uk<br>19. Only for London/Local?: <br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
