        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South West<br>3. County: Devon<br>4. Location: Ariel Centre, Totnes - UK<br>5. Type: Instrument Lessons<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): <br>7. Genre: Classical<br>8. Age: 8 - 18<br>9. Level: Intermediate<br>10. Instruments: Guitar<br>11. Other Tags: <br>12. Cost: from £75 per term<br>13. About Opportunity: A course for guitar students who already have a command of the foundations. Those who can play the open position chords (Em, Am, C, G, D, A, E, and F) and change between them with relative ease. Each term we will take various songs and instrumental pieces, breaking them down to focus on technique and theory.<br>14. When: Saturdays 10:30 - 11:20<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://sammtotnes.org/%7Esammtotnes/ensembles<br>16. Organisation Name: Saturday Morning Music - Totnes<br>17. About Organisation: SaMM is a Saturday Morning Music School based in Totnes, Devon, UK. We meet every Saturday during term time in the Ariel Centre at KEVICC,<br>We aim to help children experience music making and improve musicianship<br>whilst also learning that music is a fun and rewarding social activity<br>We are an inclusive organisation and offer children of all ages and musical abilities – from 6 to 18 and from complete beginner to virtuoso – the opportunity to enjoy making music with others in a wide variety of ensemble workshops.<br>18. Organisation Website: https://sammtotnes.org/%7esammtotnes/<br>19. Only for London/Local?: <br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
