        <address>Ariel Centre, Totnes - UK</address>
        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South West<br>3. County: Devon<br>4. Location: Ariel Centre, Totnes - UK<br>5. Type: Instrument Lessons<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): <br>7. Genre: Rock<br>8. Age: 8 - 18<br>9. Level: Intermediate<br>10. Instruments: Guitar<br>11. Other Tags: <br>12. Cost: from £75 per term<br>13. About Opportunity: An exciting guitar course for students who have a basic abillity on the electric guitar and can play a few chords and basic single note riff phrases.<br> <br>We will follow in the footsteps of the greats & learn to play guitar like Slash, Jimi Hendrix & Kurt Cobain while cultivating your own unique preferential style!<br> <br>We will bridge the gap between practical & theory whilst focusing on the joy of playing collectively in a group & and rocking out to each individual's strengths.<br>14. When: Saturdays 11:30 - 12:20<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://sammtotnes.org/%7Esammtotnes/ensembles<br>16. Organisation Name: Saturday Morning Music - Totnes<br>17. About Organisation: SaMM is a Saturday Morning Music School based in Totnes, Devon, UK. We meet every Saturday during term time in the Ariel Centre at KEVICC,<br>We aim to help children experience music making and improve musicianship<br>whilst also learning that music is a fun and rewarding social activity<br>We are an inclusive organisation and offer children of all ages and musical abilities – from 6 to 18 and from complete beginner to virtuoso – the opportunity to enjoy making music with others in a wide variety of ensemble workshops.<br>18. Organisation Website: https://sammtotnes.org/%7esammtotnes/<br>19. Only for London/Local?: <br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
