        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South West<br>3. County: Devon<br>4. Location: Ariel Centre, Totnes - UK<br>5. Type: Classes<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): <br>7. Genre: Various<br>8. Age: 6 - 8<br>9. Level: Beginner<br>10. Instruments: <br>11. Other Tags: <br>12. Cost: from £75 per term<br>13. About Opportunity: This course is aimed at 6 - 8 year olds and aims to lay a foundation in music from which students can start learning an instrument and taking part once they are 8 years old in the main groups at SaMM.<br>The course includes learning recorder, Ukulele, drumming, the basics of reading music and of course lots of singing and creative music making. It covers what was the national curriculum in music education and much more. <br>14. When: Saturdays 11:30 - 12:20<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://sammtotnes.org/%7Esammtotnes/ensembles<br>16. Organisation Name: Saturday Morning Music - Totnes<br>17. About Organisation: SaMM is a Saturday Morning Music School based in Totnes, Devon, UK. We meet every Saturday during term time in the Ariel Centre at KEVICC,<br>We aim to help children experience music making and improve musicianship<br>whilst also learning that music is a fun and rewarding social activity<br>We are an inclusive organisation and offer children of all ages and musical abilities – from 6 to 18 and from complete beginner to virtuoso – the opportunity to enjoy making music with others in a wide variety of ensemble workshops.<br>18. Organisation Website: https://sammtotnes.org/%7esammtotnes/<br>19. Only for London/Local?: <br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
