        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South West<br>3. County: Devon<br>4. Location: Ariel Centre, Totnes - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): String Ensemble<br>7. Genre: Orchestral<br>8. Age: 8 - 18<br>9. Level: Beginner - Intermediate<br>10. Instruments: Violin, Viola, Cello, Double Bass, Percussion<br>11. Other Tags: <br>12. Cost: from £75 per term<br>13. About Opportunity: String Orchestra is for orchestral string instruments which are violin, viola, cello and double bass.<br>We play music from a range of genres including baroque, classical, romantic, twentieth century and musicals. You need to be able to read music and have lessons on your instrument to join.<br>Feel free to talk to Tom Deam about this ensemble if you have any questions.<br>14. When: Saturdays 11:30 - 12:20<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://sammtotnes.org/%7Esammtotnes/ensembles<br>16. Organisation Name: Saturday Morning Music - Totnes<br>17. About Organisation: SaMM is a Saturday Morning Music School based in Totnes, Devon, UK. We meet every Saturday during term time in the Ariel Centre at KEVICC,<br>We aim to help children experience music making and improve musicianship<br>whilst also learning that music is a fun and rewarding social activity<br>We are an inclusive organisation and offer children of all ages and musical abilities – from 6 to 18 and from complete beginner to virtuoso – the opportunity to enjoy making music with others in a wide variety of ensemble workshops.<br>18. Organisation Website: https://sammtotnes.org/%7esammtotnes/<br>19. Only for London/Local?: <br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
