      <Placemark>
        <name>Sidmouth Town Band Academy</name>
        <address>St Francis Hall, Sidmouth - UK</address>
        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South West<br>3. County: Devon<br>4. Location: St Francis Hall, Sidmouth - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): Brass Ensemble<br>7. Genre: Orchestral<br>8. Age: Young Brass Players<br>9. Level: Beginners<br>10. Instruments: <br>11. Other Tags: <br>12. Cost: Enquire for more info<br>13. About Opportunity: Launching in Autumn 2022, a group of players from the band offered their time and assistance to any efforts toward growing more brass playing in the local area, and integrate those players into the Training Band, and then Senior Band when ready. The Academy was formed, which quickly split into an Academy Band, and tuition sessions for our ‘new starters’.<br><br>We have met lots of local young people since, seeking to start a brass instrument or join their first band. We have often been able to loan a brass instrument to learn with, and music provided as well. We are lucky to have Adrian Harvey and Matt Sherwood to run the ‘new starter’ tuition sessions. The band and new starters are challenged weekly, including learning about how to conduct themselves ready for performances and how ensemble rehearsals work, while learning new pieces and improving them week on week.<br><br>We love to see the enjoyment from the players and their families in rehearsal, performing and when having a joke together, because don’t forget, playing in an ensemble is fun!<br><br>The success of our young members and the running of the Academy is with thanks to the Friends of the Band and all of STB's supporters, which we value and appreciate.<br><br>As many of the members are loaning our instruments, we also offer support with taking care of them. Josie Sherwood, running the Academy Band, enjoys holding Brass maintenance sessions to teach them how to take care of and clean their instruments.<br><br>We have a strong and growing membership in the academy band, particularly from our new starter players graduating into the Academy Band. To help with this transition, we have supported some of our players with our STB Tuition Grant. This contributes to the tuition costs so they can continue their learning while attending the Academy Band. We recognise that finding tuition locally is a challenge, and for some a financial barrier that we want to help reduce, with the goal of creating more brass musicians in the area.<br><br>We have no doubt that soon enough some of our Academy players will be graduating into the Training Band.<br><br>We like to hold an Open evening in September to tell you all about how the Academy works, but we would love to hear from any young people in the area looking to take up a brass instrument or join a band at any time. We meet at St Francis Hall from 7-7:45pm every Friday.<br><br>Why not ask us about joining or find out more about the STB Grant by emailing us at info@sidmouthtownband.co.uk<br>14. When: Fridays 19:00 - 19:45<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://sidmouthtownband.co.uk/stb-academy/<br>16. Organisation Name: Sidmouth Town Band<br>17. About Organisation: There has been a band in Sidmouth for over 150 years, with the earliest record being a picture of the band taken in 1862.<br><br>By the turn of the century, the Band had become part of the local Army Volunteers, and had mixed brass and woodwind instruments. By 1908, the band was changing back to all brass instruments and in 1911 the transformation was complete.<br><br>The band was forced to put their kit away in 1914, but reformed in 1919, winning prizes in 1929, 1930 and 1931 at Crystal Palace. History repeated itself in 1939, when the instruments were laid aside once again and many of the band went off to war. In 1947, the band was reformed, becoming affiliated to the SWBBA.<br>18. Organisation Website: https://sidmouthtownband.co.uk<br>19. Only for London/Local?: <br>20. Extra Notes: Josie Sherwood at  info@sidmouthtownband.co.uk]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1801-9C27B0-labelson</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="2. Region">
            <value>South West</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="3. County">
            <value>Devon</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="4. Location">
            <value>St Francis Hall, Sidmouth - UK</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="5. Type">
            <value>Ensemble</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="6. Ensemble (if app.)">
            <value>Brass Ensemble</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="7. Genre">
            <value>Orchestral</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="8. Age">
            <value>Young Brass Players</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="9. Level">
            <value>Beginners</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="10. Instruments">
            <value/>
          </Data>
          <Data name="11. Other Tags">
            <value/>
          </Data>
          <Data name="12. Cost">
            <value>Enquire for more info</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="13. About Opportunity">
            <value><![CDATA[Launching in Autumn 2022, a group of players from the band offered their time and assistance to any efforts toward growing more brass playing in the local area, and integrate those players into the Training Band, and then Senior Band when ready. The Academy was formed, which quickly split into an Academy Band, and tuition sessions for our ‘new starters’.

We have met lots of local young people since, seeking to start a brass instrument or join their first band. We have often been able to loan a brass instrument to learn with, and music provided as well. We are lucky to have Adrian Harvey and Matt Sherwood to run the ‘new starter’ tuition sessions. The band and new starters are challenged weekly, including learning about how to conduct themselves ready for performances and how ensemble rehearsals work, while learning new pieces and improving them week on week.

We love to see the enjoyment from the players and their families in rehearsal, performing and when having a joke together, because don’t forget, playing in an ensemble is fun!

The success of our young members and the running of the Academy is with thanks to the Friends of the Band and all of STB's supporters, which we value and appreciate.

As many of the members are loaning our instruments, we also offer support with taking care of them. Josie Sherwood, running the Academy Band, enjoys holding Brass maintenance sessions to teach them how to take care of and clean their instruments.

We have a strong and growing membership in the academy band, particularly from our new starter players graduating into the Academy Band. To help with this transition, we have supported some of our players with our STB Tuition Grant. This contributes to the tuition costs so they can continue their learning while attending the Academy Band. We recognise that finding tuition locally is a challenge, and for some a financial barrier that we want to help reduce, with the goal of creating more brass musicians in the area.

We have no doubt that soon enough some of our Academy players will be graduating into the Training Band.

We like to hold an Open evening in September to tell you all about how the Academy works, but we would love to hear from any young people in the area looking to take up a brass instrument or join a band at any time. We meet at St Francis Hall from 7-7:45pm every Friday.

Why not ask us about joining or find out more about the STB Grant by emailing us at info@sidmouthtownband.co.uk]]></value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="14. When">
            <value>Fridays 19:00 - 19:45</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="15. Opportunity Website / Signup">
            <value>https://sidmouthtownband.co.uk/stb-academy/</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="16. Organisation Name">
            <value>Sidmouth Town Band</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="17. About Organisation">
            <value>There has been a band in Sidmouth for over 150 years, with the earliest record being a picture of the band taken in 1862.

By the turn of the century, the Band had become part of the local Army Volunteers, and had mixed brass and woodwind instruments. By 1908, the band was changing back to all brass instruments and in 1911 the transformation was complete.

The band was forced to put their kit away in 1914, but reformed in 1919, winning prizes in 1929, 1930 and 1931 at Crystal Palace. History repeated itself in 1939, when the instruments were laid aside once again and many of the band went off to war. In 1947, the band was reformed, becoming affiliated to the SWBBA.</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="18. Organisation Website">
            <value>https://sidmouthtownband.co.uk</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="19. Only for London/Local?">
            <value/>
          </Data>
          <Data name="20. Extra Notes">
            <value>Josie Sherwood at  info@sidmouthtownband.co.uk</value>
          </Data>
        </ExtendedData>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>East Devon Daytime Band</name>
        <address>Sidmouth Rugby Football Club Pavilion - UK</address>
        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South West<br>3. County: Devon<br>4. Location: Sidmouth Rugby Football Club Pavilion - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): Brass Ensemble<br>7. Genre: Orchestral<br>8. Age: All brass/perc players (available during the day)<br>9. Level: All abilities<br>10. Instruments: <br>11. Other Tags: Grade 1, Grade 2, Grade 3, Grade 4, Grade 5, Grade 6, Grade 7, Grade 8, Preparatory<br>12. Cost: £10 per month<br>13. About Opportunity: Since its inception the Band has successfully held regular Christmas Carolling and Easter performance events which has enabled us to donate to our nominated charities a total sum amounting to some £1,800+ shared between Devon Air Ambulance, Devon Freewheelers, Alzheimer’s Society Devon & Cornwall Branch, Sid Vale Talking Newspaper Association, St Petrocs, Exeter & the Ukrainian Red Cross.<br><br>We have successfully held performances for Cats Protection, Ottery St Mary; Dalwood Coffee and Christmas Concerts;  Kings Manor, Ottery St Mary; Green Tree Court, Pinhoe: Sundial Care Home, Tipton St. John; Exmouth Stroke Club; Seaton Care Home; Vale View Care Home, Sidford; Churchill Homes Lockyer Lodge, Newton Poppleford Primary School and Ikea Exeter store all from whom we have received warm and appreciative feedback.  <br><br>We warmly welcome new and lapsed brass and percussion players so if you are interested in joining us, and would like any further information about the Band or for booking enquiries please complete the ‘contact us’ form on this site.<br><br>Band rehearsals are held on Wednesdays ​from 10.15 a.m. to 12.15 pm ​in our band room at Sidmouth Rugby Football Club Pavilion, Byes Lane, Sidford, EX10 9PY. There is a player contribution of £10 per month.<br>14. When: Wednesdays 10:00 - 12:15<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://eastdevondaytimeband.weebly.com<br>16. Organisation Name: East Devon Daytime Band<br>17. About Organisation: Since its inception the Band has successfully held regular Christmas Carolling and Easter performance events which has enabled us to donate to our nominated charities a total sum amounting to some £1,800+ shared between Devon Air Ambulance, Devon Freewheelers, Alzheimer’s Society Devon & Cornwall Branch, Sid Vale Talking Newspaper Association, St Petrocs, Exeter & the Ukrainian Red Cross.<br><br>We have successfully held performances for Cats Protection, Ottery St Mary; Dalwood Coffee and Christmas Concerts;  Kings Manor, Ottery St Mary; Green Tree Court, Pinhoe: Sundial Care Home, Tipton St. John; Exmouth Stroke Club; Seaton Care Home; Vale View Care Home, Sidford; Churchill Homes Lockyer Lodge, Newton Poppleford Primary School and Ikea Exeter store all from whom we have received warm and appreciative feedback.  <br><br>We warmly welcome new and lapsed brass and percussion players so if you are interested in joining us, and would like any further information about the Band or for booking enquiries please complete the ‘contact us’ form on this site.<br><br>Band rehearsals are held on Wednesdays ​from 10.15 a.m. to 12.15 pm ​in our band room at Sidmouth Rugby Football Club Pavilion, Byes Lane, Sidford, EX10 9PY. There is a player contribution of £10 per month.<br>18. Organisation Website: https://eastdevondaytimeband.weebly.com<br>19. Only for London/Local?: <br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
