        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South West<br>3. County: Devon<br>4. Location: St Francis Hall, Sidmouth - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): Brass Ensemble<br>7. Genre: Orchestral<br>8. Age: Young Brass Players<br>9. Level: All abilities<br>10. Instruments: <br>11. Other Tags: <br>12. Cost: Enquire for more info<br>13. About Opportunity: Enquire for more info<br>14. When: Enquire for more info<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://sidmouthtownband.co.uk/stb-academy/<br>16. Organisation Name: Sidmouth Town Band<br>17. About Organisation: There has been a band in Sidmouth for over 150 years, with the earliest record being a picture of the band taken in 1862.<br><br>By the turn of the century, the Band had become part of the local Army Volunteers, and had mixed brass and woodwind instruments. By 1908, the band was changing back to all brass instruments and in 1911 the transformation was complete.<br><br>The band was forced to put their kit away in 1914, but reformed in 1919, winning prizes in 1929, 1930 and 1931 at Crystal Palace. History repeated itself in 1939, when the instruments were laid aside once again and many of the band went off to war. In 1947, the band was reformed, becoming affiliated to the SWBBA.<br>18. Organisation Website: https://sidmouthtownband.co.uk<br>19. Only for London/Local?: <br>20. Extra Notes: Josie Sherwood at  info@sidmouthtownband.co.uk]]></description>
