            <value><![CDATA[If you are a Bristol City Council Resident, join Evolve Music’s Barton Hill Dads Rock group for dads or male caregivers and children under 2!

Unleash your child’s potential with music! Develop emotional control, language, math skills & creativity through play.

STARTS: Saturday 17th January 2026

ENDS: Saturday 21st March 2026

FREQUENCY: Weekly, Saturday mornings 10am – 11.30am

VENUE: The Swannery @ Wellspring Settlement, 43 Ducie Rd, Barton Hill, Bristol BS5 0AX

Discover how child-led musical play helps with developing baby and toddler’s managing big emotions, powerful communication skills, a love of language, a foundation in numbers and their inner rockstar.

Dads Rock (it’s not just a saying, it’s a movement!) is also a chance to build a community with other Dads and share your parenting adventure and musical experiences.

The group is an 8-week adventure and is absolutely free to join. It is made possible through Bristol Family Hubs and you will need to be a Bristol City Council resident to access sessions.

Barton Hill Dads Rock starts on 17th January 2026 and runs until the 21st March (there are no sessions taking place on 14th or 21st February due to half term). Ideally Dads / male caregivers will join the musical revolution for the January start but this is not mandatory, so please do get in contact with us if you can only start after this date.

DATES: Session dates are Saturday mornings 10am – 11.30am

17th January
24th January
31st January
7th February
28th February
7th March
14th March
21st March
*Please note there are no sessions running on 14th or 21st February.

BOOKING INFO: https://www.eventbrite.co.uk/e/barton-hill-dads-rock-8-week-group-january-2026-tickets-1978355874677?aff=oddtdtcreator

Contact Emma if you would like further information about the group before signing up – emma@evolvemusic.org.uk]]></value>
