          <Data name="13. About Opportunity">
            <value>The Exeter Community Family Orchestra brings the joy of making music to everyone! This multi-generational group enjoys fun, easily accessible sessions. Inclusivity is key - open to all; any instrument, any standard, any age!
Music is proven to bring social and health benefits to the lives of people, and at BSO we believe everyone should be able to have the chance to create and perform music with others.

The sessions are run by our Associate, Emma Welton, who helps participants to shape the music, explore new ways to create sound and enjoy the social element of music in a comfortable environment.

Exeter Community Family Orchestra provides a common meeting ground, regardless of music taste, experience or ability. It promotes shared experiences across generations and provides a musical family for those living on their own.</value>
