        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South West<br>3. County: Devon<br>4. Location: Torquay Boys Grammar School, Torquay TQ27EL - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): Orchestra<br>7. Genre: Orchestral<br>8. Age: <br>9. Level: Grade 1+<br>10. Instruments: Piccolo/Flute, Clarinet, Trumpet, Trombone, Tuba, Horns, Violin, Viola, Cello, Double Bass<br>11. Other Tags: Grade 1, Grade 2, Grade 3, Grade 4, Grade 5, Grade 6, Grade 7, Grade 8<br>12. Cost: £45 per term<br>13. About Opportunity: Concert Orchestra is for players who have reached grade 1 standard. Music is arranged to suit individual standards. This orchestra provides a good introduction to playing in a group. The emphasis is on developing technique and expanding repertoire to increase players’ confidence .<br>Instruments:<br>violin, viola, cello, double bass, flute, clarinet, oboe, bassoon, saxophone and brass instruments<br>Grades:<br>suitable for beginners and moderately experienced players of grades 1 and above.<br>Directed by:<br>Helen Wills. Helen teaches cello and piano, and uses the Suzuki method combined with traditional teaching. Some of her pupils have become professional musicians in their own right. She is a talented arranger.<br>14. When: Fridays 16:30 - 19:00 (part of the music school)<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://tsdmc.org.uk/ensembles/<br>16. Organisation Name: Torbay & South Devon Music Centre<br>17. About Organisation: Torbay and South Devon Music Centre provides the opportunity for musicians to enjoy playing instruments and improve musical skills by performing together. Orchestras and bands are led by experienced musicians and there are opportunities to try new and endangered instruments and to play in concerts as well as weekly rehearsals. Membership is £45 per term per student. Bursaries and reductions are available for Fast Forward groups and families.<br><br>"Music Centre is for young musicians living in Torbay, Teignbridge or the South Hams. You can be any age and it doesn’t matter what sort of school you go to. You may be learning to play your instrument at school, or at home or at your teacher’s home – or you may not be having lessons at all. We also welcome parents and other not-so-young musicians. You need to be able to play a suitable instrument – have a look at the list on this page. Players of all standards can enjoy Music Centre, from beginners who can play a few tunes to experts who have been playing for some time. If you have passed any music exams (grades 1 to 8) that will help you to choose a suitable group. If not, don’t worry – we will advise you. It helps if you can read music for your instrument but don’t worry if you can’t – you will get plenty of help. You do not need any previous experience of playing in an ensemble or orchestra.<br><br><br>All instruments used in orchestras, wind bands and brass bands are played at Music Centre. Here is a list of them. If you play another instrument, please contact us – we may be able to include you in one of our ensembles.<br>Strings<br>violin<br>viola<br>cello<br>double bass<br>harp<br>Ukulele<br>Percussion<br>timpani (kettle drums)<br>side drum, bass drum<br>cymbal, triangle, tambourine, etc.<br>xylophone, glockenspiel<br>drum kit<br>Woodwind<br>flute<br>clarinet<br>saxophone<br>oboe<br>cor anglais<br>bassoon<br>Brass<br>trumpet<br>cornet<br>trombone<br>baritone horn<br>French horn<br>tuba"<br>18. Organisation Website: https://tsdmc.org.uk/<br>19. Only for London/Local?: Local Only<br>20. Extra Notes: Music Centre is for young musicians living in Torbay, Teignbridge or the South Hams. You can be any age and it doesn’t matter what sort of school you go to. You may be learning to play your instrument at school, or at home or at your teacher’s home – or you may not be having lessons at all. We also welcome parents and other not-so-young musicians. You need to be able to play a suitable instrument – have a look at the list on this page. Players of all standards can enjoy Music Centre, from beginners who can play a few tunes to experts who have been playing for some time. If you have passed any music exams (grades 1 to 8) that will help you to choose a suitable group. If not, don’t worry – we will advise you. It helps if you can read music for your instrument but don’t worry if you can’t – you will get plenty of help. You do not need any previous experience of playing in an ensemble or orchestra.<br><br><br>All instruments used in orchestras, wind bands and brass bands are played at Music Centre. Here is a list of them. If you play another instrument, please contact us – we may be able to include you in one of our ensembles.<br>Strings<br>violin<br>viola<br>cello<br>double bass<br>harp<br>Ukulele<br>Percussion<br>timpani (kettle drums)<br>side drum, bass drum<br>cymbal, triangle, tambourine, etc.<br>xylophone, glockenspiel<br>drum kit<br>Woodwind<br>flute<br>clarinet<br>saxophone<br>oboe<br>cor anglais<br>bassoon<br>Brass<br>trumpet<br>cornet<br>trombone<br>baritone horn<br>French horn<br>tuba]]></description>
