        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South West<br>3. County: Devon<br>4. Location: Torquay Boys Grammar School, Torquay TQ27EL - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): Woodwind Ensemble<br>7. Genre: Orchestral<br>8. Age: <br>9. Level: Grade 3+<br>10. Instruments: All<br>11. Other Tags: Grade 3, Grade 4, Grade 5, Grade 6, Grade 7, Grade 8<br>12. Cost: £45 per term<br>13. About Opportunity: The Flute Choir gives flautists the opportunity to play rare and valuable bass and alto flutes, and encourages the playing of the piccolo. Flute choirs have some beautiful music written and arranged for them.<br>Instruments:<br>piccolo, flute, alto flute, bass flute.<br>Grades:<br>suitable for moderately experienced and advanced flute players, grades 3 or more.<br>Directed by:<br>Claire Hindle, an accomplished teacher of woodwind and piano in schools and privately, with over 20 years experience. She has conducted many woodwind ensembles and orchestras. Claire believes that music should be a fun and rewarding experience for both adults and children.<br>14. When: Fridays 16:30 - 19:00 (part of the music school)<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://tsdmc.org.uk/ensembles/<br>16. Organisation Name: Torbay & South Devon Music Centre<br>17. About Organisation: Torbay and South Devon Music Centre provides the opportunity for musicians to enjoy playing instruments and improve musical skills by performing together. Orchestras and bands are led by experienced musicians and there are opportunities to try new and endangered instruments and to play in concerts as well as weekly rehearsals. Membership is £45 per term per student. Bursaries and reductions are available for Fast Forward groups and families.<br><br>"Music Centre is for young musicians living in Torbay, Teignbridge or the South Hams. You can be any age and it doesn’t matter what sort of school you go to. You may be learning to play your instrument at school, or at home or at your teacher’s home – or you may not be having lessons at all. We also welcome parents and other not-so-young musicians. You need to be able to play a suitable instrument – have a look at the list on this page. Players of all standards can enjoy Music Centre, from beginners who can play a few tunes to experts who have been playing for some time. If you have passed any music exams (grades 1 to 8) that will help you to choose a suitable group. If not, don’t worry – we will advise you. It helps if you can read music for your instrument but don’t worry if you can’t – you will get plenty of help. You do not need any previous experience of playing in an ensemble or orchestra.<br><br><br>All instruments used in orchestras, wind bands and brass bands are played at Music Centre. Here is a list of them. If you play another instrument, please contact us – we may be able to include you in one of our ensembles.<br>Strings<br>violin<br>viola<br>cello<br>double bass<br>harp<br>Ukulele<br>Percussion<br>timpani (kettle drums)<br>side drum, bass drum<br>cymbal, triangle, tambourine, etc.<br>xylophone, glockenspiel<br>drum kit<br>Woodwind<br>flute<br>clarinet<br>saxophone<br>oboe<br>cor anglais<br>bassoon<br>Brass<br>trumpet<br>cornet<br>trombone<br>baritone horn<br>French horn<br>tuba"<br>18. Organisation Website: https://tsdmc.org.uk/<br>19. Only for London/Local?: Local Only<br>20. Extra Notes: Music Centre is for young musicians living in Torbay, Teignbridge or the South Hams. You can be any age and it doesn’t matter what sort of school you go to. You may be learning to play your instrument at school, or at home or at your teacher’s home – or you may not be having lessons at all. We also welcome parents and other not-so-young musicians. You need to be able to play a suitable instrument – have a look at the list on this page. Players of all standards can enjoy Music Centre, from beginners who can play a few tunes to experts who have been playing for some time. If you have passed any music exams (grades 1 to 8) that