        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South West<br>3. County: Devon<br>4. Location: Paignton Baptist Church - UK<br>5. Type: Workshop<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): <br>7. Genre: Other<br>8. Age: Young Carers<br>9. Level: Young Carers<br>10. Instruments: <br>11. Other Tags: <br>12. Cost: Free<br>13. About Opportunity: <br>Young Carers<br>Our Young Carers music project takes places once or twice a month, on Mondays at Paignton Baptist Church on Winner Street. <br>​<br>These sessions are open to all young people with a caring responsibility at home, whether they have undergone a formal Young Carers assessment or not.<br>​<br>Within these sessions, we are led by the group and their musical interests and ideas. Some weeks we create songs, jam, use our voices, experiment with instruments and music technology. Let us know what might interest you. <br>​<br>To join these FREE sessions please email Laura on info@weneedmusic.org or call 07349904889. Alternatively, fill in this contact form and we'll get back to you.<br>​<br>Our upcoming dates for 2026 are:<br>Mon 23rd Feb<br>Mon 16th March<br>Mon 27th April<br>Mon 18th May<br>Mon 22nd June<br>Mon 29th June<br>We meet from 6.30-7.30pm at Paignton Baptist Church.<br>14. When: Mondays 18:30 - 19:30<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://www.weneedmusic.org/youngcarers<br>16. Organisation Name: We Need Music CIC<br>17. About Organisation: Playful, interactive music making aimed at connecting people; nurturing creativity; and building self esteem and confidence<br>​<br>Aspiring for our work to be inclusive with equality of access for all<br>18. Organisation Website: https://www.weneedmusic.org<br>19. Only for London/Local?: <br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
