        <address>The Old Firestation, Bournemouth - UK</address>
        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South West<br>3. County: Dorset<br>4. Location: The Old Firestation, Bournemouth - UK<br>5. Type: Performance Opportunity<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): <br>7. Genre: Rock<br>8. Age: 13 - 18<br>9. Level: Competition<br>10. Instruments: <br>11. Other Tags: Free<br>12. Cost: Free<br>13. About Opportunity: Are you in a band, at school, college or home educated, live across BCP, Southampton, IOW or Portsmouth, and fancy getting some fantastic auditioning and gigging experience?<br><br>STEP 1: Complete the application form below <br><br>Please note that confirmation emails aren’t generated automatically from the form but as long as you get to the Thank You message at the end, consider it submitted successfully.<br><br>STEP 2: Video audition: <br><br>Your video should be of your band performing 1 track of around 3 minutes which showcases your collective talent and enthusiasm.<br>At this first stage it doesn’t need to be polished or professional – we just want to see/hear an example of a song you are rehearsing or have performed, so, a good video you’ve taken on your phone is fine!<br>TIP – try to adjust your dynamic/volume levels for the purposes of the video audition so that we can hear all the parts in the video submitted. In the past we’ve received videos where we can only hear one part, or no vocals at all for example, because everyone is playing too loud for the small space they’re in and the device they’re recording on… don’t worry – in the real thing you’ll be able to give us the full throttle energy and the dynamic best suited to your style because you’ll have a Sound Engineer getting you set up!<br>Please submit your video audition via the website www.wetransfer.com, send to jo.farley@bcpcouncil.gov.uk and make sure to include the name of your band!  <br>The Competition<br><br>Once the application deadline has passed, successful bands will be allocated one of two Heats and will be asked to prepare 2-3 songs (covers or originals) lasting no more than 10 minutes:<br>14. When: Annually<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://soundstorm-music.org.uk/get-involved/bandstorm/<br>16. Organisation Name: Soundstorm Music<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: <br>19. Only for London/Local?: Local Only<br>20. Extra Notes: Eligible addresses: BCP (Bournmouth, Christchurch, Poole), Southampton, Isle of Wight, Portsmouth]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1899-817717-labelson</styleUrl>
