        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South West<br>3. County: Dorset<br>4. Location: Parkstone Grammar School - UK<br>5. Type: Workshop<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): <br>7. Genre: Early Years<br>8. Age: Key Stage 1<br>9. Level: Any Ability<br>10. Instruments: <br>11. Other Tags: Early Years<br>12. Cost: £16 per term<br>13. About Opportunity: Aimed at key stage 1 children, young musicians are invited to gain musicianship development in this high quality session, set mainly around the piano learning fun songs and engaging rhythm games in an immensely fun setting with the inspiring professional music teacher, Jenny Barrett. They also develop aural & rhythmic skills towards instrumental learning. No previous experience is necessary. We involve a “try out an instrument” session each term.<br><br>STARTS BACK 17.00 – 17.30, MONDAY 29th Sept, 2025 (excludes bank holiday and half term)<br>TRY OUT 1 WEEK FREE OF CHARGE! The concert will take place alongside our other Monday academy groups and soloists on 7th July at Yarrells school followed by picnic and games!<br>Many thanks to SoundStorm and our sponsors who enable this class to be accessible to all, hence we are delighted to be able to offer this at a heavily subsidised rate of £16 for the term<br>14. When: Mondays (check on website for upcoming dates)<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://broadstonemusicseries.info/music-academy-lessons/<br>16. Organisation Name: Poole Society for Young Musicians<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: <br>19. Only for London/Local?: <br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
