        <address>Poole Grammar School - UK</address>
        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South West<br>3. County: Dorset<br>4. Location: Poole Grammar School - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): Brass Ensemble<br>7. Genre: Orchestral<br>8. Age: Up to 18<br>9. Level: Grade 5+<br>10. Instruments: <br>11. Other Tags: Grade 5, Grade 6, Grade 7, Grade 8<br>12. Cost: £56 per term<br>13. About Opportunity: Full of technical and repertoire building with some of the most inspiring brass teachers in the profession, young musicians develop many new skills and learn repertoire from Baroque to Jazz. Also, improve technique, develop improvisation skills with our amazing Robb Tooley from the BSO!<br>This is Jurassic Brass’ 4th exciting year as they go from strength to strength. Last year they were invited and spent a workshop day with Richmond Music Trust Brass in London, and during this summer term they worked with and performed in concert alongside some invited brass friends, members of the BSO and performed at the Lighthouse in the spring 2025. Jurassic Brass performing schedule is getting busy and have some more exciting plans!<br><br><br>14. When: Mondays (check on website for upcoming dates)<br>16:30 - 17:30<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://broadstonemusicseries.info/music-academy-lessons/<br>16. Organisation Name: Poole Society for Young Musicians<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: <br>19. Only for London/Local?: <br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
