        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South West<br>3. County: Dorset<br>4. Location: Parkstone Grammar School - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): String Ensemble<br>7. Genre: Orchestral<br>8. Age: Up to 18<br>9. Level: Grade 5+<br>(Grade 2-4 cellists also welcome)<br>10. Instruments: <br>11. Other Tags: Grade 5, Grade 6, Grade 7, Grade 8<br>12. Cost: £45 per term<br>13. About Opportunity: Following the continued success of our Poole Society of Young Musicians Chamber music scheme, we proudly offer again this term Camerata chamber coaching sessions and solo performances classes, supported by the Albert & Eugenie Frost Trust.<br><br>This programme will take place over 4 afternoon sessions with end of season performance and catering for Grade 5+ string players with an occasional outstanding pianist too. Our junior cello ensemble offers places for grade 2-4 cellists.<br> <br><br>Fee: £45 (4 sessions of chamber music training and concert)<br><br>Please fill out one of these forms for each person wishing to apply to take part.  Applications should be from young people up to 18 years of age and the number of places is restricted.  <br><br>Spring 2026 chamber music training sessions - afternoons: <br>25th Jan, 8th Feb, 1st March - Dumpton School <br>8th March - Parkstone Grammar School with end concert <br>Summer term dates tbc soon!<br>14. When: Various dates/venues<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://broadstonemusicseries.info/music-academy-lessons/<br>16. Organisation Name: Poole Society for Young Musicians<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: <br>19. Only for London/Local?: <br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
