        <name>Wessex New Strings</name>
        <address>Lychett Minster School, Poole - UK</address>
        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South West<br>3. County: Dorset<br>4. Location: Lychett Minster School, Poole - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): String Ensemble<br>7. Genre: Orchestral<br>8. Age: Young Musicians<br>9. Level: Preparatory - Grade 3<br>10. Instruments: <br>11. Other Tags: Preparatory, Grade 1, Grade 2, Grade 3<br>12. Cost: From £75 per term<br>13. About Opportunity: ​As the name suggests, this ensemble welcomes the newest string players, giving these young musicians their first taste of orchestral playing. <br><br>The New Strings rehearsals enable youngsters to begin to make use of the skills they are learning in their instrumental lessons. The focus is on playing together, listening to each other, maintaining good posture and keeping going!<br><br>It brings a vital extra purpose to their instrumental lessons and practice at home, enables these newest young musicians to meet and make new friends with the same interests.<br>14. When: Saturdays 9:00 - 10:15<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://www.youthmusicwessex.org/string-orchestras.html<br>16. Organisation Name: Youth Music Wessex<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: <br>19. Only for London/Local?: <br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
