ent, including leads and amps (if electric).<br>You’ll also need to bring enough drinks and a packed lunch/snacks to keep you going during the day. There won’t be an opportunity to buy refreshments during the day.<br> How much? £70 for membership up until end of June 2026 (members will need to commit to at least 4 sessions including the May and June sessions). £15.00 to attend one-off sessions.<br><br>We do not want financial hardship to be a barrier for young people. To find out how SoundStorm can assist, please contact Claire Butler at claire.butler@bcpcouncil.gov.uk.<br><br>For any other queries regarding the Creative Ensemble, please contact Sarah Derwish at sarah.derwish@bcpcouncil.gov.uk<br>14. When: Saturdays, Various Times <br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://soundstorm-music.org.uk/schools-teachers/music-hub/ensembles/creative-ensemble/<br>16. Organisation Name: Soundstorm Music<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: <br>19. Only for London/Local?: <br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
