        <name>Music Futures</name>
        <address>Lyric Theatre, Bridport - UK</address>
        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South West<br>3. County: Dorset<br>4. Location: Lyric Theatre, Bridport - UK<br>5. Type: Workshop<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): <br>7. Genre: Professional Development<br>8. Age: 16 - 25<br>9. Level: All Abilities<br>10. Instruments: <br>11. Other Tags: Free<br>12. Cost: Free<br>13. About Opportunity: The Harbour Records/B Sharp MusicFutures programme supports young aspiring musicians (aged 16 to 25) living in Dorset, UK, to take the next steps towards a creative career. <br>Participants are supported to record and release their original music on the Harbour Records Label. Through the programme they will develop their musical abilities and confidence, build their industry knowledge, develop their networks and showcase their talents through monthly industry masterclasses, networking and showcase events and individual mentoring.  <br>The programme runs from October 2025– July 2026. <br>The programme involves: <br>Masterclasses in composition, recording, production, musical skills, finance and marketing <br>Networking, sharing and socials <br>Individual mentoring and recording sessions <br>Final showcase event <br>Programme dates:<br>Wednesdays 7pm – 9pm<br>2025 – Oct 22nd, Nov 26th, Dec 10th<br>2026 – Jan 21st, Feb 25th, March 25th, April 22nd, May 20th, June 17th, July tba<br>Individual mentoring and recording sessions will be arranged around your availability.<br>Venue:  Lyric Theatre, Bridport, Dorset <br>To apply for this year’s programme please complete our application form:<br>Link to Music Futures Application Form<br>Any queries please email info@bsharp.org.uk <br>The programme is funded by Octagon Music Hub and Youth Music. <br>14. When: Year-long programme<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSd2aARGwVNA4GoxnWrK3WjIE2_07SbDhKPf36N1PB9MeHrv-w/viewform<br>16. Organisation Name: BSharp<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: <br>19. Only for London/Local?: <br>20. Extra Notes: Application necessary]]></description>
