          <Data name="13. About Opportunity">
            <value>This inclusive, creative music group is for children and young people with special educational needs/disabilities and their parents/carers and siblings in the Brighton area.

ACTIVITY OVERVIEW

Anyone interested in making music is invited to join us. You do not need any prior experience, although more experienced musicians are also welcome. Members will have the opportunity to try a number of instruments and to choose what they would like to play. Parents/Carers are also invited to come and learn/play alongside their children.

o360 is a course-based music group, with one project taking place each term. Projects are usually 4-6 weeks in length and all build towards a performance. In our first year o360 performed at the Corn Exchange and Brighton Centre.

The group is led by composer and music leader James Redwood and a team of friendly and experienced music leaders from Create Music.

We hold two sessions during this time, O360 Jam band is for our younger members which is from 9.30-10.15am. Our o360 ensemble is for older members which runs from 10.30-12 midday. </value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="14. When">
            <value>Saturdays, 9:30 - 10:15 (younger members), 10:30 - 12:00 (older members)</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="15. Opportunity Website / Signup">
            <value>https://createmusic.org.uk/for-children-and-young-people/music-groups/bhmc-orchestra-360/</value>
          </Data>
