      <Placemark>
        <name>Brighton and East Sussex Youth Orchestra</name>
        <address><![CDATA[Priory School & Performing Arts Centre, Lewes - UK]]></address>
        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South East<br>3. County: East Sussex<br>4. Location: Priory School & Performing Arts Centre, Lewes - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): Orchestra<br>7. Genre: Orchestral<br>8. Age: 12 - 18<br>9. Level: Grade 6+<br>10. Instruments: <br>11. Other Tags: Grade 6, Grade 7, Grade 8, Audition<br>12. Cost: £104 per term<br>13. About Opportunity: The Brighton & East Sussex Youth Orchestra meet for weekly rehearsals during term-time, setting itself the challenge to perform great music of the classical repertoire. They have performed music by symphonies by Brahms, Beethoven and Florence Price, as well as Copland’s Appalachian Spring and Bernstein’s iconic West Side Story. They have also performed film and gaming music such as Star Wars, Batman and Horizon: Zero Dawn.<br><br>BESYO is often given the opportunity to perform at Brighton Dome as part of Brighton Festival, performing concertos including Elgar’s infamous Cello Concerto, and Florence Price’s Piano Concerto with Jeneba Kanneh-Mason. They also perform throughout Brighton & East Sussex, as well as regular tours to France, Belgium and Germany.<br><br>The orchestra’s Artistic Director is Pete Davison, composer and conductor, who is supported by a team of tutors who give their time and experience to working with the orchestra at rehearsals on Friday evenings. Auditions take place throughout the year. If you play an orchestral instrument and are Grade 6 standard or above, why not apply?     <br>14. When: Fridays 18:00 - 20:30<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://createmusic.org.uk/for-children-and-young-people/music-groups/brighton-east-sussex-youth-orchestra-besyo/<br>16. Organisation Name: Create Music / Brighton Dome<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: <br>19. Only for London/Local?: <br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1801-9C27B0-labelson</styleUrl>
