        <name>Orchestra 360 - Hastings and Rother</name>
        <address><![CDATA[St Richard's Catholic College, Bexhill-on-Sea - UK]]></address>
        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South East<br>3. County: East Sussex<br>4. Location: St Richard's Catholic College, Bexhill-on-Sea - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): SEND Inclusive Ensemble<br>7. Genre: Other<br>8. Age: 12 - 20<br>9. Level: Any Ability<br>10. Instruments: <br>11. Other Tags: Free, No Experience, SEND<br>12. Cost: Free<br>13. About Opportunity: Anyone interested in making music is invited to join us. You do not need any prior experience, although more experienced musicians are also welcome. Members will have the opportunity to try a number of instruments and to choose what they would like to play. Parents/Carers are also invited to come and learn/play alongside their children.<br><br>o360 Hastings & Rother is a brand new course-based music group. Following the success of o360 groups in Brighton & Hove and Eastbourne, we are pleased to be launching a new group for young people from Hastings and Rother. <br><br>The group is led by cellist, composer, collaborator and creative project leader Tara Franks and a team of friendly and experienced music leaders from Create Music.<br>14. When: Saturdays (view website for future dates) 10:30 - 11:30<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://createmusic.org.uk/for-children-and-young-people/music-groups/hrmc-orchestra-360/<br>16. Organisation Name: Create Music / Brighton Dome<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: <br>19. Only for London/Local?: <br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
