        <name>Hastings and Rother String Group</name>
        <address><![CDATA[St Richard's Catholic College, Bexhill-on-Sea - UK]]></address>
        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South East<br>3. County: East Sussex<br>4. Location: St Richard's Catholic College, Bexhill-on-Sea - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): String Ensemble<br>7. Genre: Orchestral<br>8. Age: 6+ (after 6 months of learning)<br>9. Level: After 6 months of learning<br>10. Instruments: <br>11. Other Tags: Preparatory<br>12. Cost: £91 per term<br>13. About Opportunity: A mixed ensemble for young Violinists and Cellists who would normally have been learning for 6 months and will be confident using the bow and their fingers.<br><br>ACTIVITY OVERVIEW<br><br>String group is an opportunity for our youngest musicians to come together and start making music.  It is for Violinists and Cellists who have been learning for approximately 6 months or more and are at a Beginner to Grade 1 level of learning. They will play tunes together as a mixed ensemble and learn how to follow a conductor. This fun ensemble will help the children to learn music of different styles and cultures, and assist them in developing their technique.  Time will be spent developing music reading skills, simple part-playing and general musicianship.  A great way to help maintain enthusiasm in the early stages!<br>14. When: Saturdays 11:15 - 12:15<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://createmusic.org.uk/for-children-and-young-people/music-groups/hrmc-string-group/<br>16. Organisation Name: Create Music / Brighton Dome<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: <br>19. Only for London/Local?: <br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
