        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South West<br>3. County: Gloucestershire<br>4. Location: Sir Thomas Rich's School, Oakleaze - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): Orchestra<br>7. Genre: Orchestral<br>8. Age: Young Musicians<br>9. Level: Preparatory (all instruments)<br>10. Instruments: <br>11. Other Tags: Preparatory, Audition<br>12. Cost: £175 per year<br>13. About Opportunity: One FREE term of ensemble sessions for students in their first year of learning.<br><br>Brookfield’s Junior Orchestra is our introductory level group, catering for all instruments. We welcome anyone who has been involved in Whole Class Ensemble Tuition (WCET) schemes through their schools as well as individuals who have been learning at home.  It doesn't matter if you only know 5 notes on your instrument or if you can't read music, as the staff at Junior Orchestra can teach you all you need to know.<br>14. When: Saturday Mornings<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://www.gloucestershiremusic.co.uk/youth-groups/music-centres/brookfield-music-centre-bmc/<br>16. Organisation Name: Gloucestershire Music<br>17. About Organisation: About Us<br><br>Gloucestershire Music is the county’s largest delivery partner for the county’s Music Education Hub ‘Make Music Gloucestershire’, which is funded by Arts Council England.<br><br> Our Mission<br><br>is to provide high quality, accessible and enjoyable musical experiences for children and adults.  Our team is passionate about music education and making a difference to people’s lives through the power of music.  Whether playing an instrument or singing is a hobby or a career path choice we have something to offer everyone, as we provide musical ensembles for all levels of learner.<br>is to support schools and music educators around the county to confidently deliver music to young people in their classrooms<br>Delivery<br><br> At Gloucestershire Music we...<br><br>provide schools with whole class instrumental lessons, CPD for sta