        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South West<br>3. County: Gloucestershire<br>4. Location: St Whites Primary School, Cinderford - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): String Ensemble<br>7. Genre: Orchestral<br>8. Age: All <br>9. Level: Beginners<br>10. Instruments: <br>11. Other Tags: <br>12. Cost: £175 per year<br>13. About Opportunity: In order to support the development of budding string players in the Forest of Dean we will also be starting a new 'String Starters' group for beginners of all ages from 13th January 2026.  Why not come and learn alongside your child, or give your child the opportunity to develop further if they have experienced Whole Class Instrumental Tuition (WCET) in their school.  Maybe convince a friend that your New Year resolution for 2026 is to start learning an instrument - it's great for your mental and physical health, as well as being lots of fun!<br>14. When: Tuesdays 18:30 - 19:30<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://www.gloucestershiremusic.co.uk/youth-groups/music-centres/forest-music-centre/<br>16. Organisation Name: Gloucestershire Music<br>17. About Organisation: About Us<br><br>Gloucestershire Music is the county’s largest delivery partner for the county’s Music Education Hub ‘Make Music Gloucestershire’, which is funded by Arts Council England.<br><br> Our Mission<br><br>is to provide high quality, accessible and enjoyable musical experiences for children and adults.  Our team is passionate about music education and making a difference to people’s lives through the power of music.  Whether playing an instrument or singing is a hobby or a career path choice we have something to offer everyone, as we provide musical ensembles for all levels of learner.<br>is to support schools and music educators around the county to confidently deliver music to young people in their classrooms<br>Delivery<br><br> At Gloucestershire Music we...<br><br>provide schools with whole class instrumental lessons, CPD for staff