          <Data name="13. About Opportunity">
            <value>Gloucestershire Youth Orchestra was formed in 1951 and is one of the county music groups run by Gloucestershire Music.

The orchestra give as many as six concerts a year, performing programmes that range from the 18th century to the present day. GYO have been awarded national recognition for their performances by attending Music for Youth’s National Festival as well as special recognition for their innovative performances.

Membership of GYO is by audition or teacher nomination, please contact us if you want to be considered for a place. Wind, brass and percussion players need to be at around a grade 7+ standard and string players around grade 6+. A positive attitude and commitment to rehearsals and concerts is required. 

Members are expected to attend at least 80% of rehearsals and give a firm commitment to all concert engagements. Absences from rehearsals should be communicated by emailing glosmusic@gloucestershire.gov.uk

 

Statement for all County Music Groups regarding membership

Grades are only a guide to the level required.  More important is a strong commitment and positive attitude alongside good sight reading and general musicianship skills. Teachers may recommend students for a specific group but the Musical Director has the final decision to whether a student is ready for entry into an ensemble.  Once you have gained a place in one of the county music groups, you will be required to maintain a high percentage of attendance at rehearsals and concerts.  A place within an ensemble may be withdrawn if commitment is deemed unsatisfactory. You can audition and join at any point throughout the year.  If a group is preparing for a concert or festival, you may be asked to wait a few weeks before joining.</value>
          </Data>
