        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: London<br>3. County: Greater London<br>4. Location: Kingston University, London - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): Orchestra<br>7. Genre: Orchestral<br>8. Age: Under 18<br>9. Level: 5 - 8+<br>10. Instruments: Piccolo/Flute, Clarinet, Oboe, Cor Anglais, Bassoon, Trumpet, Trombone, Tuba, Horns, Harp, Violin, Viola, Cello, Double Bass, Percussion, Euphonium<br>11. Other Tags: Grade 5, Grade 6, Grade 7, Grade 8<br>12. Cost: n/a<br>13. About Opportunity: Colourstrings Music School (CMS) offers music education from the age of eighteen months to eighteen years, running 33 Saturdays per year.<br><br>Children join CMS for music kindergarten between the ages of 18 months and the beginning of school year 1. To join the waiting list please fill in the form on the ‘kindergarten classes’ page. There is one other entry point to the school for advanced string players (grade 5 minimum) who wish to audition for Colourstrings Orchestra; our string chamber orchestra which meets each Saturday afternoon.<br>14. When: Saturdays, PM<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://www.colourstringsmusicschool.co.uk/index.cfm<br>16. Organisation Name: Colourstrings Music Academy<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: <br>19. Only for London/Local?: <br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
