        <name>Grinstead Music Fund</name>
        <address>Croydon, London - UK</address>
        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: London<br>3. County: Greater London<br>4. Location: Croydon, London - UK<br>5. Type: Grant/Fund<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): <br>7. Genre: Professional Development<br>8. Age: Under 26<br>9. Level: Grade 5+<br>10. Instruments: Piccolo/Flute, Clarinet, Oboe, Cor Anglais, Bassoon, Trumpet, Trombone, Tuba, Horns, Harp, Violin, Viola, Cello, Double Bass, Percussion, Piano/Keys, Guitar, Bass Guitar, Singing, Euphonium, Saxophone, Recorder<br>11. Other Tags: Grade 5, Grade 6, Grade 7, Grade 8<br>12. Cost: <br>13. About Opportunity: The fund was established in 1977 following the death in 1974 of Dorothy Grinstead who was a much- loved piano teacher and musician in Croydon.  A board of Trustees was formed to administer the fund to assist young Croydon musicians.<br><br>How can the fund help you?<br>Help with purchasing a new instrument<br><br>Help with tuition costs<br><br>Help with course costs<br><br>Criteria for applying<br>You must be, or have been, a student at a Croydon School/Academy for a substantial part of your secondary education, or currently in Year 6 at a Croydon Primary School/Academy OR be a Croydon resident<br><br>You should be Grade 5 standard minimum in your instrument<br><br>You must be a member of an ensemble/orchestra / music group or choir<br><br>You must supply references from your instrumental teacher and school<br><br>You will need to provide a reference or exam results to show how you have progressed with your instrument<br><br>You must be under 26 years of age<br>14. When: Ongoing<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://www.croydonmusicandarts.co.uk/about-us/funders-and-partners/the-grinstead-music-fund/<br>16. Organisation Name: Croydon Music Arts<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: <br>19. Only for London/Local?: <br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
