      <Placemark>
        <name>Access Music Makers</name>
        <address>Oasis Academy Shirley Park, Croydon - UK</address>
        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: London<br>3. County: Greater London<br>4. Location: Oasis Academy Shirley Park, Croydon - UK<br>5. Type: Classes<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): <br>7. Genre: Various<br>8. Age: Years 5 - 9<br>9. Level: all abilities<br>10. Instruments: <br>11. Other Tags: SEND<br>12. Cost: <br>13. About Opportunity: Access Music Makers is for disabled and neuro-diverse young people in school years 5-9. The group creates their own music using a variety of percussion, voices, and technology. The styles are eclectic, varying from pop songs to atmospheric soundscapes. Members' interests and aspirations are used to develop musical skills alongside confidence, teamwork, social awareness and much more. Please do get in touch with us for more information or 'click here' to see performances by our inclusive groups.<br>14. When: Saturdays 11:15 - 12:15<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://www.croydonmusicandarts.co.uk/learn-with-us/cma-centres-and-activities/friday-centre/<br>16. Organisation Name: Croydon Music Arts<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: <br>19. Only for London/Local?: <br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
