        <name>Hackney Lift-Off Ensemble</name>
        <address>Bridge Academy, Laburnum Street, London - UK</address>
        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: London<br>3. County: Greater London<br>4. Location: Bridge Academy, Laburnum Street, London - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): Mixed Ensemble<br>7. Genre: Various<br>8. Age: 10 - 18<br>9. Level: At least 1 year of lessons<br>10. Instruments: All<br>11. Other Tags: <br>12. Cost: £35 - £45 per term<br>13. About Opportunity: Hackney Lift-Off Ensemble is a beginner ensemble for young instrumentalists who are starting out on their instruments. We recommend players have been learning their instrument for a minimum of a year before signing up to join, either with an instrumental tutor or with their class music teacher as part of a whole class ensemble / first access programme.  The Lift-Off Ensemble provides opportunities for developing young musicians, building their creative practice, listening skills and general confidence in music-making with others.<br><br>All instruments welcome!<br><br>Hackney Lift-Off Ensemble is open to players in Year 4 and above<br>Applicants can be of Pre-Grade 1 standard but should have been taking lessons on their instrument for a minimum of a year<br>No audition is necessary for the Lift-Off Ensemble. Players become members by recommendation from their instrumental tutor or school music teacher, or by applying directly to HMS<br>Applicants must either live in the borough of Hackney or attend a Hackney school<br>Lift-Off may also accept pupils from neighbouring boroughs, please get in touch for more information<br>14. When: Tuesday 16:30 - 18:00<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://www.hackneymusic.co.uk/hackney-lift-off-ensemble/<br>16. Organisation Name: Hackney Music Service Network<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: <br>19. Only for London/Local?: Local Only<br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
