      <Placemark>
        <name>Hackney Borough Youth Choir</name>
        <address>Cardinal Pole Catholic School, London - UK</address>
        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: London<br>3. County: Greater London<br>4. Location: Cardinal Pole Catholic School, London - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): Choir<br>7. Genre: Choral<br>8. Age: 10-12<br>9. Level: Teacher Recommendation followed by an audition<br>10. Instruments: Singing<br>11. Other Tags: Audition, Invitation Only<br>12. Cost: £30 - £40 per term<br>13. About Opportunity: Junior HBYC was established as a progression route for Key Stage 2 singers.  Repertoire is diverse, challenging, joyful and exciting. Entry to the choir is via teacher recommendation followed by an audition. Termly invitations to audition are sent out to all primary schools in the borough and Head Teachers / Music Coordinators are asked to identify committed and experienced singers, usually who are already singing in their own school’s choirs, to apply. Auditions are friendly and informal. Pupils can join when they are in Yr4 – 6, and when they transfer to secondary school they can either continue with the Junior Choir for a further year or move straight up to the Senior Choir (Yr7+).  The choir performs regularly at both community events and large-scale HMS performances such as our annual Gala Concert at the Hackney Empire.<br>14. When: Wednesday 16:30 - 17:30<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://www.hackneymusic.co.uk/hbyc/<br>16. Organisation Name: Hackney Music Service Network<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: <br>19. Only for London/Local?: Local Only<br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
