      <Placemark>
        <name>Hackney Senior Vocal Ensemble</name>
        <address>Cardinal Pole Catholic School, London - UK</address>
        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: London<br>3. County: Greater London<br>4. Location: Cardinal Pole Catholic School, London - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): Choir<br>7. Genre: Choral<br>8. Age: 12 - 18<br>9. Level: Teacher Recommendation followed by an audition<br>10. Instruments: Singing<br>11. Other Tags: Audition, Invitation Only<br>12. Cost: £30 - £40 per term<br>13. About Opportunity: Senior HBYC was established more recently as a progression route for the already established Junior Choir. Like the Junior Choir, repertoire is diverse, challenging, joyful and exciting. The choir is made up of a combination of former Junior HBYC members, singers who have been referred direct from their secondary schools and singers getting in touch with us directly. Like the Junior Choir, entry is by audition, and these are friendly and informal.<br><br>Senior HBYC regularly perform. Annual events include the Hackney Music Service Gala at the Hackney Empire, the Hackney Schools Singing Festival at the Round Chapel and the Hackney One Carnival. In 2014 the choir took part in a BBC project that led to a performance at the Barbican and rehearsals at the iconic Maida Vale Studios. The performance was broadcast on BBC Radio 3. In 2018 the Senior Choir took part in a workshop at the Barbican Centre with the internationally acclaimed choir Roomful of Teeth.  The choir are regularly offered opportunities to work with professional choirs and offered tickets to concerts via our extensive network of hub partners.<br><br>When: Wednesdays 5.30pm – 6.30pm<br><br>Where: Both choirs rehearse at Cardinal Pole Catholic School, Morning Lane, E9 6LG<br><br>Termly membership to either choir costs £30 for young people attending a Hackney school, £40 for those living in Hackney but going to an out of borough school.  Costs for Pupil Premium families are £15 per term.<br><br>Both choirs are supported by our vocal pastoral team, Kelvin Ghann and Susan Brown.<br>14. When: Wednesday 17:30 - 18:00<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://www.hackneymusic.co.uk/hbyc/<br>16. Organisation Name: Hackney Music Service Network<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: <br>19. Only for London/Local?: Local Only<br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1801-9C27B0-labelson</styleUrl>
