        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: London<br>3. County: Greater London<br>4. Location: Tolworth Music Centre, Kingston - UK<br>5. Type: Classes<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): <br>7. Genre: Production/Mixing<br>8. Age: 7 - 12<br>9. Level: any<br>10. Instruments: Producing, Songwriting<br>11. Other Tags: No Experience<br>12. Cost: <br>13. About Opportunity: This weekly course will teach students all they need to know to record their very own song!<br><br>Suitable for children aged 7-12, this fun and interactive music production session will show kids how technology is a fundamental part of today's music.<br><br>Each week, we will focus on a different elements needed to compose their very own track which they will be able to show their friends and family and the end of each term.<br>14. When: not listed<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://www.kingston.gov.uk/schools-and-learning/kingston-music-service/bands-orchestras-and-theory-groups/music-technology-courses#lgd-guides__title<br>16. Organisation Name: Kingston Music Service<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: <br>19. Only for London/Local?: London & Local Only<br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
