          <Data name="13. About Opportunity">
            <value>Intermediate Concert Band (ICB) is aimed at students around Grade 2 – 4 standard, whose playing and ensemble skills are developing well, enabling them to tackle more complex arrangements. The repertoire ranges from standard concert band pieces to hits from stage and screen. As with all MMF groups, the emphasis is on learning the core skills needed to play successfully with other musicians, improving sight-reading, discovering a range of musical genres and enjoying themselves whilst playing together! ICB performs regularly at Music Centre concerts and at external events during the year.

Rehearsals take place in The Hall led by Sara Grint, Billy Fisher and Adam Cracknell.</value>
          </Data>
