        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: London<br>3. County: Greater London<br>4. Location: Wimbledon College, Edge Hill, Wimbledon - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): Concert Band<br>7. Genre: Orchestral<br>8. Age: 7 - 19<br>9. Level: Pre Grade 1 - 2<br>10. Instruments: Piccolo/Flute, Clarinet, Oboe, Cor Anglais, Bassoon, Trumpet, Trombone, Tuba, Horns, Percussion, Euphonium<br>11. Other Tags: Preparatory, Grade 1, Grade 2<br>12. Cost: https://mmf.org.uk/fees/<br>13. About Opportunity: Junior Concert Band ( JCB) is for students at pre-Grade 1 up to Grade 1/2 who are at an early stage of their playing and ensemble skills. Percussionists are invited to join once they have been members of the Junior Percussion Ensemble. The group will meet as a full band and in smaller combinations, so core skills including sight-reading and general musicianship can be developed at the right pace for each member.<br><br>Students will explore a wide range of musical genres and styles in a supportive and happy environment! There will be regular opportunities to perform to family and friends and at larger-scale events over the year.<br><br>Rehearsals take place in The Hall, led by Sara Grint, Billy Fisher and Adam Cracknell.<br>14. When: Saturdays 10:00 - 11:00<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://mmf.org.uk/ensembletimetable/<br>16. Organisation Name: Merton Music Foundation<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: <br>19. Only for London/Local?: London & Local Only<br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
