        <name>More Music Makers</name>
        <address>John Savage Centre, Hainault - UK</address>
        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: London<br>3. County: Greater London<br>4. Location: John Savage Centre, Hainault - UK<br>5. Type: Classes<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): <br>7. Genre: Various<br>8. Age: Years 2 - 4<br>9. Level: Any<br>10. Instruments: <br>11. Other Tags: <br>12. Cost: On sign up form<br>13. About Opportunity: More Music Makers is a class for children in Years 2, 3 or 4 who may have missed out on the opportunity to attend Music Kindergarten or Music Makers. They learn aural skills, musical literacy, transcription, composition, improvisation, ensemble skills and listening with understanding. These classes will enhance the musical learning of those children who are already learning an instrument while also being suitable for children who have had little formal music training<br><br>Classes use a range of percussion instruments, particularly xylophones and glockenspiels (which serve as a good introduction or accompaniment to learning the piano).<br><br>14. When: Thursdays 18:00 - 18:45<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://visionrcl.org.uk/music/learn-to-play/early-years/<br>16. Organisation Name: Redbridge Music Service<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: <br>19. Only for London/Local?: <br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
