        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: London<br>3. County: Greater London<br>4. Location: Redbridge, London - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): String Ensemble<br>7. Genre: Folk<br>8. Age: Year 5+<br>9. Level: Grade 2+ (or equivalent)<br>10. Instruments: Violin, Viola, Cello, Double Bass<br>11. Other Tags: Grade 2, Grade 3, Grade 4, Grade 5, Grade 6, Grade 7, Grade 8<br>12. Cost: https://visionrcl.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/RMS-Fees-Charges-September-2025.pdf<br>13. About Opportunity: This ensemble is for all string players at Grade 2 upwards and plays mostly folk-based music. Repertoire is learned by ear and from notation, and young musicians have lots of fun collaborating and supporting each other to perform an exciting range of music from folk traditions. String players in this ensemble are often also members of String Club, Junior String Orchestra, Intermediate Orchestra or Symphony Orchestra.<br>14. When: Thursdays 17:30 -- 18:30<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://visionrcl.org.uk/music/learn-to-play/clubs/<br>16. Organisation Name: Redbridge Music Service<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: <br>19. Only for London/Local?: <br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
