        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: London<br>3. County: Greater London<br>4. Location: Redbridge, London - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): Brass Ensemble<br>7. Genre: Orchestral<br>8. Age: Year 3 - Yr 13<br>9. Level: Pupils who can play and read at least 5 notes<br>10. Instruments: Trumpet, Trombone, Tuba, Horns, Euphonium<br>11. Other Tags: Preparatory<br>12. Cost: https://visionrcl.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/RMS-Fees-Charges-September-2025.pdf<br>13. About Opportunity: Mini Brass is the first level ensemble for all beginner brass players (trumpet, cornet, tenor horn, French horn, baritone horn, trombone, euphonium & tuba) who can play at least 5 notes. Music is arranged and adapted to suit all instruments and standards, and is a great way to experience ensemble playing for the first time. This is a fun first ensemble for brass players to experience playing alongside their peers.<br>14. When: Saturdays 9:30 - 10:30<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://visionrcl.org.uk/music/learn-to-play/clubs/<br>16. Organisation Name: Redbridge Music Service<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: <br>19. Only for London/Local?: <br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
