          <Data name="13. About Opportunity">
            <value>Pupils can join Oboe Club at any point in the year, either on teacher recommendation or as soon as they are able to play notes within the range of one octave, from low D to the D eight notes above. Parts range in difficulty to accommodate a variety of standards within the group. Help is available with reeds from the teacher, an invaluable resource for double reed players. This group is a friendly and supportive group for oboists, enabling young musicians to make faster progress on their instrument and learn vital ensemble and musicianship skills.</value>
