        <name><![CDATA[Tomorrow's Warriors: Fundamentals]]></name>
        <address>Southbank Centre, London - UK</address>
        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: London<br>3. County: Greater London<br>4. Location: Southbank Centre, London - UK<br>5. Type: Workshop<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): <br>7. Genre: Jazz<br>8. Age: Young Musicians<br>9. Level: Confident on Instrument<br>10. Instruments: <br>11. Other Tags: <br>12. Cost: Free<br>13. About Opportunity: The Fundamentals – led by Ky Osborne<br><br>This practical class is a fun, encouraging space, focusing on gaining confidence in improvisation, as well as covering some basic fundamental concepts within jazz theory and performance.<br>14. When: <br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://tomorrowswarriors.org/contact/our-programmes-at-southbank-centre/<br>16. Organisation Name: Southbank Centre / Tomorrow's Warriors<br>17. About Organisation: Tomorrow’s Warriors invites young musicians interested in learning jazz and pursuing a career in music to join our Young Artist Development Programme.<br><br>We are looking for enthusiastic young musicians who are confident on their instruments to join our programme. Our sessions are completely free, so there’s no need to worry about the cost.<br><br>We run sessions every weekend during the school term and additional rehearsals throughout the week (see details below). To check if we can offer you a place, just fill in the details on the form below. Due to high demand we currently have a waiting list to join our programme, but we are still accepting musicians on certain instruments and are keen to accommodate for talented musicians.<br>18. Organisation Website: <br>19. Only for London/Local?: No Restriction<br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
