          <Data name="13. About Opportunity">
            <value><![CDATA[At the Southwark Music Saturday Centre, we offer young people a fun and engaging programme of music throughout the morning. With an emphasis on musicianship and ensemble skills, our young musicians gain a broad understanding and appreciation of a range of styles and disciplines.

Instrumental & Ensemble Playing for Southwark Children
Children in Year 3 and above who live or go to school in Southwark can take part in a wide range of music activities, including:

Instrumental lessons

Ensemble playing (group music-making)

Choir singing

Percussion

Music theory and listening skills

These sessions are designed to build confidence, improve musical skills, and help children enjoy making music in a variety of settings.

Classical, Jazz and Rock & Pop Exams
When ready, students can be entered for Classical, Jazz and Rock & Pop public examinations, currently provided by ABRSM (The Associated Board of the Royal Schools of Music), Trinity College London and Rockschool.]]></value>
          </Data>
