        <name>Sutton Young Singers</name>
        <address>Carshalton Methodist Churdh, Ruskin Road, Carshalton - UK</address>
        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: London<br>3. County: Greater London<br>4. Location: Carshalton Methodist Churdh, Ruskin Road, Carshalton - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): Choir<br>7. Genre: Choral<br>8. Age: 8 - 13<br>9. Level: Auditioned<br>10. Instruments: <br>11. Other Tags: Audition<br>12. Cost: £84.50 per term (discounts for siblings/multiple ensembles)<br>13. About Opportunity: Sutton Young Singers (SYS) is an auditioned choir for enthusiastic and talented young singers aged 8-13, open to boys and girls with unchanged voices. We are a friendly, inclusive choir that likes to sing lots of different styles of music from folk to pop, musicals to classical. Sutton Young Singers rehearse weekly (term-time only) and enjoy performing at end of term concerts and special events. No previous experience is necessary, and you do not need to be able to read music to join our choir! <br><br>“I like that the songs are really fun, that you make a lot of new friends and that you get to sing solos!” – Magdalene <br><br>“I like that we get lots of opportunities to do solos and we get to meet lots of new people. We are able to sing in lots of different places that we might not have been before.” – Sophie  <br><br>“I like my friends that I’ve made here. Singing is fun and I love the music!” – Maksym  <br>14. When: Thursdays 17:00 - 18:00<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://suttonmusictrust.org.uk/singing/sutton-young-singers/<br>16. Organisation Name: Sutton Music Trust<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: <br>19. Only for London/Local?: London & Local Only<br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
