        <name>Sutton Supernova Singers</name>
        <address>Cognus Limited, Cantium House, Railway Approach, Wallington, SM6 ODZ - UK</address>
        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: London<br>3. County: Greater London<br>4. Location: Cognus Limited, Cantium House, Railway Approach, Wallington, SM6 ODZ - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): Choir<br>7. Genre: Choral<br>8. Age: 8 - 13<br>9. Level: Any (with additional learning needs)<br>10. Instruments: Singing<br>11. Other Tags: SEND<br>12. Cost: £84.50 per term (discounts for siblings/multiple ensembles)<br>13. About Opportunity: Sutton Supernova Singers is a fully inclusive, unauditioned choir for singers with all additional learning needs (e.g. ASD, ADHD, Speech & Language, Global Developmental Delay, etc.) aged 8-13. Sessions are carried out in a supportive environment that has been adapted to the differing needs of the children and young people attending.<br><br>Break out rooms are available, as well as fidget toys and visual cues. Parents are invited to attend rehearsals with their singer. The choir rehearse weekly (term-time only) and enjoy small end of term performances to friends and family. No previous experience is necessary, and you do not need to be able to read music to join our choir! <br><br>“I like that all autistic people can be involved. There is a special fundamental need for Supernova Singers. I like that the sessions are not too overstimulating or tiring for me.” <br>14. When: Tuesdays 17:15 - 18:15<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://suttonmusictrust.org.uk/singing/sutton-supernova-singers/<br>16. Organisation Name: Sutton Music Trust<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: <br>19. Only for London/Local?: London & Local Only<br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
