      <Placemark>
        <name>New Young Voices Collective (New YVC)</name>
        <address>Spotlight Youth Centre, Langdon Park - UK</address>
        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: London<br>3. County: Greater London<br>4. Location: Spotlight Youth Centre, Langdon Park - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): Choir<br>7. Genre: Choral<br>8. Age: 11  - 19<br>9. Level: Any<br>10. Instruments: <br>11. Other Tags: Free, No Experience<br>12. Cost: Free<br>13. About Opportunity: New YVC is a free, non-auditioned, East London based youth choir, singing everything from music by pop giants and soul legends, through musicals and movie hits, to world and folk music and classical greats.<br><br>The collective is led by Naveen Arles, assisted by jazz icon Steve Lodder on piano and managed by Spitalfields Music. NewYVC is different from your average singing group and thanks to its commitment to learning, many members have gone on to lead groups of their own or take up amazing roles in the music industry.<br><br>Members will learn lots about music and musicianship, meet new people, and have the chance to perform throughout the year in exciting venues and special events, including with our partners.<br><br>For more information or if you have any questions, please contact newyvc@spitalfieldsmusic.org.uk.<br>14. When: Tuesdays, 17:00 - 19:00<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://thames.towerhamlets.gov.uk/get-involved/join-a-group<br>16. Organisation Name: THAMES: Tower Hamlets Arts + Music Education Service<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: <br>19. Only for London/Local?: Local Only<br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1801-9C27B0-labelson</styleUrl>
