      <Placemark>
        <name>Soundbox</name>
        <address><![CDATA[St.Paul's Way Trust School, Tower Hamlets - UK]]></address>
        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: London<br>3. County: Greater London<br>4. Location: St.Paul's Way Trust School, Tower Hamlets - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): SEND Inclusive Ensemble<br>7. Genre: Various<br>8. Age: 11 - 25<br>9. Level: Any<br>10. Instruments: <br>11. Other Tags: No Experience, Free<br>12. Cost: Free<br>13. About Opportunity: part of THAMES Saturday Music Centre, St Paul’s Way Trust School)<br>Soundbox is an all-ability inclusive music collective that brings together disabled and non-disabled musicians aged 11-25 to make and create music using a mix of traditional instruments, music technology and singing. We aim for sessions to be accessible, welcoming and engaging for all.<br><br>Soundbox takes place as part of the THAMES Saturday Music Centre (SMC) on five Saturday mornings per term at St Paul’s Way Trust School. It was originally set-up as a partnership with Drake Music, Spitalfields Music and London Symphony Orchestra. They continue to have a close relationship with the ensemble.<br><br>Participation is FREE.<br>14. When: Saturdays 10:30 - 13:00 (every 2 weeks, part of THAMES Saturday music centre)<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://thames.towerhamlets.gov.uk/get-involved/join-a-group<br>16. Organisation Name: THAMES: Tower Hamlets Arts + Music Education Service<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: <br>19. Only for London/Local?: Local Only<br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
