      <Placemark>
        <name><![CDATA[Tomorrow's Warriors: Frontline]]></name>
        <address>London - UK</address>
        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: London<br>3. County: Greater London<br>4. Location: London - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): Jazz Group<br>7. Genre: Jazz<br>8. Age: 11 - 25<br>9. Level: Invitation Only<br>10. Instruments: <br>11. Other Tags: Invitation Only<br>12. Cost: Free<br>13. About Opportunity: Tomorrow’s Warriors Frontline is a formidable 8-piece line-up of some of our finest young Warriors musicians, championing the role of women in jazz. Membership of the ensemble is by invitation only.<br><br>Frontline is one of Tomorrow’s Warriors’ flagship development groups under the tutelage and mentorship of Romarna Campbell and Dr Gary Crosby OBE.<br><br>With regular performance opportunities, Frontline’s powerful live show draws inspiration from the jazz greats and blends a contemporary vibe with elements of jazz-fusion, funk, and R&B. Featuring a mix of jazz standards and their own compositions, Frontline channels the influences of Hank Mobley, Esperanza Spalding, Thelonious Monk, Wayne Shorter, Nérija and many more.<br><br>Get in touch for bookings and/or further information.<br>14. When: <br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://tomorrowswarriors.org/tw-frontline/<br>16. Organisation Name: Tomorrow's Warriors<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: <br>19. Only for London/Local?: <br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1801-9C27B0-labelson</styleUrl>
