          <Data name="13. About Opportunity">
            <value/>
          </Data>
          <Data name="14. When">
            <value>Many of our young musicians aged 11-15 begin their journey into jazz as a member of our  Junior Warriors. Whilst all our Junior members will have opportunities to participate in public performances at various points throughout the year, those with more advanced skills may be invited to join our Junior Band.

As a member of our Junior Band, young musicians have an opportunity to work more intensively within a small ensemble, developing ensemble/soloing/band leading skills mentored by a professional jazz musician in our artistic team. Band members also have additional performance opportunities, for example in the Imagine Children’s Festival at Southbank Centre, in the Music For Youth Festival, and in a variety of community arts and music festivals.

Our Junior Band never fails to wow audiences with their confidence, skill and passion for jazz music. And, as these budding stars progress, they may be invited to join our Youth Warriors Development Group, one of our Youth Ensembles, and possibly the Tomorrow’s Warriors Youth Orchestra.</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="15. Opportunity Website / Signup">
            <value>https://tomorrowswarriors.org/bands/tw-junior-band/</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="16. Organisation Name">
            <value><![CDATA[Tomorrow's Warriors]]></value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="17. About Organisation">
            <value/>
          </Data>
          <Data name="18. Organisation Website">
            <value/>
          </Data>
          <Data name="19. Only for London/Local?">
            <value/>
          </Data>
          <Data name="20. Extra Notes">
            <value/>
          </Data>
        </ExtendedData>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name><![CDATA[Tomorrow's Warriors: Small Ensembles]]></name>
        <address>London - UK</address>
        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: London<br>3. County: Greater London<br>4. Location: London - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): Jazz Group<br>7. Genre: Jazz<br>8. Age: 11 - 25<br>9. Level: On Application Basis<br>10. Instruments: <br>11. Other Tags: Free<br>12. Cost: Free<br>13. About Opportunity: Each of our cohorts reveals a new generation of rising stars. This is what makes Tomorrow’s Warriors so exciting!<br><br>Over the course of your participation in our programmes, and as part of your progression, you may be invited with other members to form one of our core TW ensembles or to join one of our existing bands.<br><br>Since inception, we have been proud and privileged to have brought together some of the most fantastic young musicians in the UK, helping them to develop, launch and establish award-winning ensembles.<br><br>Our support in the infancy stage of their careers has helped fast-track the careers of some notable artists and bands – Gary Crosby’s Nu Troop, J-Life, Denys Baptiste Quartet, Robert Mitchell’s Panacea, Soweto Kinch Quartet, Andrew McCormack Trio, Abram Wilson Sextet, Empirical, Rhythmica and, more recently, Ezra and Nérija to name just a few! – all of whom have brought diversity and richness to our cultural life in the UK and, in many cases, the international jazz scene.<br>14. When: <br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://tomorrowswarriors.org/bands/tw-small-ensembles/<br>16. Organisation Name: Tomorrow's Warriors<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: <br>19. Only for London/Local?: <br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
