            <value>Free</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="13. About Opportunity">
            <value>Each of our cohorts reveals a new generation of rising stars. This is what makes Tomorrow’s Warriors so exciting!

Over the course of your participation in our programmes, and as part of your progression, you may be invited with other members to form one of our core TW ensembles or to join one of our existing bands.

Since inception, we have been proud and privileged to have brought together some of the most fantastic young musicians in the UK, helping them to develop, launch and establish award-winning ensembles.

Our support in the infancy stage of their careers has helped fast-track the careers of some notable artists and bands – Gary Crosby’s Nu Troop, J-Life, Denys Baptiste Quartet, Robert Mitchell’s Panacea, Soweto Kinch Quartet, Andrew McCormack Trio, Abram Wilson Sextet, Empirical, Rhythmica and, more recently, Ezra and Nérija to name just a few! – all of whom have brought diversity and richness to our cultural life in the UK and, in many cases, the international jazz scene.</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="14. When">
            <value/>
          </Data>
