        <name>Mini Musicians Baby and Toddler</name>
        <address>The Community Hub, E17 9LN - UK</address>
        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: London<br>3. County: Greater London<br>4. Location: The Community Hub, E17 9LN - UK<br>5. Type: Workshop<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): <br>7. Genre: Early Years<br>8. Age: 0 - 4 years<br>9. Level: any<br>10. Instruments: <br>11. Other Tags: Early Years<br>12. Cost: £75 - £95 per term<br>13. About Opportunity: Our music courses for babies and toddlers are a fun way for parents and children to connect and explore music together.<br><br>Taught by professional musicians and Early Years Music Specialists our progressive curriculum uses a variety of musical activities to lay a foundation for future musicality and to helping children to feel more secure and confident when coping with new experiences.<br><br>Singing and movement are always at the heart of every session. As repetition is very important to children at this stage, the classes have a familiar framework each week but will always include some new challenge. Daily routines such as nappy changing, bath time, meal times, waking, sleeping and even tidying up toys are more enjoyable if done through singing or playing musical instruments and dancing.<br>14. When: Fridays 10:45 - 11:30<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://www.wfmusichub.org/groups/explore/mini-musicians-baby-and-toddler<br>16. Organisation Name: Waltham Forest Music Hub<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: <br>19. Only for London/Local?: Local Only<br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1637-FFD600-labelson</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
