        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: London<br>3. County: Greater London<br>4. Location: Walthamstow School for Girls - UK<br>5. Type: Workshop<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): <br>7. Genre: Production/Mixing<br>8. Age: 11 - 16<br>9. Level: Any Level<br>10. Instruments: <br>11. Other Tags: No Experience<br>12. Cost: The fee for this group is separate to Music School Membership. Sign up at the link below.<br>13. About Opportunity: This is open to any young person who is secondary aged and is interested in learning to produce their own music.<br><br>An music tech course for aspiring young producers, composers, song-writers, and MCs interested in creating their own beats and tracks.<br><br>Try your hand at working with a range of music production software (YuStudio, Logic, Ableton), experiment with electronic instruments or try recording vocals or live instruments using studio quality microphones.<br><br>How do I Join?<br>This group is part of the Music School - please sign up for Music School Groups and Ensembles and select 'Beats and Bass' as the group you'd like to join.<br>14. When: Tuesdays 16:30 - 17:30<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://www.wfmusichub.org/groups/explore/youth-chamber-orchestra<br>16. Organisation Name: Waltham Forest Music Hub<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: <br>19. Only for London/Local?: Local Only<br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
