        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: London<br>3. County: Greater London<br>4. Location: Walthamstow School for Girls - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): Mixed Ensemble<br>7. Genre: Orchestral<br>8. Age: <br>9. Level: Beginners to Grade 2<br>10. Instruments: <br>11. Other Tags: Grade 1, Grade 2, Preparatory<br>12. Cost: Free (with music school membership)<br>13. About Opportunity: Our beginner mixed ensemble is for children learning any instrument to come and play music together and develop performance skills in a relaxed and friendly environment. We play music in a range of styles and welcome students ideas. Young musicians who can play a few notes up to Grade 2 level are invited to join. The group is open to beginners who can confidently use three fingers to players at Grade 3 standard.<br><br>How do I Join?<br>This group is part of the Music School - please sign up for Music School Groups and Ensembles and select 'Beginner Mixed Ensemble' as the group you'd like to join.<br>14. When: Saturdays 9:00 - 9:45<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://www.wfmusichub.org/groups/explore/beginner-mixed-ensemble<br>16. Organisation Name: Waltham Forest Music Hub<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: <br>19. Only for London/Local?: Local Only<br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
