        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: London<br>3. County: Greater London<br>4. Location: Walthamstow School for Girls - UK<br>5. Type: Workshop<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): <br>7. Genre: Songwriting<br>8. Age: 11 - 16<br>9. Level: Any Level<br>10. Instruments: <br>11. Other Tags: No Experience<br>12. Cost: The fee for this group is separate to Music School Membership. Sign up at the link below.<br>13. About Opportunity: This is open to any young person who is secondary aged and is interested in writing their own songs.<br><br>From structure and tonality to genre and instrumentation, this course covers a whole range of skills that will be useful to any young person interested in creating their own music, particularly for GCSE composition.<br><br>All students need to bring along is themselves, any material they’ve written or started to write (don’t worry if they haven’t got any!) and an instrument (if portable).<br><br>How do I Join?<br>This group is part of the Music School - please sign up for Music School Groups and Ensembles and select 'Songwriter's Circle' as the group you'd like to join.<br>14. When: Mondays 16:00 - 17:00<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://www.wfmusichub.org/groups/explore/songwriters-circle<br>16. Organisation Name: Waltham Forest Music Hub<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: <br>19. Only for London/Local?: Local Only<br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
