        <address>Walthamstow School for Girls - UK</address>
        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: London<br>3. County: Greater London<br>4. Location: Walthamstow School for Girls - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): String Ensemble<br>7. Genre: Orchestral<br>8. Age: <br>9. Level: Beginners to Grade 3<br>10. Instruments: <br>11. Other Tags: Grade 1, Grade 2, Preparatory, Grade 3<br>12. Cost: Free (with music school membership)<br>13. About Opportunity: The Strings Group is an ensemble for violin, viola, cello and double bass players. The rehearsals are varied and involve a mixture of working from sheet music, using improvisation and various musical tools to enhance the experience of learning. The group is open to beginners who can confidently use three fingers to players at Grade 3 standard.<br><br>How do I Join?<br>This group is part of the Music School - please sign up for Music School Groups and Ensembles and select 'Strings Group' as the group you'd like to join.<br>14. When: Wednesdays 17:30 - 18:30<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://www.wfmusichub.org/groups/explore/strings-group<br>16. Organisation Name: Waltham Forest Music Hub<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: <br>19. Only for London/Local?: Local Only<br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
