        <address>Walthamstow School for Girls - UK</address>
        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: London<br>3. County: Greater London<br>4. Location: Walthamstow School for Girls - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): Orchestra<br>7. Genre: Orchestral<br>8. Age: <br>9. Level: Grade 4+<br>10. Instruments: <br>11. Other Tags: Grade 4, Grade 5, Grade 6, Grade 7, Grade 8<br>12. Cost: The fee for this group is separate to Music School Membership. Sign up at the link below.<br>13. About Opportunity: The Youth Chamber Orchestra is one of our most advanced groups, aimed at string, woodwind, brass and percussion players Grade 4 and above. It covers core classical repertoire from Beethoven to Mozart and performs at various venues around the borough. It is a great opportunity for young musicians to develop their ensemble skills to a high level and share their love of music with like-minded instrumentalists.<br><br>How do I Join?<br>This group is part of the Music School - please sign up for Music School Groups and Ensembles and select 'Youth Chamber Orchestra' as the group you'd like to join.<br>14. When: Wednesdays 18:30 - 20:00<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://www.wfmusichub.org/groups/explore/youth-chamber-orchestra<br>16. Organisation Name: Waltham Forest Music Hub<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: <br>19. Only for London/Local?: Local Only<br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
