        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: London<br>3. County: Greater London<br>4. Location: Burntwood School, Wandsworth - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): Orchestra<br>7. Genre: Orchestral<br>8. Age: <br>9. Level: Grade 3 - 6<br>10. Instruments: <br>11. Other Tags: Grade 3, Grade 4, Grade 5, Grade 6<br>12. Cost: <br>13. About Opportunity: WCO is a full symphony orchestra for intermediate orchestral musicians and the feeder ensemble to the Wandsworth Philharmonic Orchestra.<br><br>The Orchestra performs a varied and challenging range of repertoire. Performance opportunities include concerts at Fairfield Halls, Croydon and the Clore Ballroom at the Southbank Centre.<br><br>WCO is open to young musicians playing brass, wind, string and percussion instruments at approximately Grade 3 to Grade 6 standard.<br><br>WCO rehearse on Saturdays, 12.30pm-1.30pm. There are also 3 days of intensive sectional coaching during the Autumn and Spring Half Term holidays.<br>14. When: Saturdays 12:30 - 13:30<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://wandsworthmusic.co.uk/music-academy/ensembles/<br>16. Organisation Name: Wandsworth Music <br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: <br>19. Only for London/Local?: London & Local Only<br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
