            <value>WCO is a full symphony orchestra for intermediate orchestral musicians and the feeder ensemble to the Wandsworth Philharmonic Orchestra.

The Orchestra performs a varied and challenging range of repertoire. Performance opportunities include concerts at Fairfield Halls, Croydon and the Clore Ballroom at the Southbank Centre.

WCO is open to young musicians playing brass, wind, string and percussion instruments at approximately Grade 3 to Grade 6 standard.

WCO rehearse on Saturdays, 12.30pm-1.30pm. There are also 3 days of intensive sectional coaching during the Autumn and Spring Half Term holidays.</value>
