          <Data name="13. About Opportunity">
            <value>In The Mix is a recurring, bimonthly programme marrying personalised feedback, industry level insights, and professional guidance. The intention of the programme is for young creatives to air their projects in a critical and empathetic space, receiving feedback which enables them to develop those projects to the point of completion. Following the programme, participants can continue to receive support from Raw Material through accessing our own fully-equipped music studio along with a professional sound engineer.

To participate, you need to sign up below and send your creative project in advance to programmes@rawmusicmedia.org.</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="14. When">
            <value>Bi-monthly Wednesdays 18:00 - 20:30 (check website for details on next session)</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="15. Opportunity Website / Signup">
            <value>https://rawmusicmedia.org/programmes/creative-communities-creating-change</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="16. Organisation Name">
            <value>RawMaterial</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="17. About Organisation">
            <value/>
          </Data>
          <Data name="18. Organisation Website">
            <value>https://rawmusicmedia.org</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="19. Only for London/Local?">
            <value>Unknown</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="20. Extra Notes">
            <value>In The Mix is open to creatives of all disciplines (visual artists, rappers, producers, musicians, poets, writers, etc.). 
The programme is for works-in-progress. We would like participants to come to In The Mix with a willingness to incorporate the feedback they receive into their finished projects. It will be possible to share completed projects that were brought to In The Mix at our termly Listening Events. 
To present your work, please bring the file on a USB storage device. 
It’s important to ensure that the file is compatible with Apple devices.

</value>
          </Data>
        </ExtendedData>
