        <name>Hampshire County Youth Orchestra</name>
        <address>Thornden Hall, Winchester Road, Chandlers Ford - UK</address>
        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South East<br>3. County: Hampshire<br>4. Location: Thornden Hall, Winchester Road, Chandlers Ford - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): Orchestra<br>7. Genre: Orchestral<br>8. Age: Up to 19 years in full time education<br>9. Level: At/close to Grade 7+ (yearly annual audition)<br>10. Instruments: Piccolo/Flute, Clarinet, Oboe, Cor Anglais, Bassoon, Trumpet, Trombone, Tuba, Horns, Harp, Violin, Viola, Cello, Double Bass, Percussion, Euphonium, Drum Kit<br>11. Other Tags: Audition<br>12. Cost: £75 - £125 per Term<br>13. About Opportunity: Join a great team of enthusiastic young musicians to enjoy making music of the highest standard with like-minded people. Membership is by audition only and open to anyone in full time education in Hampshire. Auditions will take place in early July so please apply now! We are in particular looking for Bassoons, Clarinets, Trumpets, Double Bass and Percussionists, but welcome all new applicants.  The deadline for applications is normally in June, but please contact us if you have missed the deadline and we will see what we can do. Places in the Hampshire County Youth Orchestra are limited and we do advise candidates to apply before the deadline. <br>14. When: Saturdays 10:30 - 15:30 (every 2 weeks)<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://hcyo.hmsensembles.org.uk/<br>16. Organisation Name: Hampshire Music Service<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: <br>19. Only for London/Local?: Local Only<br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1801-9C27B0-labelson</styleUrl>
