        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South East<br>3. County: Hampshire<br>4. Location: Fairfield Infant School, Havant - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): Wind Band<br>7. Genre: Orchestral<br>8. Age: <br>9. Level: Grade 4+<br>10. Instruments: Piccolo/Flute, Clarinet, Oboe, Cor Anglais, Bassoon, Trumpet, Trombone, Tuba, Horns, Percussion, Euphonium, Recorder<br>11. Other Tags: Free, Grade 4, Grade 5, Grade 6, Grade 7, Grade 8<br>12. Cost: Free (voluntary contribution)<br>13. About Opportunity: New players are welcome all year round, or just come along to have a try before committing to signing up.<br>Rehearsal Details<br><br>Day: Saturday (term time only)<br><br>Time: 9:30am<br><br>Venue: Fairfield Infant School<br><br>Grade: 4 +<br><br>Music is selected from a wide range of musical genres to suit players of approximately Grade 4 and upwards. Designed to provide a balance of challenge and support for all players, adaptations can be made to parts where needed, with personalised guidance and encouragement offered by our experienced directors.<br><br>Director: Steve Tanner and Lara Jelliff<br><br>Price: FREE - Voluntary contributions are welcome<br>14. When: Saturdays (Term Time), 09:30<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://www.portsmouthmusichub.org/ocean-wind<br>16. Organisation Name: Portsmouth Music Hub<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: www.portsmouthmusichub.org<br>19. Only for London/Local?: Local Only<br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
