            <value>Free </value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="13. About Opportunity">
            <value><![CDATA[SIOW Music is delighted to be partnering with The Stage Door and Golden Groove Productions to create a unique opportunity for young (under 18) musicians in the city to take part in a monthly open mic night!

Our sessions this year are:
Tuesday 14th October 2025
Tuesday 4th November 2025
Tuesday 6th January 2026
Tuesday 3rd February 2026
Tuesday 3rd March 2026
Tuesday 14th April 2026
Tuesday 5th May 2026
Tuesday 2nd June 2026
Tuesday 7th July 2026


Please make sure you book tickets through Stage Door's website before each session (please note, these can be free, or you can make a donation to ensure that these fantastic events can continue!) : https://thestagedoor.org.uk/

Each month we will send you a form to sign up, which will include a space to put which songs your young person would like to perform and links to any backing tracks.

Each night will feature local professional musicians as the house band or artist who will host each night and support young musicians with their performance techniques.  We will provide all the technical requirements and backline (instruments) that you might need to perform - just let us know in the notes below what you need.

The sessions will run from 6 - 9pm upstairs in The Stage Door and parents, friends and family are very welcome to attend and support you.

Please note that anyone in school year 11 or below will need to be chaperoned either by a parent/guardian or by a teacher if attending with a school group.  The Stage Door and Southampton Music Hub will not be responsible for the safeguarding of those taking part]]></value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="14. When">
            <value>Tuesdays throughout 2025/2026</value>
