      <Placemark>
        <name>Folk Active Youth Ensemble</name>
        <address>cantell School, Southampton - UK</address>
        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South East<br>3. County: Hampshire<br>4. Location: cantell School, Southampton - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): Folk Ensemble<br>7. Genre: Folk<br>8. Age: 11 - 19 (acoustic instruments)<br>9. Level: Confidence to hold tune without sheet music<br>10. Instruments: <br>11. Other Tags: <br>12. Cost: £156 per year<br>13. About Opportunity: The FolkActive Youth Ensemble (FAYE) is open to musicians aged 11-19 who want to develop their folk music skills in a welcoming and inclusive environment. You’ll receive expert tuition and grow as a musician while having fun, learning to improvise harmonies, compose tunes, and play by ear. You’ll explore folk techniques, including common modes and tune types, enhance your instrumental technique and musicianship, and gain skills in arranging music and performing with confidence.<br><br>It’s also a chance to make friends and connect with like-minded people! The ensemble offers plenty of social opportunities to build relationships.<br><br>You’ll need your own acoustic instrument and the confidence to hold a tune or musical idea without sheet music.<br><br>The ensemble is led by Chris Nichols, educator and founder of the folk band Threepenny Bit.<br>14. When: Sundays 10:00 - 12:00<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://www.folkactive.org.uk/education/youth-ensemble/<br>16. Organisation Name: SIOW Music<br>17. About Organisation: The new home for Southampton Music Hub, IOW Music Hub and Southampton Music Services<br><br>Empowering children and young people to make, learn and love music<br>18. Organisation Website: https://www.siowmusic.org<br>19. Only for London/Local?: <br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1801-9C27B0-labelson</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="2. Region">
            <value>South East</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="3. County">
