        <name>Music Mentoring (Isle of Wight)</name>
        <address>The Department, Ryde - UK</address>
        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South East<br>3. County: Isle of Wight<br>4. Location: The Department, Ryde - UK<br>5. Type: Mentoring<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): <br>7. Genre: Professional Development<br>8. Age: 11 - 18<br>9. Level: All abilities<br>10. Instruments: Songwriting, Producing, Rap, Singing, All<br>11. Other Tags: Free<br>12. Cost: Free<br>13. About Opportunity: Mentoring sessions are part of our affordable music tuition offer, but we also work with education settings, charities and organisations who support young people to offer free sessions. <br>If you work with young people who may face barriers to accessing music, get in touch to request a Priority Access Code.<br><br>About the sessions:<br>Music Mentoring Sessions are run by Southampton and Isle of Wight Music, a partnership of organisations, which are led by Southampton City Council. Sessions are available in both Southampton and Isle of Wight, at:<br>Southampton — Mayflower Studios, City Centre<br>IOW — The Department, Ryde<br>These sessions are for young people aged 11–18 who want help to create and release music. We welcome singers, rappers, songwriters, producers and other musicians!<br>With music mentoring, you will get to work with a music expert to craft beats, write lyrics and produce tracks, as well as getting support to release and promote your own music!<br>It doesn’t matter if you’re just starting out, not sure where to go next or have big ambitions - our team are here to help!<br>14. When: individual appointments<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://www.siowmusic.org/music-mentoring<br>16. Organisation Name: SIOW Music<br>17. About Organisation: The new home for Southampton Music Hub, IOW Music Hub and Southampton Music Services<br><br>Empowering children and young people to make, learn and love music<br>18. Organisation Website: https://www.siowmusic.org<br>19. Only for London/Local?: <br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
