        <name>Oxfordshire County Youth Choir</name>
        <address>Centre for Music, Bayswater Road, Headington - UK</address>
        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South East<br>3. County: Oxfordshire<br>4. Location: Centre for Music, Bayswater Road, Headington - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): Choir<br>7. Genre: Choral<br>8. Age: Year 7 - 13<br>9. Level: no experience, reading music would help<br>10. Instruments: Singing<br>11. Other Tags: <br>12. Cost: £8.20 per session<br>13. About Opportunity: We invite all young people who love singing to join Oxfordshire’s County Youth Choir. We are open to both boys and girls and cater for soprano, alto, tenor and bass voice parts. No audition is necessary, but being able to read music would be a distinct advantage.<br><br>Oxfordshire County Youth Choir enjoys singing in a variety of styles and aims to perform at the end of each term. There are also opportunities to sing with some of the county’s instrumental ensembles.<br><br>Come along on a Thursday and see if you like it!<br>14. When: Thursdays 18:30 - 20:00<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://www.oxfordshire.gov.uk/residents/music-service/music-groups/choirs-and-performing-arts/oxfordshire-county-youth-choir<br>16. Organisation Name: Oxfordshire Music Service<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: https://www.oxfordshire.gov.uk/residents/music-service<br>19. Only for London/Local?: <br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
