      <Placemark>
        <name>Oxfordshire Inclusive Choir</name>
        <address>Centre for Music, Bayswater Road, Headington - UK</address>
        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South East<br>3. County: Oxfordshire<br>4. Location: Centre for Music, Bayswater Road, Headington - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): Choir<br>7. Genre: Choral<br>8. Age: Under 25<br>9. Level: all abilities<br>10. Instruments: Singing<br>11. Other Tags: SEND, Free<br>12. Cost: Free<br>13. About Opportunity: The Oxfordshire Inclusive Choir welcomes people aged 25 years and under, and their families/carers. It is administered by Oxfordshire County Music Service and supported by Soundabout.<br><br>By welcoming all voices we aim to be as inclusive as possible, and actively try to remove barriers to participation from those with severe and profound learning disabilities.<br><br>There are no auditions, and you do not need to be able to read music notation.<br>14. When: Thursdays at 5pm for one hour online, fortnightly, with termly face-to-face/hybrid sessions at The Centre for Music.<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://www.oxfordshire.gov.uk/residents/music-service/music-groups/choirs-and-performing-arts/oxfordshire-inclusive-choir<br>16. Organisation Name: Oxfordshire Music Service<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: https://www.oxfordshire.gov.uk/residents/music-service<br>19. Only for London/Local?: <br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
