          <Data name="13. About Opportunity">
            <value>The Oxfordshire Inclusive Choir welcomes people aged 25 years and under, and their families/carers. It is administered by Oxfordshire County Music Service and supported by Soundabout.

By welcoming all voices we aim to be as inclusive as possible, and actively try to remove barriers to participation from those with severe and profound learning disabilities.

There are no auditions, and you do not need to be able to read music notation.</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="14. When">
            <value>Thursdays at 5pm for one hour online, fortnightly, with termly face-to-face/hybrid sessions at The Centre for Music.</value>
