      <Placemark>
        <name>Oxfordshire Youth Folk Group</name>
        <address>Centre for Music, Bayswater Road, Headington - UK</address>
        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South East<br>3. County: Oxfordshire<br>4. Location: Centre for Music, Bayswater Road, Headington - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): Folk Ensemble<br>7. Genre: Folk<br>8. Age: year 6 - 11<br>9. Level: Baseline ability level: able to play simple melodies, chords or rhythms on chosen instrument or voice.  Intermediate and advanced players are also welcome.<br>10. Instruments: All<br>11. Other Tags: <br>12. Cost: £17.50 per session<br>13. About Opportunity: This is a new ensemble for young musicians who are interested in learning folk tunes and songs. We will learn the tunes and songs together by ear and then explore ways to arrange them to create something new and exciting.<br>14. When: Saturdays 13:45 - 15:45<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://www.oxfordshire.gov.uk/residents/music-service/music-groups/oxfordshire-youth-folk-group<br>16. Organisation Name: Oxfordshire Music Service<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: https://www.oxfordshire.gov.uk/residents/music-service<br>19. Only for London/Local?: <br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
