          <Data name="13. About Opportunity">
            <value>An exciting and creative two-day songwriting and band skills workshop for children aged 8-18.

Sessions include:

song-writing
band rehearsals
live sound
sound checking
The workshops are led by professional players and teachers.

You do not have to be a member of an existing band to attend this workshop, however we also welcome established bands.

</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="14. When">
            <value>various dates (2 day period), 9:30 - 15:30 both days
check website for next available workshop</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="15. Opportunity Website / Signup">
            <value>https://www.oxfordshire.gov.uk/residents/music-service/music-groups/rock-and-pop-workshops</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="16. Organisation Name">
            <value>Oxfordshire Music Service</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="17. About Organisation">
            <value/>
          </Data>
          <Data name="18. Organisation Website">
            <value>https://www.oxfordshire.gov.uk/residents/music-service</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="19. Only for London/Local?">
            <value/>
          </Data>
          <Data name="20. Extra Notes">
            <value>Everyone will need:

pencil
a little money for refreshments (including tuck shop)
packed lunch
All attendees are responsible for the electrical safety of their own equipment - please bring a circuit breaker to plug into. 

Drummers: You must bring your kit, sticks, brushes and a mat or piece of carpet to set up on (if you have one). 

Keyboard players: Your keyboard, power supply, and amplifier (if possible). 

Bassists and guitarists: Your guitar, guitar strap, amplifier, power cable, guitar cable (plus a spare if you have one), plectrums and an electronic tuner (if you have one). 

Singers: Your voice and a pad or notebook to write lyrics in. </value>
          </Data>
        </ExtendedData>
      </Placemark>
