        <name>Oxfordshire Youth Big Band I</name>
        <address>centre for Music, Bayswater Road, Headington - UK</address>
        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South East<br>3. County: Oxfordshire<br>4. Location: centre for Music, Bayswater Road, Headington - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): Jazz Band<br>7. Genre: Jazz<br>8. Age: up to 18<br>9. Level: Grade 7-8<br>10. Instruments: Trumpet, Trombone, Piano/Keys, Guitar, Bass Guitar, Saxophone<br>11. Other Tags: <br>12. Cost: £11 per session<br>13. About Opportunity: <br>There are four Oxfordshire Youth Big Bands:<br><br>OYBB III - grades 3 - 5 approx<br>OYBB II - grades 5 - 6 approx<br>OYBB I - grades 7 - 8 approx<br>OYJC - grade 8+<br>Our aim is to enthuse and encourage students to play jazz and improvise at all levels. The foundations for this are laid in OYBB III, where students learn the skills to play in a big band and the basics of improvisation. As they move up through the bands, students will play in a wide variety of styles from Ellington to Steely Dan, develop their improvising skills, and take part in regular performances.<br>14. When: Tuesdays 19:00 - 21:00<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://www.oxfordshire.gov.uk/residents/music-service/music-groups/youth-big-bands-and-oyjc<br>16. Organisation Name: Oxfordshire Music Service<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: https://www.oxfordshire.gov.uk/residents/music-service<br>19. Only for London/Local?: <br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
