          <Data name="13. About Opportunity">
            <value>
There are four Oxfordshire Youth Big Bands:

OYBB III - grades 3 - 5 approx
OYBB II - grades 5 - 6 approx
OYBB I - grades 7 - 8 approx
OYJC - grade 8+
Our aim is to enthuse and encourage students to play jazz and improvise at all levels. The foundations for this are laid in OYBB III, where students learn the skills to play in a big band and the basics of improvisation. As they move up through the bands, students will play in a wide variety of styles from Ellington to Steely Dan, develop their improvising skills, and take part in regular performances.</value>
