        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South West<br>3. County: Somerset<br>4. Location: Wellington School. Somerset - UK<br>5. Type: Workshop<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): <br>7. Genre: Classical<br>8. Age: Year 7 - 9<br>9. Level: Beginners<br>10. Instruments: Piccolo/Flute, Clarinet, Oboe, Cor Anglais, Bassoon, Trumpet, Trombone, Tuba, Horns, Harp, Violin, Viola, Cello, Double Bass, Percussion, Piano/Keys, Singing, Euphonium, Saxophone, Recorder<br>11. Other Tags: <br>12. Cost: Enquire for more info<br>13. About Opportunity: Designed for musicians in Key Stage 3 (school years 7–9), our Developing Programme offers a dynamic and immersive musical experience. The programme includes three one-day weekend workshops.<br><br>Each of our students will be placed within one of our two specialist groups:<br>🎻 Classical Group – for musicians playing piano, voice, and orchestral instruments.<br>🎸 Contemporary Group – for those playing electric guitar, bass guitar, drums, saxophone, keys, and vocals.<br><br>Each session provides a collaborative space where students can learn, explore, and create music alongside like-minded peers. While part of a structured programme, each workshop is designed as a standalone experience, allowing students to attend as many sessions as they wish.<br><br>Sessions take place in the well-equipped music department at Wellington School, led by highly experienced and professional music tutors.<br><br>Find out more about our tutors below:<br>14. When: Enquire for more info<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://swms.org.uk/developing-programme/<br>16. Organisation Name: South West Music School<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: https://swms.org.uk/<br>19. Only for London/Local?: <br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
