          <Data name="13. About Opportunity">
            <value><![CDATA[Students on our Advancing Programme are expected to be working to a minimum standard of Grade 5.
We recognise that not all students sit exams, so we assess ability level through audition videos.

Our Advancing Programme activities include:

1 intensive residential course (collaborative, cross-genre), full board inc.
2 orchestral workshop days
3 specialist classical tuition school workshops inc. 1-2-1 mentoring
Termly tuition budget (grant-holding students only)
Exam costs and music accessories budget (grant-holding students only)
Consultancy mentoring sessions
We can also offer access to:

Trinity Laban A level Music Distance Learning*
Music production support & workshops
Composition and songwriting support
Additional projects (e.g. Piano Concerto project, conducting ‘Podium’ project, Elizabethan Ensemble workshop)
We are happy to discuss a bespoke programme of support to suit your available budget.

For further information about our mentoring, tuition school workshops, music production and songwriting activities, please scroll down.

* South West Music School work in collaboration with Trinity Laban to offer the opportunity to study A level music on a distance learning basis. For information about the A level music course, please contact us:

]]></value>
