        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South West<br>3. County: Somerset<br>4. Location: Wellington School. Somerset - UK<br>5. Type: Workshop<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): <br>7. Genre: Rock<br>8. Age: 8 - 19<br>9. Level: Expected to be working minimum grade 5<br>10. Instruments: Composing, Songwriting<br>11. Other Tags: Grade 5, Grade 6, Grade 7, Grade 8, Audition<br>12. Cost: Enquire for more info<br>13. About Opportunity: Students on our Advancing Programme are expected to be working to a minimum standard of Grade 5.<br>We recognise that not all students sit exams, so we assess ability level through audition videos.<br><br>Our Advancing Programme activities include:<br><br>1 intensive residential course (collaborative, cross-genre), full board inc.<br>2 orchestral workshop days<br>3 specialist classical tuition school workshops inc. 1-2-1 mentoring<br>Termly tuition budget (grant-holding students only)<br>Exam costs and music accessories budget (grant-holding students only)<br>Consultancy mentoring sessions<br>We can also offer access to:<br><br>Trinity Laban A level Music Distance Learning*<br>Music production support & workshops<br>Composition and songwriting support<br>Additional projects (e.g. Piano Concerto project, conducting ‘Podium’ project, Elizabethan Ensemble workshop)<br>We are happy to discuss a bespoke programme of support to suit your available budget.<br><br>For further information about our mentoring, tuition school workshops, music production and songwriting activities, please scroll down.<br><br>* South West Music School work in collaboration with Trinity Laban to offer the opportunity to study A level music on a distance learning basis. For information about the A level music course, please contact us:<br><br><br>14. When: Enquire for more info<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://swms.org.uk/advancing-programme/<br>16. Organisation Name: South West Music School<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: https://swms.org.uk/<br>19. Only for London/Local?: <br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
