        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South East<br>3. County: Surrey<br>4. Location: Farnham Music and Drama, Tilford Road - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): Choir<br>7. Genre: Choral<br>8. Age: 11 - 18<br>9. Level: All Abilities<br>10. Instruments: Singing<br>11. Other Tags: <br>12. Cost: <br>13. About Opportunity: The FMD Medleys and Mashups is an all inclusive vocal group for students aged 11-18 years (school years 7-13). They sing a variety of medleys and mashups from musical theatre to pop with the odd classical piece too.<br><br>The emphasis will be to have fun and develop as an ensemble. Don’t worry if you have never sung before, this group is about growing in confidence together! The students will sing in parts and work on harmony, with the opportunity for those who want to sing solos.<br><br>We will take part in FMD concerts as well as going on our annual European tours.<br>14. When: Tuesday 17:10<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://www.farnhammusicanddrama.com/medleys-and-mashups/<br>16. Organisation Name: Farnham Music and Drama (FMD)<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: <br>19. Only for London/Local?: No Restriction<br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
