        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: National (UK Wide)<br>3. County: UK Wide<br>4. Location:  - UK<br>5. Type: Grant/Fund<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): <br>7. Genre: Other<br>8. Age: Under 18<br>9. Level: Auditioned<br>10. Instruments: All<br>11. Other Tags: Audition<br>12. Cost: Free<br>13. About Opportunity: In order to be eligible for support, musicians must:<br>• Be under 18 years old on 1st September 2025<br>• Have been permanently resident in the UK for a minimum of 3 years<br>• Provide evidence of combined household income under £37,500 per annum.<br>Applicants must also provide details of household income totalling no more than £37,500 per<br>annum. We understand that there may be mitigating factors as to why household income may be<br>over this amount, and so we will consider applications with a higher income due to extenuating<br>circumstances. These could include increased income due to Disability Living Allowance (DLA) or<br>Personal Independence Payments (PIP). If you are unsure if your circumstance might be included<br>in this, please get in touch and one of our Relationship Managers will advise you.<br>Shortlisted applicants must provide evidence of household income figures. Applications not<br>providing evidence will not be considered.<br>14. When: -<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://www.futuretalent.org/join/programme<br>16. Organisation Name: Future Talent<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: <br>19. Only for London/Local?: No Restriction<br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
