          <Data name="13. About Opportunity">
            <value>In order to be eligible for support, musicians must:
• Be under 18 years old on 1st September 2025
• Have been permanently resident in the UK for a minimum of 3 years
• Provide evidence of combined household income under £37,500 per annum.
Applicants must also provide details of household income totalling no more than £37,500 per
annum. We understand that there may be mitigating factors as to why household income may be
over this amount, and so we will consider applications with a higher income due to extenuating
circumstances. These could include increased income due to Disability Living Allowance (DLA) or
Personal Independence Payments (PIP). If you are unsure if your circumstance might be included
in this, please get in touch and one of our Relationship Managers will advise you.
Shortlisted applicants must provide evidence of household income figures. Applications not
providing evidence will not be considered.</value>
          </Data>
