      <Placemark>
        <name>Help Musicians: Business Skills for Musicians</name>
        <address>- UK</address>
        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: National (UK Wide)<br>3. County: UK Wide<br>4. Location:  - UK<br>5. Type: Workshop<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): <br>7. Genre: Professional Development<br>8. Age: All<br>9. Level: Any level<br>10. Instruments: <br>11. Other Tags: Free, No Experience<br>12. Cost: Free<br>13. About Opportunity: Held ONLINE<br>If you’re a musician, there are lots of different aspects to your career that you must juggle — being your own social media manager, dealing with contracts and finances, project managing your releases and tours, and so much more. <br><br>Sometimes it’s difficult to know where to start, and that’s where our Business Skills workshops come in. These online sessions offer advice and guidance on a wide range of topics to help you manage the many different parts of being a musician with confidence. They are free to join, and led by experts who can give you the tools you need to build a sustainable career in music. <br><br>Upcoming sessions will appear below. <br>14. When: Multiple - see opportunity page for details<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://www.helpmusicians.org.uk/get-support/develop-as-a-musician/business-skills<br>16. Organisation Name: Help Musicians<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: <br>19. Only for London/Local?: No Restriction<br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1637-FFD600-labelson</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
