        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: National (UK Wide)<br>3. County: UK Wide<br>4. Location:  - UK<br>5. Type: Grant/Fund<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): <br>7. Genre: Professional Development<br>8. Age: 18+<br>9. Level: Be a working musician who has made at least 40% of your income from music over the past two years. Musicians with a long-term health condition and/​or disability that impacts their ability to work as a musician will just need to show some income from music within the past 2 years.<br>10. Instruments: Composing, Songwriting, DJ, Producing, Rap<br>11. Other Tags: Free, Music of Black Origin<br>12. Cost: Free<br>13. About Opportunity: MOBO Help Musicians Amplified is for musicians creating music of Black origin looking to take the next step in their career or expand their work. If you’re a producer, DJ or musician creating or performing music of Black origin without the resources to pursue a career-changing opportunity, then this support might be for you.<br><br>In partnership with the MOBO Trust, we have invested nearly £1 million into funding, mentoring, and hands-on support to date — helping musicians creating music of Black origin turn ambition into action. And we are just getting started.MOBO Help Musicians Amplified is a 12-month programme that enables you to connect with other musicians, access business advice, build out your industry networks and insights, and receive funding towards your own music.<br><br>Who is this support for? <br>This support is for musicians looking to take the next step or expand your career, those working with one or more of these genres:<br><br>Hip-Hop<br>Grime<br>Drill<br>R&B/Soul<br>African Music<br>Electronic/​Dance Music<br>Gospel<br>Jazz<br>Caribbean Music<br>Alternative Music<br>You might be a budding artist with the right momentum to release a debut EP, or an established producer wanting to build out your career by moving into live performance.<br><br>Full eligibility criteria and details of what our panel are looking for can be found on our FAQs and guidance page.<br><br>MOBO Help Musicians Amplified FAQs and application guidance<br>What does this award include? <br>Up to £3,000 that can be used to fund your own music<br>6 hours of 1−2−1 Business Advice from industry experts <br>Online meet ups with other awardees and industry guests, with expenses to attend a one-day peer and industry mixer event in London <br>Monthly online peer drop-in spaces with other musicians (optional)<br>Access to a healthy practice session delivered by BAPAM (optional)<br>14. When: Annual application windows - check opportunity page for more details<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://www.helpmusicians.org.uk/get-support/develop-as-a-musician/mobo-help-musicians-amplified<br>16. Organisation Name: Help Musicians<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: <br>19. Only for London/Local?: No Restriction<br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
