          <Data name="13. About Opportunity">
            <value><![CDATA[MOBO Help Musicians Amplified is for musicians creating music of Black origin looking to take the next step in their career or expand their work. If you’re a producer, DJ or musician creating or performing music of Black origin without the resources to pursue a career-changing opportunity, then this support might be for you.

In partnership with the MOBO Trust, we have invested nearly £1 million into funding, mentoring, and hands-on support to date — helping musicians creating music of Black origin turn ambition into action. And we are just getting started.MOBO Help Musicians Amplified is a 12-month programme that enables you to connect with other musicians, access business advice, build out your industry networks and insights, and receive funding towards your own music.

Who is this support for? 
This support is for musicians looking to take the next step or expand your career, those working with one or more of these genres:

Hip-Hop
Grime
Drill
R&B/Soul
African Music
Electronic/​Dance Music
Gospel
Jazz
Caribbean Music
Alternative Music
You might be a budding artist with the right momentum to release a debut EP, or an established producer wanting to build out your career by moving into live performance.

Full eligibility criteria and details of what our panel are looking for can be found on our FAQs and guidance page.

MOBO Help Musicians Amplified FAQs and application guidance
What does this award include? 
Up to £3,000 that can be used to fund your own music
6 hours of 1−2−1 Business Advice from industry experts 
Online meet ups with other awardees and industry guests, with expenses to attend a one-day peer and industry mixer event in London 
Monthly online peer drop-in spaces with other musicians (optional)
Access to a healthy practice session delivered by BAPAM (optional)]]></value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="14. When">
            <value>Annual application windows - check opportunity page for more details</value>
          </Data>
