        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: National (UK Wide)<br>3. County: UK Wide<br>4. Location:  - UK<br>5. Type: Grant/Fund<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): <br>7. Genre: Jazz<br>8. Age: 18+<br>9. Level: Be a working musician who has made at least 40% of your income from music over the past two years. Musicians with a long-term health condition and/​or disability that impacts their ability to work as a musician will just need to show some income from music within the past 2 years.<br>10. Instruments: All<br>11. Other Tags: Free<br>12. Cost: Free<br>13. About Opportunity: The Peter Whittingham Jazz Award supports emerging jazz artists or groups with the creativity and ambition to build a career in music.<br><br>Since starting in 1990, it has become a prestigious and influential award, with previous winners including Xhosa Cole, Soweto Kinch, Errollyn Wallen and Roller Trio.<br><br>One awardee will receive: <br>£5,000 in financial support towards your work. This could include recording new material, a period of mentoring, promotional activity and much more <br>One-to-one business advice, tailored to your needs and delivered via experienced music industry professionals<br>In addition, a further £5,000 is distributed between musicians demonstrating potential to make an impact in the scene. Those musicians will also receive one-to-one business advice.<br>14. When: Annual application windows - check opportunity page for more details<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://www.helpmusicians.org.uk/get-support/develop-as-a-musician/peter-whittingham-jazz-awards<br>16. Organisation Name: Help Musicians<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: <br>19. Only for London/Local?: Local Only<br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
