          <Data name="13. About Opportunity">
            <value>The Peter Whittingham Jazz Award supports emerging jazz artists or groups with the creativity and ambition to build a career in music.

Since starting in 1990, it has become a prestigious and influential award, with previous winners including Xhosa Cole, Soweto Kinch, Errollyn Wallen and Roller Trio.

One awardee will receive: 
£5,000 in financial support towards your work. This could include recording new material, a period of mentoring, promotional activity and much more 
One-to-one business advice, tailored to your needs and delivered via experienced music industry professionals
In addition, a further £5,000 is distributed between musicians demonstrating potential to make an impact in the scene. Those musicians will also receive one-to-one business advice.</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="14. When">
            <value>Annual application windows - check opportunity page for more details</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="15. Opportunity Website / Signup">
