        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: National (UK Wide)<br>3. County: UK Wide<br>4. Location:  - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): Orchestra<br>7. Genre: Orchestral<br>8. Age: 13 - 18<br>9. Level: Grade 8 (or equivalent)<br>10. Instruments: Piccolo/Flute, Clarinet, Oboe, Cor Anglais, Bassoon, Trumpet, Trombone, Tuba, Horns, Harp, Violin, Viola, Cello, Double Bass, Percussion, Euphonium, Saxophone, Rap<br>11. Other Tags: Audition, Grade 8, Free<br>12. Cost: Free<br>13. About Opportunity: Open up your world when you join The National Youth Orchestra. Take on new <br>ideas, meet new friends, visit new places and explore music like never before.  <br>You will join a nationwide community of musicians who are just as passionate as <br>you about orchestral music. You will experience every second of this musical <br>adventure with them by your side, playing your part in shaping a welcoming <br>environment for everyone to thrive.  <br>You will reach new heights as a musician through coaching from NYO’s world<br>class musical and support teams. This will give you the confidence to conquer <br>huge musical challenges.   <br>Play massive orchestral masterworks and stunning ensemble music, whilst <br>exploring new musical concepts and the work of a diverse range of composers.   <br>You will perform with and for teenagers across the UK. With the guidance of <br>leading creative innovators, you’ll find new ways to perform and present the music <br>you love, in concert halls, schools and surprising spaces and places.<br>14. When: Annually<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://www.nyo.org.uk/get-involved/the-nyo-orchestra<br>16. Organisation Name: National Youth Orchestra<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: <br>19. Only for London/Local?: No Restriction<br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
