      <Placemark>
        <name>West Sussex Youth Orchestra</name>
        <address>Horsham Music Centre - UK</address>
        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South East<br>3. County: West Sussex<br>4. Location: Horsham Music Centre - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): Orchestra<br>7. Genre: Orchestral<br>8. Age: Under 21<br>9. Level: Grade 5+<br>10. Instruments: <br>11. Other Tags: Audition, Grade 5, Grade 6, Grade 7, Grade 8<br>12. Cost: From £78 per term<br>13. About Opportunity: West Sussex Youth Orchestra sits at the pinnacle of the progression of string orchestras & wind bands offered by West Sussex Music. Performances include the finals of the Music for Youth National Festival at Symphony Hall, Birmingham, and venues across West Sussex and toured Europe.<br><br>Current repertoire includes:<br><br>Brahms Academic Festival Overture<br>Elgar Pomp and Circumstance<br>Schubert Unfinished Symphony<br>Stravinsky – Firebird<br>Patrick Doyle & John Williams – Harry Potter<br>Tchaikovsky – Swan Lake<br>14. When: Saturdays (Term Time)<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: <br>16. Organisation Name: West Sussex Music<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: https://westsussexmusic.co.uk<br>19. Only for London/Local?: <br>20. Extra Notes: Who can join?  Grade 5 and above, by audition<br>(Please note: Members of WSYO are also expected to be part of our West Sussex Youth String/Wind Orchestras)<br><br>When does the orchestra take place? Rehearsals take place on Saturdays during term-time at Horsham Music Centre, c/o Millais School, Depot Road, RH13 5HR<br><br>How do I apply to join West Sussex Youth Orchestra? Click the button below to apply, and we will get in touch with you to arrange an audition<br>]]></description>
