        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South East<br>3. County: West Sussex<br>4. Location: The Phoenis Centre, Bognor Regis - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): Choir<br>7. Genre: Choral<br>8. Age: 9 - 13<br>9. Level: Any Ability<br>10. Instruments: <br>11. Other Tags: No Experience<br>12. Cost: From £78 per term<br>13. About Opportunity: West Sussex Youth Choir<br><br>West Sussex Youth Choir is a mixed-voice choir for experienced singers aged 13yrs to 21yrs. We learn large-scale choral works, with opportunities to perform with an orchestra, as well as lighter and more contemporary repertoire.<br><br>An ability to read music isn’t essential and sessions offer a chance for singers to build their skills and confidence with a focus on having fun and being creative. Singers with changing voices are supported during rehearsals as they find their new tenor and bass registers.<br><br>Who can join?  Anyone aged 13yrs to 21yrs with a passion for singing.<br>Apply now and try something new!<br><br>When does the choir take place? Rehearsals take place on Saturdays, 9am – 10:30am at Horsham Music Centre, c/o Millais School, RH13 5HR<br>14. When: Saturdays 9:00 - 10:30<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://www.westsussexmusic.co.uk/bognor-regis-music-centre/<br>16. Organisation Name: West Sussex Music<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: https://westsussexmusic.co.uk<br>19. Only for London/Local?: <br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
