        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South East<br>3. County: West Sussex<br>4. Location: St Joseph's CE Junior School, Chichester - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): Orchestra<br>7. Genre: Orchestral<br>8. Age: Young Musicians<br>9. Level: Grade 2 - 5<br>10. Instruments: <br>11. Other Tags: Grade 2, Grade 3, Grade 4, Grade 5<br>12. Cost: From £78 per term<br>13. About Opportunity: An ensemble programme for intermediate level players.<br><br>Our Training Orchestras offer young musicians a fun and supportive environment to develop their skills, make music, and build friendships.<br><br>There are two training orchestras – Training Strings and Training Winds. Both orchestras rehearse weekly at Horsham Music Centre, and perform at the end of every term at concert venues across West Sussex.<br><br>These groups are ideal for learners of orchestral instruments working at junior to intermediate standard – Grade 2 to Grade 4.<br>Led by experienced specialist tutors, sessions include varied and exciting repertoire that’s carefully chosen to match the group’s ability and inspire confidence.<br><br>There are approximately 10 sessions per term, with a public concert celebrating what’s been learned at the end of each term.<br><br>If you have any questions please contact: music.centre@westsussexmusic.co.uk<br>14. When: Saturdays 11:00 - 12:00<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://www.westsussexmusic.co.uk/chichester-music-centre/<br>16. Organisation Name: West Sussex Music<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: https://westsussexmusic.co.uk<br>19. Only for London/Local?: <br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
