          <Data name="13. About Opportunity">
            <value>An ensemble programme for intermediate level players.

Our Training Orchestras offer young musicians a fun and supportive environment to develop their skills, make music, and build friendships.

There are two training orchestras – Training Strings and Training Winds. Both orchestras rehearse weekly at Horsham Music Centre, and perform at the end of every term at concert venues across West Sussex.

These groups are ideal for learners of orchestral instruments working at junior to intermediate standard – Grade 2 to Grade 4.
Led by experienced specialist tutors, sessions include varied and exciting repertoire that’s carefully chosen to match the group’s ability and inspire confidence.

There are approximately 10 sessions per term, with a public concert celebrating what’s been learned at the end of each term.

If you have any questions please contact: music.centre@westsussexmusic.co.uk</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="14. When">
            <value>Saturdays 9:00 - 10:15</value>
          </Data>
