        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South East<br>3. County: West Sussex<br>4. Location: Bohunt School, Worthing - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): Choir<br>7. Genre: Choral<br>8. Age: 9 - 13<br>9. Level: Any Ability<br>10. Instruments: <br>11. Other Tags: No Experience<br>12. Cost: From £78 per term<br>13. About Opportunity: West Sussex Young Voices is a treble voice choir that provides younger singers, aged 9yrs to 13yrs with the foundations they need to become outstanding choral singers. This includes learning to sing in parts, music reading skills and developing their individual voices. No previous experience is necessary, just a love of singing and a willingness to learn<br><br>Who can join?  Anyone in aged 9yrs to 13yrs with a passion for singing.<br><br>Where can I join? West Sussex Young Voices rehearses at Bognor Regis Music Centre, Horsham Music Centre and Worthing Music Centre. Apply now and try something new!<br><br>When does the choir take place? Rehearsals take place at Bognor Regis Music Centre on Thursdays 5.15-6.15pm; Worthing Music Centre on  Saturdays 10-11am and, Horsham Music Centre – Saturday Mornings 10.45am-12pm<br>14. When: Saturdays 10:00 - 11:00<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://www.westsussexmusic.co.uk/worthing-music-centre/<br>16. Organisation Name: West Sussex Music<br>17. About Organisation: <br>18. Organisation Website: https://westsussexmusic.co.uk<br>19. Only for London/Local?: <br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
