        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South West<br>3. County: Wiltshire<br>4. Location: Wiltshire Music Centre, Bradford-on-Avon - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): Choir<br>7. Genre: Choral<br>8. Age: 12-<br>9. Level: All abilities<br>10. Instruments: Singing<br>11. Other Tags: No Experience<br>12. Cost: Enquire for more info<br>13. About Opportunity: Be part of our community choir and sing on the WMC stage!<br><br>WMC Chorus is a friendly community choir that gets together for one-off choral projects with professional artists on the WMC stage – for singers who love a new challenge! Our community choir welcomes all Soprano, Alto, Tenor and Bass singers from age 12 and upwards, of all singing abilities – we’d love for you to join us!<br><br>With repertoire ranging from classical, folk and jazz, the choir join with professional ensembles and musicians to experience memorable and unique performances. Previous projects have included work with VOCES8, Tenebrae and the Orchestra of the Age of Enlightenment, as well as jazz vocalists Emma Smith and Denny Ilett alongside GBH Big Band<br><br>this is a ‘project’ choir, which we recruit singers for in advance of each concert. There will then be a short run of rehearsals (usually 4 or 5) before a concert.<br>14. When: this is a ‘project’ choir, which we recruit singers for in advance of each concert. There will then be a short run of rehearsals (usually 4 or 5) before a concert.<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://www.wiltshiremusic.org.uk/project/wmc-chorus/<br>16. Organisation Name: Wiltshire Music Centre (Bradford on Avon)<br>17. About Organisation: A first-class performance venue bringing live music, entertainment and music-making to everyone<br>A rare and unique gem nestled in beautiful rural Wiltshire, offering the best in Classical, Contemporary, Jazz, and Folk music, and Comedy, locally – and a range of creative activities for everyone.<br>18. Organisation Website: https://www.wiltshiremusic.org.uk<br>19. Only for London/Local?: <br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
