        <name>Wiltshire Youth Jazz Orchestra</name>
        <address>Wiltshire Music Centre, Bradford-on-Avon - UK</address>
        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South West<br>3. County: Wiltshire<br>4. Location: Wiltshire Music Centre, Bradford-on-Avon - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): Jazz Band<br>7. Genre: Jazz<br>8. Age: 12 - 21<br>9. Level: Auditioned, invited from Jazz Academy Sessions<br>10. Instruments: <br>11. Other Tags: Audition, Invitation Only<br>12. Cost: £150 per course<br>13. About Opportunity: Wiltshire Youth Jazz Orchestra (WYJO) provides young jazz musicians aged 12-21 from Wiltshire and the surrounding area with opportunities to perform with like-minded young musicians and leading professionals.<br><br>Led by experienced local jazz educator and performer Mike Daniels, the ensemble meets for two courses per year at WMC. Taking part across two weekends and culminating in a concert in our world-class auditorium, WYJO courses give young players the opportunity to push their musical development and learn from visiting guest artists who share their expertise in a fun and welcoming environment. Recent guests have included Jason Rebello, Tim Garland, Laura Jurd, Huw Warren, Steve Banks, Raph Clarkson and Giacomo Smith.<br>14. When: 2 courses per academic year<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://www.wiltshiremusic.org.uk/project/wyjo/<br>16. Organisation Name: Wiltshire Music Centre (Bradford on Avon)<br>17. About Organisation: A first-class performance venue bringing live music, entertainment and music-making to everyone<br>A rare and unique gem nestled in beautiful rural Wiltshire, offering the best in Classical, Contemporary, Jazz, and Folk music, and Comedy, locally – and a range of creative activities for everyone.<br>18. Organisation Website: https://www.wiltshiremusic.org.uk<br>19. Only for London/Local?: <br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
