          <Data name="13. About Opportunity">
            <value>Wiltshire Youth Jazz Orchestra (WYJO) provides young jazz musicians aged 12-21 from Wiltshire and the surrounding area with opportunities to perform with like-minded young musicians and leading professionals.

Led by experienced local jazz educator and performer Mike Daniels, the ensemble meets for two courses per year at WMC. Taking part across two weekends and culminating in a concert in our world-class auditorium, WYJO courses give young players the opportunity to push their musical development and learn from visiting guest artists who share their expertise in a fun and welcoming environment. Recent guests have included Jason Rebello, Tim Garland, Laura Jurd, Huw Warren, Steve Banks, Raph Clarkson and Giacomo Smith.</value>
          </Data>
