        <name>West of England Youth Orchestra</name>
        <address>Wiltshire Music Centre, Bradford-on-Avon - UK</address>
        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South West<br>3. County: Wiltshire<br>4. Location: Wiltshire Music Centre, Bradford-on-Avon - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): Orchestra<br>7. Genre: Orchestral<br>8. Age: 12 - 21<br>9. Level: Grade 6+, trial instead of formal audition process<br>10. Instruments: Piccolo/Flute, Clarinet, Oboe, Cor Anglais, Bassoon, Trumpet, Trombone, Tuba, Harp, Violin, Viola, Cello, Double Bass, Percussion<br>11. Other Tags: Audition<br>12. Cost: £150 per course<br>13. About Opportunity: Make new friends, pursue your creative potential and explore exciting music!<br><br>The West of England Youth Orchestra (WEYO) is a symphony orchestra that provides young musicians aged 12-21 from Wiltshire and the surrounding area with opportunities to perform with other instrumentalists and learn from leading professionals.<br><br>Principally conducted by Tim Redmond (professor of conducting at Guildhall School, London), WEYO meets at WMC three times per year during school holidays for non-residential courses lasting between 4 and 7 days, culminating in concerts in our world-class auditorium. Working with your conductor, a team of exceptional instrumental tutors and totally inspiring guest artists, you will explore new repertoire and push your musical development to new heights!<br><br>For each course, WEYO is joined by an inspirational professional soloist – recent guests have included Charlotte Saluste-Bridoux (violin), Ariel Lanyi (piano), Alice Neary (cello), Ben Goldscheider (French horn), Alexandra Dariescu (piano) and Emily Apps (voice).<br><br>Up next for WEYO… Wallace & Gromit!<br><br>We’re excited to announce that WEYO’s next project in April 2026 will be Wallace & Gromit’s ‘The Wrong Trousers’! In this fun and entertaining family-friendly show, the orchestra will be playing along live to a screening of this iconic animation film, as well as performing other treats designed to introduce the orchestra to an audience of all ages!<br>14. When: 3 courses per academic year<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://www.wiltshiremusic.org.uk/project/weyo/<br>16. Organisation Name: Wiltshire Music Centre (Bradford on Avon)<br>17. About Organisation: A first-class performance venue bringing live music, entertainment and music-making to everyone<br>A rare and unique gem nestled in beautiful rural Wiltshire, offering the best in Classical, Contemporary, Jazz, and Folk music, and Comedy, locally – and a range of creative activities for everyone.<br>18. Organisation Website: https://www.wiltshiremusic.org.uk<br>19. Only for London/Local?: <br>20. Extra Notes: We’re looking for young musicians aged 12-21 interested in finding their next musical adventure! Experience in performing in symphony orchestras or other large ensembles is useful but not essential.<br><br>Instruments based on availability]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1801-9C27B0-labelson</styleUrl>
        <ExtendedData>
          <Data name="2. Region">
