            <value>Grade 6+, trial instead of formal audition process</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="10. Instruments">
            <value>Piccolo/Flute, Clarinet, Oboe, Cor Anglais, Bassoon, Trumpet, Trombone, Tuba, Harp, Violin, Viola, Cello, Double Bass, Percussion</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="11. Other Tags">
            <value>Audition</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="12. Cost">
            <value>£150 per course</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="13. About Opportunity">
            <value><![CDATA[Make new friends, pursue your creative potential and explore exciting music!

The West of England Youth Orchestra (WEYO) is a symphony orchestra that provides young musicians aged 12-21 from Wiltshire and the surrounding area with opportunities to perform with other instrumentalists and learn from leading professionals.

Principally conducted by Tim Redmond (professor of conducting at Guildhall School, London), WEYO meets at WMC three times per year during school holidays for non-residential courses lasting between 4 and 7 days, culminating in concerts in our world-class auditorium. Working with your conductor, a team of exceptional instrumental tutors and totally inspiring guest artists, you will explore new repertoire and push your musical development to new heights!

For each course, WEYO is joined by an inspirational professional soloist – recent guests have included Charlotte Saluste-Bridoux (violin), Ariel Lanyi (piano), Alice Neary (cello), Ben Goldscheider (French horn), Alexandra Dariescu (piano) and Emily Apps (voice).

Up next for WEYO… Wallace & Gromit!

We’re excited to announce that WEYO’s next project in April 2026 will be Wallace & Gromit’s ‘The Wrong Trousers’! In this fun and entertaining family-friendly show, the orchestra will be playing along live to a screening of this iconic animation film, as well as performing other treats designed to introduce the orchestra to an audience of all ages!]]></value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="14. When">
            <value>3 courses per academic year</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="15. Opportunity Website / Signup">
            <value>https://www.wiltshiremusic.org.uk/project/weyo/</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="16. Organisation Name">
            <value>Wiltshire Music Centre (Bradford on Avon)</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="17. About Organisation">
            <value>A first-class performance venue bringing live music, entertainment and music-making to everyone
A rare and unique gem nestled in beautiful rural Wiltshire, offering the best in Classical, Contemporary, Jazz, and Folk music, and Comedy, locally – and a range of creative activities for everyone.</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="18. Organisation Website">
            <value>https://www.wiltshiremusic.org.uk</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="19. Only for London/Local?">
            <value/>
          </Data>
          <Data name="20. Extra Notes">
            <value>We’re looking for young musicians aged 12-21 interested in finding their next musical adventure! Experience in performing in symphony orchestras or other large ensembles is useful but not essential.

Instruments based on availability</value>
          </Data>
        </ExtendedData>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Wiltshire Jazz Academy</name>
        <address>Wiltshire Music Centre, Bradford-on-Avon - UK</address>
        <description><![CDATA[2. Region: South West<br>3. County: Wiltshire<br>4. Location: Wiltshire Music Centre, Bradford-on-Avon - UK<br>5. Type: Ensemble<br>6. Ensemble (if app.): Jazz Group<br>7. Genre: Jazz<br>8. Age: 12 - 18<br>9. Level: Grade 4+ (approx)<br>No experience in jazz needed to join the sessions<br>10. Instruments: All<br>11. Other Tags: <br>12. Cost: £20 per session (first session free)<br>13. About Opportunity: Come along to Wiltshire Jazz Academy! We welcome musicians aged 12-18 who are playing confidently (approximately Grade 4 or equivalent). You do not need to have experience in performing jazz music to join and the sessions are open to all instrumentalists.<br><br>The ensemble was created in partnership with NYJO as a Regional Academy to provide more opportunity in the South West for young people to access high quality jazz tuition. Led by jazz tutor Mike Daniels and visiting guest artists, it provides a perfect progression route to joining Wiltshire Youth Jazz Orchestra, and is a valuable opportunity for jazz musicians at all stages of their development.<br>14. When: Monthly Saturdays, 10:00 - 13:00<br>(check website for exact dates)<br>15. Opportunity Website / Signup: https://www.wiltshiremusic.org.uk/project/wja/<br>16. Organisation Name: Wiltshire Music Centre (Bradford on Avon)<br>17. About Organisation: A first-class performance venue bringing live music, entertainment and music-making to everyone<br>A rare and unique gem nestled in beautiful rural Wiltshire, offering the best in Classical, Contemporary, Jazz, and Folk music, and Comedy, locally – and a range of creative activities for everyone.<br>18. Organisation Website: https://www.wiltshiremusic.org.uk<br>19. Only for London/Local?: <br>20. Extra Notes: ]]></description>
