          <Data name="5. Type">
            <value>Ensemble</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="6. Ensemble (if app.)">
            <value>Jazz Group</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="7. Genre">
            <value>Jazz</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="8. Age">
            <value>12 - 18</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="9. Level">
            <value>Grade 4+ (approx)
No experience in jazz needed to join the sessions</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="10. Instruments">
            <value>All</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="11. Other Tags">
            <value/>
          </Data>
          <Data name="12. Cost">
            <value>£20 per session (first session free)</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="13. About Opportunity">
            <value>Come along to Wiltshire Jazz Academy! We welcome musicians aged 12-18 who are playing confidently (approximately Grade 4 or equivalent). You do not need to have experience in performing jazz music to join and the sessions are open to all instrumentalists.

The ensemble was created in partnership with NYJO as a Regional Academy to provide more opportunity in the South West for young people to access high quality jazz tuition. Led by jazz tutor Mike Daniels and visiting guest artists, it provides a perfect progression route to joining Wiltshire Youth Jazz Orchestra, and is a valuable opportunity for jazz musicians at all stages of their development.</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="14. When">
            <value>Monthly Saturdays, 10:00 - 13:00
(check website for exact dates)</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="15. Opportunity Website / Signup">
            <value>https://www.wiltshiremusic.org.uk/project/wja/</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="16. Organisation Name">
            <value>Wiltshire Music Centre (Bradford on Avon)</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="17. About Organisation">
            <value>A first-class performance venue bringing live music, entertainment and music-making to everyone
A rare and unique gem nestled in beautiful rural Wiltshire, offering the best in Classical, Contemporary, Jazz, and Folk music, and Comedy, locally – and a range of creative activities for everyone.</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="18. Organisation Website">
            <value>https://www.wiltshiremusic.org.uk</value>
          </Data>
          <Data name="19. Only for London/Local?">
            <value/>
          </Data>
          <Data name="20. Extra Notes">
            <value/>
          </Data>
        </ExtendedData>
